title: bul koo kee
directions: Slice beef in thin bite size strips.
Mix beef with all ingredients.
Use hands to mix well.
Put mixed beef into hot greased frypan using 1 tablespoon oil to grease.
Fry quickly until brown and tender.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: fudge bars
directions: Mix together margarine and cocoa.
Cool.
Mix eggs, sugar and flour and add to cooled cocoa mix.
Add vanilla and pecans.
Grease and flour 9 x 9-inch pan.
Add mixture and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: walnut-raisin bread
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Set aside.
In another bowl, cream butter and sugar.
Add egg and orange juice.
Beat well.
Add 1/3 cup of flour mixture. Beat until smooth.
Mix in remaining flour mixture and the pineapple.
Stir in raisins and walnuts.
Pour into a greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes.
Let cool in pan for 10 minutes.
Remove to wire rack to cool completely. Yields 1 loaf.

title: dip for strawberries
directions: Combine cream cheese and marshmallow cream.
Blend well and serve as dip for strawberries and other fruits.
Really good!

title: strawberry sponge cake
directions: Set the oven at 410° to preheat.
Grease and flour an 8 x 10-inch pan.
Sift together the salt, baking powder and flour. Place the eggs in a mixing bowl and beat vigorously until very thick and lemon colored.

title: banana pudding
directions: Put milk in large bowl and add pudding mix.
Mix on low speed until thick.
Add sour cream and mix well.
Fold in Cool Whip. Place a layer of vanilla wafers on the bottom of large, deep dish and cover with a layer of sliced bananas.
Cover this with half of the pudding mixture.
Repeat with another layer.
To dress it up, sprinkle some vanilla wafer crumbs on top.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: curried chicken salad mold
directions: In large bowl, sprinkle gelatin over 1/2 cup cold water.
Let stand 5 minutes to soften.

title: citrus cup
directions: Arrange first 2 fruits in individual serving dishes, alternating grapefruit and orange segments.
Top each with a kumquat and strips of candied pineapple.

title: chicken with noodles
directions: Stew chicken with poultry seasoning until tender.
Remove chicken from broth; cool and debone.
Add noodles to broth and cook until tender.
Add chicken and cream of chicken soup; cover and simmer for 15 minutes.

title: cappuccino sipper
directions: Combine all ingredients in container of an electric blender. Top with cover and process until smooth.
Serve immediately. Makes 2 cups.

title: poppy seed salad
directions: Combine sugar, lemon juice, chopped onion, dijon mustard& salt in blender.
Blend for 5 seconds, while still blending open jar lid and pour in the oil slowly and then the poppy seeds.
You can make this the day before the salad.
For salad mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Pour dressing over salad just before serving.

title: chili
directions: Follow directions on chili mix.
Add chopped onion and finely chopped peppers while browning beef. Let simmer for at least 1 hour.

title: wartime cake
directions: Place first 8 ingredients in saucepan and simmer 10 minutes. Cool, then add rest of ingredients.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 25 minutes.
Makes great cupcakes.

title: shrimp cantonese
directions: Saute shrimp in oil for 1 minute or until shrimp turn pink, using a large skillet.
Add onion and snow peas; cook, stirring 2 minutes.
Add Chinese vegetables which have been rinsed and drained.
Cover and cook 1 minute.
Blend pepper, soy sauce, chicken broth and cornstarch.
Stir into shrimp/vegetable mixture. Cook, stirring until sauce is clear and thickened.

title: low-fat minestrone soup
directions: Combine all ingredients except the spaghetti in a large soup kettle.
Cover and bring to a boil.
Turn down to simmer; simmer until vegetables are done.
Add spaghetti last 10 minutes.
Serve piping hot.

title: fruited freeze
directions: Oil a 3-quart mold or 9 x 13-inch pan.
Thoroughly drain the pineapple.
Measure 1/2 cup reserved pineapple juice and heat to boiling.
Prepare pie filling as directed on package, but substitute the 1/2 cup hot pineapple juice for 1/2 cup boiling water.
Cool.
Blend whipped cream with mayonnaise.
Fold in pineapple, marshmallows, fruit cocktail and cherries. Combine with pie filling.
Pour into prepared pan. Freeze.
Unmold and garnish about 30 minutes before serving.

title: shredded beef
directions: Place everything in roaster.
Cut
onions
medium fine. If roast is frozen, cook at 350°
for 1 hour.	Reduce temperature
to 325° and cook 4 to
hours
longer.
If	roast
is thawed, cook at 250° for 6 hours.
Use
fork to shred meat, if necessary, after cooking.

title: glorified rice
directions: Drain the pineapple; combine it with the sugar.
Stir until sugar dissolves; add to the rice in a large mixing bowl.
Fold in the marshmallows; let stand for at least 1 hour.
Before serving, fold in the whipped cream until blended.
Garnish with cherries and nuts.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: pistachio cake
directions: Beat 5 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes in greased angel food pan.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Melt butter in casserole dish.
Thaw hash browns.
Mix all ingredients together and put in casserole dish, 9 x 13-inches. Bake in 350° oven for about 45 minutes.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to directions on package.
Drain. Rinse with cold water.
Drain.
Pour macaroni into large bowl.
Add onion, eggs, celery and pickles.
Stir.
Add mayonnaise and mustard.
Stir well.
Cover and refrigerate for at least 4 hours. Makes 12 to 14 servings.

title: raspberry cream
directions: Pour boiling water over gelatin in bowl, stirring until gelatin is dissolved.
Stir in ice cream and raspberries, breaking up berries with fork.
Chill until set, about 20 minutes.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Combine
first	4
ingredients	in
a large Dutch oven. Bring to	a boil and cook over low heat about 30 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: peaches and cream cobbler
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients and mix.
Pour batter into 9-inch square baking pan coated with vegetable spray.
Put peaches over batter.
In another bowl, add cream cheese, peach juice and sugar; mix well.
Spoon mixture over peaches; cover peaches completely.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: peanut patties
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients and bring to boil.
Cook on low fire for 1 hour.
Stir occasionally to keep from scorching. Add remaining ingredients.
Remove from heat.
Beat a few minutes. Spread on a greased cookie sheet.
Break into pieces.

title: michigan rocks
directions: Soak raisins in rum for 3 days to a week.
Mix together all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: chicken cheese chowder
directions: Saute the onion and carrots in the margarine until the onion is clear, about 10 minutes.
Add the flour; stir in very well. Add the chicken stock; heat until smooth and thick.
Add the chopped chicken; cook until chicken is done, about 10 to 15 minutes.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook carrots in water until just tender; drain.
Add remaining ingredients and bring to a boil.
Remove from heat; cool and refrigerate.
Will keep for a long time.
The longer the better. Serve hot or cold.

title: fruit crunch
directions: Bring water and sugar to a boil and cool.
Add orange juice, pineapple juice, lemon juice and bananas.
Can be put in ice cube trays for use in individual glasses or freeze in molds for punch bowl.

title: lenten pea soup
directions: Place washed peas into boiling, salted water and cook until soft.
Add barley, celery, carrots and potatoes.
Cook over low heat stirring occasionally to keep from burning.
In a skillet, saute some onion in cooking oil.
Add tomato sauce and mushrooms. Cook a few minutes.
Add to peas.
Cook until vegetables are done.

title: velveeta cheese roll
directions: Roll Velveeta out like bread dough to about 1/4-inch thickness.
Cover with cream cheese.
Sprinkle chopped chilies and onions on top.
Roll up like jelly roll.
Best if you use wax paper, keeps from sticking so much.
Refrigerate 2 hours.
Serve with crackers and grapes.
Slice across.

title: potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes and mash.
Add other ingredients.
Put in casserole.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Can sprinkle more cheese on top, if desired.

title: brian's chili
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; drain.
Add chili seasoning and stir well.
Put into large pan.
Add remainder of ingredients and cook on medium heat, stirring often, about 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to simmer for about 10 to 15 minutes.
Add water if needed.

title: creamsicle cake
directions: Bake cake as directed.
Poke holes in cake.
Mix 1 package jello with 1 cup boiling water until dissolved.
Add 1/2 cup cold water.
Mix, pour over cake.
Refrigerate until completely cooled. Mix pudding with 1 package orange jello and 1 cup milk.
Beat until thickened.
Add vanilla and fold in Cool Whip.
Spread on cooled cake.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except cheese and chips.
Place in 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle cheese on top, then cover with the potato chips.
Bake 15 minutes at 450°.

title: janet's salad dressing
directions: In blender, combine soup (as in the can), onion, cheese, Worcestershire, vinegar, paprika and 1/8 teaspoon pepper.
Blend until all combined.
Through hole in lid or take cover off, gradually add oil in slowly.
Chill in refrigerator 15 minutes to 1/2 hour or longer.
Serve over your favorite salad.

title: acorn squash casserole
directions: Split squash in half; scoop out seeds and fibers (discard). Place squash in small pan, cut side up; add water to bottom of pan.
Cover with foil; bake 35 to 40 minutes.
Remove squash from its shell; combine all ingredients, mixing with electric mixer. Put in 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 375° or until set.

title: cornbread salad
directions: In a bowl, crumble cornbread
and mix in all other ingredients.
Stir in 1 c. of mayonnaise.

title: cocoa pudding
directions: Heat oven to 400 degrees.
Separate eggs, put the whites in a separate bowl for later use for icing.
Add cocoa, sugar, flour, milk flavoring, butter and egg yolks mix together well.
Cook in sauce pan on top of stove, stir often until ingredients began to thicken; do not burn or get too thick.
Pour into baking dish and set aside.

title: chili mac(serves 4)
directions: Brown ground beef, along with onion and green pepper.
Season with garlic powder and black pepper.
Add mushrooms and cook until tender.
Add canned tomatoes (broken up).
Sprinkle with chili powder to taste.
Bring to a boil, then cover and simmer approximately 15 minutes.
Meanwhile, prepare elbow macaroni according to package directions.
Drain macaroni and add to chili mixture.
Let sit for 5 minutes.
Stir and serve.

title: chocolate truffle cookies
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream butter, sugar and cocoa until light and fluffy. Beat in sour cream and vanilla. Add flour and mix well. Stir in chocolate chips. Refrigerate for an hour or so. Roll into 1-inch balls. Dip in the chocolate sprinkles. Place, sprinkles side up, 2-inches apart on ungreased baking sheet. Bake in 325° oven for 10 to 12 minutes. Cool before removing from pan.

title: flavored coffees - bavarian mint
directions: Process in a blender on liquefies until well blended. Store in airtight container.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix margarine, salt, cheese, egg, milk and onion.
Blend ingredients with rice.
Add broccoli to mixture.
Pour into buttered 2 1/2-quart casserole and bake for 45 minutes.

title: ten-minute meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients and shape into a round oval loaf. Place in a microwave-safe dish.
Cover with wax paper and microwave on High for 10 minutes, turning dish after 5 minutes of cooking.
Drain; cover with foil.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Microwaves may vary.
Test for doneness.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Combine all ingredients; form into small balls and chill. Melt in top of double boiler 1/2 cake paraffin and 1 large bag chocolate chips.
After chilling, dip balls in mixture.

title: melon ball
directions: Mix together with shaker and add ice. Can also be done in blender with ice for a slush effect.
Makes 1 serving.

title: pay day bars
directions: Heat first four ingredients in a saucepan.
When melted, stir in peanuts and Rice Krispies.
When cake is removed from oven, cover with marshmallows, then cover with the saucepan mixture. Cool to room temperature, then refrigerate, covered.
Cut cold.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Melt butter; set aside.
Beat eggs well.
Add all ingredients. Bake 40 or 45 minutes at 325° or 350°.

title: black forest torte
directions: Place all ingredients except eggs in a mixing bowl.
Beat together at medium speed for 4 or 5 minutes.
Add whole eggs and beat for 2 minutes.
Pour into 4 buttered 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes.
Cool before filling.
Spread first layer with half of chocolate filling.
Add the second layer and cover with half of cream filling.
Repeat, having cream filling on top.
Chill cake until firm before serving.

title: five bean salad
directions: Cook bacon in a large Dutch oven until crisp; drain well, reserving 1/4 cup drippings in Dutch oven.
Crumble bacon; set aside.
Add sugar, cornstarch, salt and pepper to drippings.
Stir until smooth.
Gradually add vinegar and water; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened and bubbly.

title: cinnamon cut-outs(do not eat)
directions: Knead applesauce and cinnamon together to form a "dough" ball. Roll out on flat surface using cinnamon to prevent dough from sticking (the way you would use flour).
Roll out 1/2 inch thick for normal size cookie cutter, thinner for mini's.
Remember to use a toothpick to make a hole for hanging.
Place cut-outs on cookie sheets and set aside to dry (approximately 2 days).
Hang with narrow satin ribbons.
Use as tree ornaments, package decorations, wreath decorations, etc.

title: cream of parisienne
directions: Cook frozen vegetables in 2 cups water.
Do not drain.
Melt butter.
Add celery and onion; saute until clear.
Add flour.
Stir until blended.
Add bouillon cubes and milk to butter mixture. Stir and cook until thick and smooth.
Add vegetables and liquid. Add ham and seasonings.
Simmer until heated through.

title: cranberry freezer pie
directions: Beat cream
cheese
until fluffy.
Slowly add condensed milk, beating until smooth.
Stir in cranberry sauce.
Fold in topping; pour into crust.
Chill for 2 hours.

title: cranberry orange relish
directions: Wash and slice cucumbers thin in pan (not aluminum or metal). Slice onions over, sprinkle with canning salt.
Put ice cubes over top.
Refrigerate.
Set for 2 hours or overnight and drain.
Rinse off pickles.
Cook up cup of vinegar to cup of sugar.
Boil up and pour over pickles.
Put in refrigerator or freezer.
These are crisp.

title: beef and potato casserole
directions: Arrange potatoes in a greased 2-quart casserole. Sprinkle with next four ingredients and set aside.

title: 15 minute dinner
directions: In a large pot, put the garden peas in 2-quarts of water. Bring to a boil and add macaroni.
Cook until macaroni is done and then drain.
Put butter and milk in pot; add cheese mix, then add drained macaroni and peas and then chicken.
(Can substitute tuna for chicken.)

title: creamy cheese grits
directions: Combine chicken broth and whipping cream in large sauce pan; bring to a boil.
Stir in grits, and return in cheese.
Cool 10 minutes.
Yield: 5 3/4 cups.

title: chicken soup
directions: Put the chicken and giblets, water and next 5 ingredients into soup kettle.
(Save 3 carrots and 3 celery stalks for later.) Cover and bring to a boil.
Skim off the foam.
Simmer for 2 hours or until meat is tender.
Remove meat, vegetables and peppercorns. Discard cooked vegetables and peppercorns.
Strain stock, if desired.

title: turkey spaghetti
directions: Spray nonstick pan and brown chopped bell pepper, onion and garlic with ground turkey.
Add seasoning, salt and pepper.
Add tomatoes and tomato sauce and sugar; bring to boil, then turn down to simmer for 1 hour.
Pour over spaghetti.
Mix well.
Serve.

title: done buttered rolls
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix all ingredients.
Spoon into small muffin tins.
Bake for about 15 minutes or until golden.
Makes about 36.

title: cream cheese pecan pie
directions: In a large mixer bowl at medium speed, beat together until smooth the cream cheese, 1 teaspoon vanilla, 1 egg and 1/3 cup sugar.
Spread over the bottom of pastry shell.
Sprinkle with the pecans.
In a large mixing bowl at medium speed, beat the remaining 3 eggs.
Add the corn syrup, 1/4 cup sugar, salt and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Beat until blended.

title: campbelled eggs
directions: Stir soup until smooth.
Blend in eggs and pepper.
In skillet, melt butter.
Pour in egg mix.
Cook over low heat until set.

title: swiss meat loaf
directions: Mix meat and cheese; add eggs.
Combine rest of ingredients, except milk; mix well.
Add milk and mix well.
Form into a greased loaf pan or baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: tomato relish(servings:  approximately 3 pints)
directions: Boil slowly for 3 hours or until tender.
Seal in sterilized jars.

title: blueberry pinwheel cobbler
directions: Combine sugar and water in a saucepan; stir well.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, just until sugar dissolves. Stir in vanilla; set aside.
Cut shortening into flour until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Add milk, stirring just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Turn dough out onto a lightly floured surface; knead 4 or 5 times.
Roll dough into a 12 x 9-inch rectangle.
Spread blueberries over dough and roll up, jelly roll fashion, beginning with long side.
Set aside.
Melt butter in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Cut dough into 12 (1-inch) slices. Place slices, cut side down, in butter.
Pour sugar syrup over slices.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes, or until golden.

title: mom's cheese roll
directions: Let Velveeta soften.
Put between pieces of wax paper and roll into rectangle with rolling pin about 1/4 inch thick.
Spread with softened cream cheese.
Sprinkle chopped olives and chilies over top.
Roll like jelly roll from long edge.
Cut in half, wrap in wax paper, then foil and chill before serving or freeze for later use.
Serve with crackers.

title: banana-pineapple cake
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients. Add and stir (do not beat) remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased and floured pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes. Cool in pan.
Serve plain or with ice cream or whipped topping.

title: elephant stew
directions: Cut elephant into bite-sized pieces.
This should take about 2 months.
Cover with brown gravy.
Cook over kerosene fire about 4 weeks at 465°.
This will serve about 3,800 people.
If more are expected, 2 rabbits may be added.
But do this only if absolutely necessary, as most people don't like to find hare in their soup.

title: seafood cocktail dip
directions: Combine all ingredients; chill 2 hours.
Makes 2 1/2 cups of dip.
Serve with your favorite crackers, Town House or Escort crackers.

title: moist carrot cake
directions: Combine eggs, oil, milk, sugar and vanilla; mix well.
Combine flour, cinnamon, baking soda and salt; stir into egg mixture. Stir in pineapple, carrots, nuts and coconut.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes or until cake tests done.
Do not overbake.

title: chinese pork and green beans
directions: Heat oil in a large skillet, saute pork 15 minutes over high heat.
Add onion, garlic and water chestnuts; cook 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Mix in a cup of broth.
Bring to a boil; stir in green beans, celery and mushrooms.
Cook 1 minute, then cover and cook until vegetables are tender.
Combine cornstarch, soy sauce, salt and remaining broth in a small bowl.
Pour into skillet and stir until thickened.
Serve with rice.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Saute onion with oil.
Add ground beef and brown.
Grease with butter a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Boil 6 potatoes (peeled) for 40 minutes.
Mash with milk and butter.
Place ground beef and onion in bottom of casserole dish.
Add a tablespoon of Worcestershire sauce.
Drain can of peas and layer peas over beef. Place mashed potatoes on top of peas; dab with butter.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Broil for 3 to 5 minutes, then serve.
Makes 4 servings.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Thaw shrimp.
On pizza pan, spread cream cheese evenly.
Pour cocktail sauce over top.
Clean shrimp.
In single layer, lay shrimp on top of cocktail sauce.
Dip tortilla chips and enjoy!

title: creme de menthe cake
directions: Add water and 1/3 cup of creme de menthe to cake mix.
Blend and beat for 2 minutes.
Bake with directions on box.
Cool.

title: chopped kraut salad
directions: Stir and marinate all day.
Keeps well.

title: meat loaf supreme
directions: Mix meat, oats, salt, pepper, eggs, onion, celery and catsup; shape into a loaf.
Cover with sauce.
Pour water in baking dish over loaf.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: moist turkey, grilled
directions: Fire a generous amount of charcoal; when they're all red, push them evenly to the sides of your grill, forming a circle.
Now put fresh charcoal cubes on top of the hot coals (be generous).
In the center of the hole (or circle opening), place a medium pot of water.
Place cooking rack and set turkey over pot of water under rack.
Turkey should be in a large baking pan.
Put a handkerchief, soaked in butter, over turkey.
Close grill lid and go shopping.
Turkey will be done in about 6 hours.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Mix oleo, oil and sugar.
Add eggs, vanilla and milk.
Mix well and add cocoa, flour, baking powder, baking soda and cinnamon.
Mix and add zucchini.
Pour in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 60 minutes.
May sprinkle powdered sugar over top of cake while warm. Needs not to be frosted.

title: cheese and sausage balls
directions: Brown sausage.
Mix sausage, Cheddar cheese and water.
Stir in the Bisquick/self-rising flour.
Drop in small muffin tins. Bake at 400° until brown.

title: dinner rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add sugar and baking powder. Let stand 20 minutes.
Scald the milk.
Add margarine, sugar, salt and eggs.
Combine all with the flour.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Roll out 2 hours before serving.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.

title: green chili enchilada pie
directions: Cook and drain hamburger.
Mix in Fritos and spread in casserole dish. Combine onion, soup, milk and chilies.
Pour over hamburger mixture and top with cheese.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes. Serves 10.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish with olive oil.
Saute onions and garlic in olive oil until clear.
Add zucchini, mushrooms, red pepper and seasonings until tender.
Beat eggs in separate large bowl; add cheese and sauteed vegetables. Pour into baking dish and bake for approximately 25 minutes or until knife comes out clean.

title: lentil loaf
directions: Mix together and put in a greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: garlic chicken
directions: Blend ingredients together.
Take pastry brush and apply to the chicken.
Bake at 350° until tender.

title: beef burgundy
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in oven for 3 hours at 350°.
Serve over rice or noodles or top with Chinese noodles. Serves 8.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Saute celery and onion in margarine.
Cook rice and broccoli as directed.
Combine can of soup with 1/2 can of water.
Add Cheez Whiz to hot soup and heat.
Combine with remaining ingredients in 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken gumbo
directions: Put rice in bottom of oblong baking dish.
Place washed chicken pieces on top of rice; salt and pepper to taste.
Pour cream of chicken soup and then cream of mushroom soup over chicken (in that order) and add water.
Bake at 375° for 2 hours.
Add extra water if needed.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix together flour, cinnamon, salt, soda, baking powder, vanilla, chopped nuts and grated zucchini squash.
Add to eggs, sugar and oil.
Mix well.
Bake in loaf pans 50 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: orange raisin cake
directions: Cream margarine, sugar and orange rind.
Beat in eggs.
Mix raisins with 1/4 cup dry ingredients.
Mix dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture, alternately with buttermilk.
Add raisins and nuts.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut each biscuit into 4 pieces.
Roll pieces in sugar-cinnamon mixture.
Place pieces in greased tube pan until all are used. Sprinkle layers with pecans, raisins or coconut if desired.

title: easy cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to package directions in 9 x 12-inch pan.
While warm punch holes in cake with 2 pronged fork. Pour Eagle Brand milk over cake.
Spread crushed pineapple over cake.
Sprinkle coconut over cake.
Spread Cool Whip over cake and sprinkle with remaining coconut and chopped pecans.
Garnish with cherry per square when serving.
Serve chilled.

title: a fast salad
directions: Put dry Jell-O into cottage cheese.
Mix.
Add Cool Whip, drained fruit and nuts.
May be chilled or used right away.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Boil first 3 ingredients for 10 minutes.
Add Marshmallow Creme and peanut butter.
Mix with electric mixer and pour into greased pan.
Cool and cut into pieces.

title: green beans with walnuts
directions: Wash and trim beans; cook for about 5 minutes in boiling water until just tender-crisp.
Drain and refresh with cold water; drain.
Heat oil in large skillet.
Saute walnuts for 3 minutes over medium heat until lightly browned.
Add garlic, beans and lemon juice; toss to coat.
Season with salt and pepper.
Makes 4 servings.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix eggs, oil, sugar, vanilla and zucchini; beat well.
Mix dry ingredients together.
Add to the first mixture and beat well. Stir in raisins and nuts.
Bake in three small loaf pans, well greased and floured, in preheated oven at 350° for one hour.

title: toffee bars
directions: Cream butter, sugar, vanilla and egg.
Add flour and mix well. Add chips and nuts.
Press into ungreased pan and bake 25 minutes at 350°.
When cool, ice with chocolate icing.

title: nikas peach pork chops
directions: Season pork chops with salt and pepper. Brown in shortening over medium heat about 5 minutes per side.	Put pork chops in single layer in casserole dish.
Drain oil from pan used to brown pork chops.
Put apple juice and frozen peaches in blender.
Blend until smooth.
Add cornstarch and blend for additional 30 seconds. Pour mixture into pan and bring to boil; pour
over pork chops. Cover tightly and bake in 300° oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach and squeeze out all liquid.
Combine remaining ingredients and store in refrigerator overnight.
Serve with vegetables as dippers such as carrot sticks, celery sticks, zucchini, broccoli, etc. or large pretzel sticks.

title: oatmeal date bars
directions: Melt butter and mix all ingredients in large bowl. Form into bars or balls and coat in chocolate.

title: congratulations chiffon cake
directions: Sift into the first bowl the flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Make a well and add oil, egg yolks, water, vanilla and lemon rind.
Mix well.
In a large bowl, beat egg whites and cream of tartar until stiff peaks form.
Pour yolk mix slowly over whites, blending carefully with a spatula.
Pour into ungreased tube pan and bake 55 minutes.
Increase to 350° for 10 to 15 minutes more.
Cool over bottle upside down.

title: cheesy baked potatoes
directions: Wash and peel potatoes then slice in thin slices. Place potatoes on bottom of 9 x 13 baking dish. Mix cheese soup and mushroom soup in separate bowl. Add water to thin mixture (about 1 soup can). Pour over potatoes. Sprinkle with cheese and bacon bits. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until potatoes are tender (uncovered).

title: crispy chili-corn baked chicken
directions: Wash chicken pieces and pat dry.
Measure buttermilk into shallow glass baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients, except margarine, in a resealable bag; shake to mix well.
Coat chicken pieces in buttermilk; place chicken, a few pieces at a time, in a zipper top bag and shake to coat evenly.
Repeat with remaining chicken and place, meaty sides up, in baking pan.
Bake in preheated 375° oven until chicken is fork-tender and juices run clear, about 45 minutes.
Brush tops of chicken lightly with margarine halfway through baking time.

title: calico rice
directions: In a skillet or saucepan, saute peppers and onion in butter for 3 minutes. Stir in the rice, soup mix, picante or salsa, cumin, garlic, salt and water.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 20 to 25 minutes or until rice is tender. Garnish with sour cream, if desired. Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: all-american strawberry pie
directions: Bake and cool pie shell as package directs; set aside.
In 3-quart saucepan combine pudding mix and milk.
Cook and cool for pie, as package directs.
Pour into cooled crust.
Chill several hours until set.
Spread 1 cup of whipped topping over filling. Arrange strawberries and blueberries on top.
Pipe or dollop with remaining whipped topping.
Just before serving, dust with powdered sugar.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: marinades(beef)
directions: Marinating times (in refrigerator):

fish or shrimp 20 to 30 minutes, chicken 30 minutes to 2 hours, beef or pork strips 30 minutes to 2 hours, steaks 30 minutes to 2 hours, cubes 1 hour to 24 hours, chops 30 minutes to 2 hours, roast 12 hours to 24 hours and ribs 12 hours to 24 hours.

title: moist 'n chewy brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Melt chips and butter.
Add other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan sprayed with Pam.

title: zucchini patties
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients with salt and pepper, then add rest of ingredients.
Drop spoonfuls into hot skillet until brown. Turn and brown other side.	Delicious.

title: cream puff
directions: In saucepan add the water and butter/oleo.
Bring to a boil and add flour gradually.
Stir until smooth, like a paste, on low flame.
Once flour is all mixed in, remove from stove.
Let cool 20 minutes.
Add 4 eggs, one at a time.
Beat with wooden spoon.
In a greased 9 x 13-inch dish add the paste, spreading it on the bottom. Bake 35 minutes in 400° oven.
When removed from oven, wrap paper towel around hand and press any air bubbles that may be there, out. Mix the milk and pudding and softened cream cheese with mixer, beat well until very thick.
Spread over the cool crust.
Add Cool Whip on top and refrigerate.

title: low-fat spinach vegetable dip
directions: In a medium bowl mix all ingredients (except raw vegetables). Cover and chill.
Makes 3 cups.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt chocolate and peanut butter.
Mix with cereal.
Dump into a large brown bag which has the powdered sugar in the bottom. Shake well and put on a large cookie sheet to crisp up.

title: minnesota pumpkin bread
directions: Combine sugar, oil, pumpkin and egg.
Beat until smooth.
In another bowl, combine flour, powder, soda and spices.
To plump raisins, boil 1/3 cup water and raisins and let stand for 5 minutes.
Mix wet and dry ingredients together, folding in raisins and any remaining soaking water and nuts.
Bake in a loaf pan sprayed with nonstick cooking spray.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: In a large bowl, combine eggs and sugar, beating well.
Add pumpkin, mixing until blended.
In a separate bowl, combine flour, baking powder, spices and salt.
Add to egg mixture, mixing well. Spread batter into a greased and wax paper lined 10 x 15-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Remove from pan. Cool for 15 minutes.
Place cake on clean tea towel.
Cool 10 minutes longer.
From 10-inch side, roll cake up in towel.
Set aside.
Meantime, prepare filling.

title: spanish rice supper
directions: In a skillet, cook onions and pepper in butter about 3 minutes, until soft.
Add beef and cook until lightly browned. Stir in tomato soup, water, vinegar, salt, basil and oregano, blending well.
Stir in the cooked rice and pimento.
Put in 2-quart casserole dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pecan tarts
directions: Melt
margarine
in
small pan.
Pour sugar into mixing bowl. Pour
margarine
directly into sugar.
Measure oatmeal. Add enough
water
to wet oatmeal thoroughly (water will cook out). Add
oatmeal to sugar and margarine mixture.
Add syrup and salt. Whip mixture.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Mix egg, margarine, vanilla, milk, oil and rhubarb; set aside. Mix sugar, flour, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Mix all together and add nuts; pour into greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix 1 1/2 sticks melted butter with graham cracker crumbs. Spread over bottom of container.
Refrigerate.
Mix 2 sticks melted butter, powdered sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Beat 20 minutes at medium speed.
Spread over crust.
Place sliced bananas lengthwise on filling.
Spread drained pineapple over bananas. Prepare Dream Whip as directed as package.
Spread over pineapple. Top with cherries and pecan chips.
Place cherries as centers of cutting squares.

title: seafoam candy
directions: In 2 quart saucepan combine sugar, syrup and water.
Cook; stirring constantly until sugar dissolves and starts boiling. Cook on medium heat, without stirring, to 260° (hard ball). Remove from heat.
In large bowl beat egg whites to stiff peak. Gradually pour hot syrup over egg whites; beating constantly on high 6 minutes.
Add vanilla; keep beating for 10 more minutes until soft peaks form and starts losing gloss.
Add nuts; mix. Let stand 2 minutes.
Drop by teaspoon onto buttered baking sheet. Bake 20 minutes at 300°.

title: cherry yum yum
directions: In oblong pan, place graham cracker crumbs for crust.
Mix Cool Whip, cream cheese, milk and sugar with electric mixer. Spread half the mixture over crust.
Pour cherry pie filling over mixture.
Pour other half of the mixture over cherries.
Sprinkle graham cracker crumbs on top and refrigerate for 1 hour.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Mix well and roll out on floured board.
Handle as little as possible.
This makes 3 to 4 crusts.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Sift flour, sugar and baking soda together. Melt margarine, cocoa and water over low heat and bring to a boil. Pour over dry ingredients. Add buttermilk, eggs and vanilla and mix well. Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Pour frosting on cake while warm.

title: chicken (or turkey) and artichoke casserole
directions: Saute chopped onions and mushrooms in oil.
Drain artichoke hearts well and quarter.
Make sauce by melted butter; add flour, milk and chicken stock.
Cook and stir until thick and smooth. Remove from heat.
Add 1/4 cup cheese and 3 tablespoons sherry if desired.
Season if needed.
Pour sauce over chicken, artichokes, mushrooms and onions; mix well.
Put into casserole dish.
Put remaining cheese on top.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Can add olives and pimento for color if desired.
Bake uncovered at 375° for 40 to 50 minutes or until hot.
This can be prepared ahead of time and refrigerated for 2 to 3 days.

title: stir-fry veggies
directions: Heat oil in large skillet on medium high heat.
Add veggies; cook and stir until tender-crisp.
Sprinkle salad dressing mix over veggies; toss to coat well.
Stir in vinegar until well mixed.
Serve warm.

title: sugarless cake*
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Beat eggs and vanilla; add to dry mixture.
Add melted butter, applesauce, raisins and nuts.
Bake in tube pan in 350 °oven for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream oleo and sugar.
Beat in vanilla and egg, then add flour and soda.
Blend in milk and mix well.
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Dip glass in sugar and press on cookies. Bake at 325° for 6 to 8 minutes.

title: aggie salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add raspberries, mashed with a potato masher.
Add applesauce.
Serve with sour cream with sugar added.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown ground beef; drain and add salt and pepper.
Spread in casserole dish or long cake pan.
Spread pizza sauce over meat and sprinkle cheese over sauce. Combine Bisquick with milk and eggs and pour over casserole (mixture will be thin).
Bake at 400° for about 40 minutes or until brown.

title: pink delight(frozen dessert)
directions: Mix together and pour into a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Freeze overnight.
Will keep for weeks (frozen) and is so easy that it is perfect to keep on hand for unexpected guests or dinners.

title: chocolate pudding pizza
directions: You also need 1 (12-inch) foil pizza pan.

title: chicken-macaroni salad
directions: Prepare macaroni according to package directions; drain.
In medium bowl, combine macaroni, chicken and next 4 ingredients; mix well.
In small bowl, blend remaining ingredients.
Add to salad mixture; toss to coat.
Cover and chill thoroughly.
Toss gently before serving.
Garnish as desired.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: cabbage slaw
directions: Mix cabbage, carrot and bell pepper.
Blend vinegar, sugar, celery seed and mayonnaise.
Mix all together and store in refrigerator.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Boil sugar, syrup, water, vinegar and oleo; add vanilla. After mixture is cooked, boil until mixture forms hard ball in cold water.
Add
vanilla;
stir.
Pour
over the popped corn; dip your hands in cold water so mixture won't stick to them.
I usually double this batch.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits in quarters.
Put 3/4 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon in a plastic bag.
Put biscuits in bag and shake good on all.
Layer in tube pan.
Mix butter, brown sugar and 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon.
Heat this mixture and pour on top of coated biscuits. Cook at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sour cream chicken enchiladas
directions: Mix chicken soup, chicken, 3/4 pint sour cream, green chilies, salt and onions.
Place filling in each tortilla with a small amount of cheese.
Roll.
Place in baking dish that has been lined with small amount of filling.
Assemble all enchiladas; add remaining filling on top, then add remaining sour cream and cheese. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Break cauliflower up into bite size pieces.
Sprinkle the Zesty Italian dressing on it and pour peas over it.
Next, sprinkle the Cheddar cheese on.
Put enough Hellmann's (approximately 3/4 of a gallon jug) over top to cover. Let set overnight.
Next day, stir and mix.

title: gelatin strawberries
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and refrigerate overnight. Shape into berries and roll into jello. Make confectioners sugar icing with green food coloring and drizzle over top like leaves.

title: chili con queso casserole
directions: Grease square pan,

8 x 8 x 2 inches. Sprinkle chilies and tomato evenly in pan. Beat remaining ingredients with wire whisk or hand beater until smooth; pour over top. Heat oven to 375°. Bake uncovered 35 to 40 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
This has 18 grams carbohydrates.

title: tex mex dip
directions: Spread dip in bottom of 9 x 13-inch dish.
Mash avocados with lemon juice and salt and pepper.
Drain off lemon juice.
Spread over bean dip.
Mix sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasoning. Spread over previous layer.
Top with onions, tomatoes and olives. Cover with cheese.
Chill overnight if possible.

title: italian chicken
directions: Dip chicken in dressing.
Roll in crumbs.
Bake at 375° until done.

title: broccoli cheese casserole
directions: Melt margarine and saute onions.
Add cheese, soup and garlic powder.
Melt slow.
Cook the broccoli; drain.
Put broccoli in casserole dish and pour in sauce.
Top with Durkee onions.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: garlic bread and butter pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers thoroughly, using a vegetable brush; drain on rack.
Slice unpeeled cucumbers into 1/8-inch or 1/4-inch slices; discard ends.
Add onions and garlic.
Add salt and mix thoroughly. Cover with crushed ice or ice cubes; let stand 3 hours.
Drain thoroughly; remove garlic cloves.
Combine sugar, spices and vinegar; heat just to boiling.
Add drained cucumbers and onion slices and heat 5 minutes.

title: kale greens
directions: Place the meat in the water with the red pepper.
Cook with lid on for about 1 1/2 hours or until meat is tender.
Wash kale several times.
Trim off the root and heavier part of the leaf. Remove meat and put the kale in; cook until tender.
Replace the meat on top and heat thoroughly.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: beef stew
directions: Coat meat with flour.
Slowly brown meat in hot fat on all sides.
Add salt, pepper, chopped onions, bay leaf and garlic. Slowly stir in hot water or meat stock and canned tomatoes.
Add Worcestershire sauce.
Cover pan and simmer 2 hours until meat is tender.
Add sliced celery, whole onions, carrots cut into 2-inch lengths and potatoes.
Sprinkle vegetables with salt and pepper. Cover and simmer 20 to 30 minutes longer until vegetables are tender.
(If serving with dumplings, 15 minutes before end of cooking time drop dumplings by the spoonful on top of bubbling stew and cover tightly.)
Place meat and vegetables in middle of a hot platter.
Surround them with dumplings.
Serves 6.

title: carrot layer cake
directions: Mix sugar and salad oil, then add eggs, soda, flour, powder, cinnamon and salt, one at a time.
Mix in nuts and carrots.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Makes 3 layers.

title: savory salmon patties
directions: In a medium bowl, combine salmon, potatoes, yogurt, mustard, egg white, carrot, onion, paprika and lemon juice.
Shape into 8 patties.
Put bread crumbs on a plate and coat the patties with the crumbs.

title: chicken basque(microwave)
directions: Cut larger pieces of chicken in half for uniform size. Combine all ingredients in 4-quart casserole. Cook, covered, in microwave for 30 minutes or until done, stirring once. If desired, thicken sauce with 1 tablespoon cornstarch. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: pea picking cake
directions: Mix cake mix, eggs, oil and oranges.
Makes 4 layers.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool.
Mix pineapple, pudding and Cool Whip in a large bowl.
Put lots of icing to each layer.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Cook and crumble sausage; drain well.
Press rolls into 9 x 13 inch casserole dish.
Sprinkle sausage over rolls.
Beat eggs slightly; add milk, salt and pepper to taste.
Mix well; pour over sausage.
Sprinkle cheese over all and bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: perfect pie crust
directions: Combine flour and shortening thoroughly.
Add remaining ingredients and mix.
Press into pie pan and bake in a 400° oven until brown.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Blend soup, milk and pepper.
In 1 1/2-quart casserole arrange alternate layers of potatoes, onion, soup mixture and cheese.
Dot top with butter.
Cover.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Uncover.
Bake 15 minutes more or until done.
Makes 4 cups.

title: hot mulled cider
directions: Combine all ingredients in a pan.
Bring to a boil, then simmer, covered, for 20 minutes.
Serve hot.
Serves 15 to 20.

title: sauerkraut balls
directions: Cook sausage in skillet.
Add onion and cook until it is transparent (do not brown onion).
Drain sausage and onion.
Add next 7 ingredients to sausage and onion and mix well.
Chill for at least 2 hours (may chill overnight).
Shape into small balls (walnut size) and roll in flour.
Beat together eggs and milk. Dip meat balls into this mixture, then roll in bread crumbs.
Fry in hot oil until golden brown.
(Change oil often.)
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: presbyterian meatballs
directions: Form ingredients into meatballs (approximately 75 meatballs). Place in large roaster.

title: diet frankly cabbage
directions: Combine all ingredients in pan or saucepan.
Simmer on moderate heat, covered, for 25 to 30 minutes or until cabbage is tender.

title: frosty orange pie
directions: Drain oranges, saving juice; refrigerate.
Add enough water to the juice to make 1 cup.
Bring to boil.
Add jello; mix until dissolved.
Stir in the ice cream.
Let sit in refrigerator until thickened.
Stir in orange slices and pour filling into the pie shell.

title: angel food cake delight
directions: Mix well all of the ingredients (except pie filling).
Spread in 8 x 8 x 2-inch Pyrex dish.
Spread pie filling on top of cake mixture.
Chill in refrigerator.

title: rainbow jello salad
directions: Mix well and pour into an oblong glass dish.
Let set until firm.
When firm, mix second layer.

title: dirt cake
directions: Mix together margarine, cream cheese and powdered sugar. Then mix together Cool Whip, instant pudding and milk in a very large bowl.
Combine both mixtures together.

title: date bars
directions: Boil the first 3 ingredients together until thick. Set aside. Mix together the butter, flour, sugar and soda. Add oatmeal.
This is crumbly mixture.
Pat half into greased pan. Spread on date filling, then top with balance of crumbly mixture.
Bake in a 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: sausage stars(makes 4 to 5 dozen.)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook sausage on stove and blot with paper towels to remove grease.
Combine sausage with cheese, dressing, olives and red pepper.
Mix well.
Refrigerate until needed.
Lightly grease mini-muffin tins and press 1/4 cut won ton wrapper into pan.
(It will look almost like a star.)
Brush with oil.
Bake 5 minutes until golden brown.
Cool and remove from tins.
Fill with sausage mixture and place on baking sheet.
Bake 5 minutes until bubbly.

title: fruit salad
directions: Combine ingredients together.
Just before serving, fold in 1 pint whipping cream.

title: lime iced tea
directions: Stir together 1/2 of tea and 1 can of limeade in a pitcher. Pour into individual ice filled glasses.
Garnish each glass with a lime slice.
Repeat with remaining tea and limeade.
Serves 12.

title: old fashioned fudge
directions: Cook sugar, salt, cocoa, milk and white syrup on high to bring to boil and turn down low.
Find the setting that will keep it at a rolling simmer.
Cook to medium ball in water (takes a minimum of 40 minutes).
`Set off fire and add oleo.
Let set 10 minutes to cool.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Beat by hand until thick. Pour into buttered pan.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix together sweet potatoes, granulated sugar, milk, eggs, salt, cream cheese and vanilla.
Pour into baking dish.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Take 1 cup berries and crush.
Place in a 2-quart saucepan. Add water and bring to a boil. Cook 3 to 4 minutes. Mix together the sugar, cornstarch and salt, then add slowly into berries. Cook until thick and clear.
Put 1 cup berries in a pie shell.
Mix the rest in thickened sauce and pour on top of berries in pie shell. Chill and serve with Cool Whip.

title: mexican macaroni and cheese
directions: Combine butter and flour over medium heat.
Make a smooth paste.
Gradually add milk.
Simmer for 2 or 3 minutes.
Add cheese.
Simmer until cheese melts.
Remove from heat.
Add green pepper, onion, salt, pepper, tomatoes and macaroni.
Mix lightly. Pour into baking dish.
Bake at 325° for 1/2 hour after mixture begins to boil, about 45 minutes total.

title: scotcheroos
directions: Cook sugar and white syrup in a 3-quart pan over moderate heat until mixture boils (no more).
Remove from heat and stir in peanut butter.
Mix in Rice Krispies.
Press in buttered pan.

title: pecan pie
directions: Place pecans in 3 unbaked pie shells.
Mix other ingredients. Pour over pecans.
Bake 10 minutes at 400°.
Reduce to 350° for 30 minutes or until set.
Yields 3 pies.

title: crock pot dressing
directions: Crumble cornbread and loaf bread.
Mix together with chopped onions, sage, salt and pepper.
Melt margarine in 1 qt. broth, then mix with cornbread mixture.
Add beaten eggs after mixtures cools.
Continue to add extra broth as needed for a thin consistency.
Pour in crock pot.
Cook on low for 4 - 5 hours until onions are tender.

title: cheesy broccoli and meat salad
directions: Prepare rice per package directions and chill for one hour. Cook and drain broccoli and chill for 1 hour.
Gently toss rice, broccoli and shredded cheese.
Stir in meat, sour cream and mayonnaise.
Lightly pepper and salt.
Garnish with croutons. Chill for one hour or overnight.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: onion kisses for the grill
directions: Peel onion and trim the top.
Place in a 9 x 9-inch piece of heavy-duty aluminum foil.
Sprinkle with bouillon.
Twist top of foil like a chocolate Kiss.
Place on warming shelf of grill.
Cook on low with lid closed for 25 to 35 minutes.

title: potato bacon casserole
directions: Cook potatoes in salted water.
While they are cooking, fry bacon until crisp and cut into small pieces.
In 2 tablespoons of drippings, cook onion and green pepper until tender.
Place potatoes, salt, pepper, butter and milk in a large bowl of electric mixer.
Begin beating on low and move gradually to high speed until potatoes are fluffy.
Add eggs, cheese, onion, green pepper and bacon.
Beat until well mixed.
Bake in buttered casserole at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: christmas rainbow poke cake
directions: Prepare cake
mix
as directed on package.
Pour batter into 2 round pans, 8 or 9 x 1 1/2 inches (do not use pans with removable bottoms).
Bake
as
directed;
cool
minutes. Remove from pans;
cool
completely.
Place
cake layers, top sides up, back in
the
clean
pans; prick each layer with utility fork at 1/2-inch intervals.
Pour 1 cup of the boiling water over raspberry
flavored
gelatin
in
bowl; stir until gelatin is dissolved.
Spoon raspberry flavored gelatin over 1 layer.
Repeat with lime flavored gelatin.
Refrigerate 3 to 4 hours.
Dip 1 layer in pan into warm water 10 seconds; invert on plate,
gently shaking to loosen.
Remove pan; spread layer with 1
cup
of
the whipped topping.
Remove remaining layer from pan
as
directed; invert
on
first layer.
Remove pan; frost
with
remaining topping.
Refrigerate;
garnish
with flattened gumdrops cut to resemble holly.

title: cookie pops
directions: Cream sugars and butter.
Blend in the egg and vanilla. Combine the flour, baking soda and salt; add to mixture.
Then shape 1 tablespoon of dough into a ball for each cookie and roll in sugar.
Next push an ice cream stick into the center of each ball and flatten balls with a sugar-dipped glass bottom.
Press M&M's lightly into the dough.
Bake at 350° for 7 to 10 minutes.

title: chunky beef soup to can
directions: Heat to boiling.
Add vegetables which have been cooked and salted.
(Cook vegetables separately, cut up in small cubes.) Brown hamburger with onions.
Add drippings and hamburger to soup. Take some less thant 2 quarts flour and add water to make a smooth paste to thicken soup.
Cold pack 2 hours or 40 minutes at 10 pounds pressure.

title: baked potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes
for
1 hour at 400°.
Cut in half; scoop out center and whip.
Add remaining ingredients and beat well. Stuff empty potato shells with this mixture.
Serve warm.

title: potato soup - crock-pot
directions: Put all ingredients except evaporated milk in crock-pot. Cover and cook on low, 10 to 12 hours or high, 3 to 4 hours.
Stir evaporated milk during last hour.

title: king chocolate cake
directions: Combine butter and sugar. Mix 10 - 15 minutes until creamy. Add one egg at a time, mixing well. Add remaining ingredients. Mix at high speed until creamy. Bake at 325° for 20 - 30 minutes. Makes either two layer cake or sheet cake.

title: sausage and egg pie
directions: Preheat oven and baking sheet to 450°.
Slice each sausage link into one quarter inch pieces.
Cook according to package directions; drain on paper towels.
In medium bowl, beat eggs slightly with fork.
Stir in milk, cheeses, green onion and sausage.
Pour into thawed pie crust; sprinkle top with paprika. Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.
Reduce oven temperature to 350° and continue baking for 25 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Let cool on wire rack 15 minutes before serving. Makes 6 servings.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Save 1/2 of margarine for top.
Boil chicken until done.
Chop into bite size chunks.
Mix soup, sour cream and margarine.
Then spread over chicken.
Crumble crackers and spread over chicken. Drizzle with remainder of margarine.
Bake for 30 minutes at 325°.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix with pumpkin (can) and pour into pie shell and bake until center is almost firm.

title: lemon squares
directions: Pour over cake mix and bake at 350° for 10 minutes and watch them until done.

title: tater tot hot dish
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, crumble hamburger.
Put chopped onion over that.
Put drained vegetables over all.
Mix soups in mixing bowl.
Spread soups over all in the cake pan, then put Tater Tots over all and cover with foil.
Bake one hour at 350°.

title: rocky road s'mores
directions: Beat margarine and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add combined flour and crumbs.
Mix well.
Press onto bottom of greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle with remaining ingredients.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes until golden brown.

title: italian spaghetti
directions: Brown beef with onion and pepper in olive oil.
Break up meat. Add next 5 ingredients; cover and simmer 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Stir garlic and 1 teaspoon salt into sauce.
Add remaining salt to boiling water and cook spaghetti according to package directions.

title: taffy apple salad
directions: Drain pineapple (save juice).
Mix together pineapple and marshmallows.
Refrigerate.
In saucepan, mix sugar, pineapple juice, vinegar and flour.
Cook until thickened.
Cool.
Pour into pineapple and marshmallow mixture and mix.
Refrigerate. Chop peanuts and apples (unpeeled).
Mix together and add to pineapple mixture.
Add Cool Whip.
Mix well.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Blend cottage cheese, milk and lemon juice in blender.
Add chives and onion powder; blend again.
Add Hidden Valley mix; blend again.
Chill at least one hour.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Grease and flour a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan or 2 loaf pans.
Mix the first 6 ingredients well.
Mix flour, cocoa, baking soda, salt and baking powder.
Add alternately with zucchini.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.
After cake cools, can frost with favorite frosting.

title: whole wheat dinner rolls
directions: In small saucepan, heat first 3 ingredients until very warm (120° to 130°).
In large bowl, blend warm liquid, 1 cup all-purpose flour, 3/4 cup wheat flour, sugar, salt, yeast and egg at low speed until moistened.
Beat 4 minutes at medium speed.
By hand, stir in remaining wheat flour and enough all-purpose flour to form a stiff dough.
Knead on a floured surface until smooth and elastic, about 5 minutes.
Place dough in a vegetable spray coated bowl; turn greased side up.
Cover; let rise in warm place until light and doubled in size, 45 to 60 minutes.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Soften yeast in lukewarm water; pour hot water over sugar, salt and shortening.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add 1/2 cup flour and mix thoroughly.
Add softened yeast, about 1/2 remaining flour and egg, beating thoroughly.
Add enough flour to make a soft dough that can be handled on board.
Allow to rest for 5 to 10 minutes. Knead 3 to 5 minutes.

title: scottish shortbread
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients by hand until like fine bread crumbs. Add egg yolks, one at a time.
Knead well after each addition. Divide into 8 balls.
Place onto cookie sheets.
Press with hand into rounds; prick with a fork.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 300° and bake for 30 minutes.
Cut into eighths.
Return to oven to brown edges (optional).
Arrange on small paper plates and sprinkle with sugar, if desired.
Wrap in foil or Saran Wrap.
Store in airtight tin.

title: carrot bread
directions: Beat together vegetable oil and baby carrots.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to first mixture.
Grease and flour two loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Very moist.

title: apricot banana bread
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs; mix well. Combine bananas and buttermilk.
Combine the flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt; add to creamed mixture alternately with banana mixture.
Stir in bran, apricots and nuts.
Pour into a greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes or until bread tests done.
Cool 10 minutes before removing from pan to a wire rack.
Yield:
1 loaf.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Place in refrigerator a few hours.
Roll in small balls and roll in sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 400°.

title: saucepan brownies
directions: Melt together butter with cocoa in saucepan.
Remove from heat.
Stir in sugar, flour, baking powder, vanilla and nuts.
Add eggs.
Beat thoroughly.
Spread in greased 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Cut into squares when cooled.

title: twinkie cake
directions: Split Twinkies lengthwise and arrange in 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Spread pudding over Twinkies, then pineapple.
Next, spread pie filling over pineapple and then cover with Cool Whip and top with pecans.
Chill for 1 hour.

title: wild rice casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt 1/2 cup butter over low heat.
Add onions, bay leaves and thyme.
Cover and cook until tender, approximately 20 minutes.
Add stock, rice and salt.
Bring to boil.
Cover and bake 30 minutes.
Uncover and bake an additional 25 minutes or until the liquid is absorbed.
Meanwhile, melt the unsalted butter in a large skillet over medium heat.
Add pears and chestnuts.
Stir 5 minutes.
Mix together with wild rice.
Bake another 5 minutes or until all the liquid is absorbed.
Season with fresh pepper.
Discard bay leaves.
Serves 10.

title: snowballs
directions: In a medium saucepan, combine butter, sugar, egg, vanilla and dates. Cook for 7 minutes. Cool and add crisp rice cereal. Scoop mixture by rounded teaspoonful into coconut, then roll into balls. Chill until firm.

title: baked trout with crab stuffing
directions: Melt the butter in a skillet.
Saute all fresh vegetables for 2 to 3 minutes on medium heat.
In a large bowl, pour bread crumbs.
Add melted butter and slightly cooked vegetables to bread crumbs, then add seasonings.
Add 1/2 white wine; mix thoroughly. Add all other ingredients; mix thoroughly.
Add boiling water if texture of stuffing is extremely stiff.
The texture of the stuffing should be to your desired specification before baking, because the texture will not change (other than some expansion) after it is fully cooked.

title: vinegar taffy candy
directions: Combine ingredients and cook to hard ball stage.
Pour onto oiled platter.
When cool enough to handle, pull until light colored and porous.
Stretch taffy into a rope and cut off in 1-inch pieces with scissors.

title: eggnog wreath
directions: In medium saucepan,
mix
gelatin
with
half of sugar. Blend in milk and egg
yolks.
Let
stand 1 minute.
Stir over low
heat until
gelatin
is	completely
dissolved,	about
5 minutes.
Add rum
and
nutmeg.
Chill,
stirring occasionally until mixture mounds slightly
when
dropped from a spoon.
In large bowl, beat egg
whites with cream of tartar until foamy. Beat in remaining sugar,
tablespoon at a time until whites are glossy and stand in	soft peaks.
Fold in gelatin mixture and whipped cream.
Turn into
cup ring mold.
Chill until firm.	Makes 8 servings.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Let set for 3 to 4 hours in refrigerator.
Keep refrigerated.

title: great rhubarb pie
directions: Mix all ingredients but margarine.
Pour into pie shell and dot with margarine, then put top on pie.
Cut slits and sprinkle with cinnamon sugar.
Bake at 425° for 35 to 50 minutes.

title: kate's sinfully good cake
directions: Prepare cake according to directions. Bake in a 13 x 9-inch pan. Combine undrained pineapple and sugar; heat until it comes to a boil. Boil 2 minutes. When cake is done, pierce all over with fork. Pour pineapple over hot cake. Cool cake. Mix pudding according to directions. Fold in sour cream. Spread over cooled cake. Top with Cool Whip and sprinkle with toasted coconut and nuts. Refrigerate until ready to use.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Put in pie shells.
Leave in refrigerator overnight.

title: barbecue seasoning
directions: Mix all of the ingredients and store in a tightly covered shaker container.
Use on meat, poultry.
Makes 1 cup.

title: pepper potatoes(a change from the regular home-fries.)
directions: Peel potatoes.
In frying pan, melt margarine.
Spread layer of potatoes in bottom of pan.
Liberally salt and pepper.
Spread second layer and again salt and pepper.
Repeat for all layers. Cover and cook on low to medium heat; occasionally stir.
Serve when potatoes are soft.
Serve with pork sirloin, pork chops or beef tenderloin.

title: tuna pate pyramids
directions: Combine tuna, cream cheese, onion, salt and Tabasco sauce; mix well.
Mound onto crackers.
Serves 24.

title: scalloped onions
directions: Into a buttered casserole, place onions; cover with milk just half full.
Sprinkle with flour and salt and pepper to taste.
Dot with butter and parsley flakes.
Bake in 350° oven for 10 minutes. Turn to 325°.
Bake for an hour or until soft.
Delicious!

title: nick's veal and peppers marsala
directions: Combine flour, salt and pepper.
Pound meat to 1/8-inch thick. Coat veal lightly with flour mixture.
In large skillet, brown meat slowly in hot oil.
Add onions and peppers; cook until tender, but not brown.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer until veal is tender, 20 to 30 minutes; stir occasionally. Makes 4 servings.

title: fluffy cheese spread
directions: Beat until soft cream cheese.
Beat in orange juice, pineapple, pudding and nutmeg.
Chill.
Serve with gingersnaps.

title: zesty italian crescent casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Brown beef and onion; drain.
Stir in sauce mix and tomato sauce; heat until bubbly.
Pour hot meat mixture into ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine cheese and sour cream; spoon over meat.
Separate dough into a rectangle.
Lay over cheese mixture.
Combine Parmesan cheese and margarine; spread evenly over dough.
Bake at 375° for 18 to 25 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Bring cheese to room temperature.
Add onion, ham and hot sauce; mix with hand.
Form into ball.
Roll in pecans until well covered.
Put in refrigerator until firm.
Serve with crackers.

title: pickled fish(pescado en escabeche)
directions: Season the fish steaks with salt and pepper and fry in oil. Remove and drain on a paper towel to soak any excess oil.
Prepare a sauce by combining all other ingredients and cooking on low heat until the onions become soft.
Put fish in a glass bowl and pour sauce over it.
Cover and let it stand for an hour before served or store in the refrigerator overnight or a few days for best flavor.

title: beef tamales
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Place heaping tablespoonful mixture on 5-inch wide piece of foil, shaping with wet hands.
Roll about 3 times and twist ends.
Boil for 15 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli for 3 minutes in salt water.
Mix together all ingredients except bread crumbs.
Add broccoli.
Mix well and pour into buttered casserole dish.
Top with buttered bread crumbs. Bake for 25 minutes on 350°.
Let set for 5 minutes.

title: front stove brown cake
directions: Mix Crisco and sugar. Add the flour and water/cocoa mixture, then add the buttermilk/baking soda mixture and vanilla. Add eggs 1 at a time. Pour into 3 greased and floured 9-inch pans. Bake for 25 to 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook and drain spaghetti; add butter, cheese and eggs.
Form into crust in a 10-inch glass pie pan, buttered.
Spread Ricotta cheese on spaghetti crust.
Fill pie with meat sauce.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese (shredded) over top.
Bake 7 minutes longer, until cheese melts. Let stand a few minutes before slicing.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Mix all together.
Spread over graham cracker crust pie or 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle graham cracker crumbs over top. Refrigerate.

title: fruit custard pie
directions: Mix egg yolks, sugar and flour well.
Add milk and stir over boiling water until thick.
Add vanilla.
Bake pie shell and line bottom of pie shell with sweetened, cooked, dried fruit.
Put the vanilla filling on top of dried fruit.
Top with meringue and brown.

title: 1948 original barbecue sauce
directions: Saute onion and garlic in butter in a saucepan until tender. Stir in remaining ingredients; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer uncovered 30 minutes; stir occasionally.
Discard bay leaf and lemon slices.
Process mixture through a food mill, if desired.
Use sauce for basting or serve with chicken.
Yields 3 cups.

title: easy grilled salmon with thyme
directions: Wipe salmon steaks dry.
Moisten with the lemon juice, pat on the next 5 ingredients and let stand 30 minutes.

title: great northern italian casserole
directions: Sort and rinse beans.
Cover with water and cook until barely tender, about 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Drain.
Pour beans into a 2-quart casserole.
Reserve liquid from beans.
Lightly brown sausage in oil.
Add onion, garlic and celery.
Cook until tender.
Add seasoning, tomato paste, 2 cups bean liquid and salt.
Pour over beans.
Stir.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Add more bean liquid if necessary.
Top with cheese and brown lightly.
Serves 8.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Combine crushed corn flakes and margarine for topping. (Ritz crackers or canned onion rings can be substituted.)

title: mexican pot roast
directions: Brown meat (use oil if necessary).
Combine undrained chilies, 1/4 cup water, taco mix, bouillon and sugar.
Pour over meat. Simmer, covered, on stove top or in oven for 2 to 2 1/2 hours, until meat is tender.
Remove meat to warm platter.
Pour juices into measuring cup; skim off fat.
Add water if necessary to make 1 3/4 cups liquid.
Transfer to saucepan.
Blend the 1/4 cup cold water into flour.
Add to mixture in saucepan; cook and stir until thick and bubbly.

title: ham and noodles
directions: Melt butter in a saucepan; stir in flour, salt, pepper and mustard until smooth.
Gradually add milk.
Bring to a boil.
Cook and stir for 2 minutes or until thickened.
Stir in ham and pasta. This dish is ready when heated through.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Cook macaroni and cool.
Stuff each shell with a tablespoon of each of the cheeses.
Place in a 5-quart baking dish.
Pour spaghetti sauce over the shells.
Top with Mozzarella cheese. Bake in 350° oven until cheese has melted.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Combine instant pudding mix with 2 cups milk; mix well.
Add condensed milk, evaporated milk and sugar; mix well.
Pour in freezer can and add enough milk to finish filling container. Freeze.

title: speedy little devils
directions: Combine melted butter and dry cake mix.
Reserve 1/2 cup of this topping for top crust.
Pat remaining crumb mixture in ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Top that layer with combined peanut butter and Marshmallow Creme; spread evenly.
Crumble remaining mixture over that.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool. Makes 3 dozen bars.

title: creamy baked cheese cake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°. Combine margarine, crumbs and sugar. Press firmly on bottom of a 9-inch spring-form pan.
In a large mixer bowl, beat cheese until fluffy. Gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk until smooth. Add eggs and ReaLemon.
Mix well. Pour into prepared pan. Bake 50 to 55 minutes or until cake springs back when lightly touched.
Cool.
Chill.
Remove side of pan. Spread sour cream on cheese cake.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: In large skillet, heat oil and cook beef and onion until meat is browned and onion is tender.
Drain off excess fat.
Add bouillon and Worcestershire sauce.
Bring to a boil; then reduce heat and simmer, covered, 1 hour or until meat is tender.
Add mushrooms with liquid.
Combine sour cream and flour; blend into meat mixture.
Continue cooking, stirring constantly, 5 minutes or until thickened.
Cook noodles according to package directions; drain.
Serve stroganoff over hot cooked noodles.
Makes 6 servings.

title: fruit compote or salad(low-fat)
directions: Mix pineapple juice and Jell-O pudding together until smooth. Mix with fruit.
(Sometimes a can of fruit cocktail is sufficient.)

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add bananas, pecans, strawberries and pineapple.
Stir well.
Pour half into 9 x 11-inch pan.
Chill until set.
Spread with cream cheese, then pour other half on top and chill until firm.

title: hawaiian wedding cake
directions: Sift together in bowl the flour, sugar, baking soda and baking powder. Blend well. Add the beaten eggs, vanilla, crushed pineapple with juice and the chopped nuts. Combine all ingredients, mixing thoroughly by hand. Pour into a greased and floured 13 x 9-inch baking pan. Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: mama's favorite cake frosting
directions: Cook and stir first 5 ingredients over medium heat until thickened (about 12 minutes). Add coconut and chopped pecans. Cool until thick enough to spread. Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix flour with soda.
Add oil.
Stirring constantly, add rest of ingredients.
Pour into ungreased large pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
After cool, frost with cream cheese frosting.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream together butter, sugar and flour.
Add the vanilla and potato chips.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheet.
Bake in oven at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: pear custard pie
directions: Line unpricked pastry shell with a double thickness of heavy-duty foil.
Bake at 450° for 8 minutes. Remove the foil; bake 3 minutes longer.
Reduce heat to 350°.
Place pears in pastry shell.
In a bowl, combine sugar, flour and nutmeg.
Whisk in egg, 1/4 cup cream, butter, lemon peel and vanilla. Pour over pears.
Cover edges loosely with foil.
Bake for 50 minutes or until filling is just set (mixture will jiggle).
Cool on a wire rack for 1 hour.
Cover and refrigerate until time to serve.

title: pistachio or watergate cake
directions: Mix in large mixer, eggs, salad oil and 7-up or soda. Then add the box of cake mix and beat until smooth, then add the instant pistachio pudding and nuts. Pour into well greased and floured tube pan. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes. When taken from the oven, let stand upright in pan for 30 minutes, not longer, before putting on cake plate.

title: cowboy cake
directions: Mix together flour, baking soda and sugar; set aside.
Bring to a boil oleo, cocoa and water; let cool.
Mix with flour mixture.
Add eggs, vanilla and buttermilk.
Pour in greased and floured cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: dump cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Spread cherry filling in a 13 x 9-inch ungreased pan.
Spread pineapple and juice over cherries. Sprinkle cake mix evenly over top.
Drizzle margarine over cake mix and sprinkle on nuts.
Bake for 1 hour.

title: rolled apple dumplings
directions: Mix and roll out like pie crust.
Cover with diced apples, sugar and cinnamon.
Roll up as a jelly roll and cut into 2 inch pieces.
Place in a 9x11x1/2 inch baking pan.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Mix together sugar, flour and salt.
In a saucepan, combine water, shortening,
margarine and cocoa.
Bring to a boil.
Pour over flour mixture.
Stir well.
Beat eggs, buttermilk, soda and vanilla together; add to flour mixture.
Stir well.
Bake in a greased and floured deep cookie sheet, 11 x 15-inches, at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until done.

title: prune cake
directions: Blend sugar, oil and eggs.
Mix dry ingredients thoroughly together and add to first mixture alternately with buttermilk; then add vanilla, nuts and prunes.
Pour into buttered oblong pan.
Bake at 300° about 40 minutes or until done.
While cake is still hot, pour Buttermilk Icing on it.

title: oreo freeze dessert
directions: Mix cookies and margarine like a graham cracker crust and spread ice cream over it; put into freezer.
Mix topping in saucepan.
Cook until thickens and drizzle over top of ice cream. Return to freezer.
Use 9 x 12-inch pan.
Cut in squares.

title: millie's potato salad
directions: Peel potatoes and dice.
Put in pot with water to cover and cook until	done.
Drain and let cool.
Blend onion, green pepper and celery	on
chop in blender, drain well.
Mix sugar with mayonnaise and mustard.
Sprinkle salt and celery seed on potatoes, then mix in all remaining ingredients.

title: fresh cornbread
directions: Mix dry ingredients. Put eggs, milk, corn and butter in blender and puree.
Stir in flour mixture.
Add nuts.
Leave batter lumpy.
Bake at 425° in well-buttered, hot baking dish (muffin tins, cornstick pans, etc.).
Bake for 20 to 30 minutes. Makes 12 muffins.

title: mexican meat cornbread
directions: Cook until most liquid is absorbed.

title: baked apple donuts
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Cut in shortening.
Mix together egg, milk and grated apple.
Add to flour mixture.
It will be stiff.
Place in greased 12-cup muffin pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Melt 1 stick butter.
Mix 1/3 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon. Dip donuts in butter and roll in sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Serve warm.

title: tootsie rolls
directions: Melt the margarine and chocolate.
Mix all together and form into tootsie rolls.

title: orange dream salad
directions: In a blender, mix egg yolks, flour and sugar.
Juice from pineapple and mandarin oranges.
Cook until thick and add orange jello and stir until cool.
Pour over oranges, pineapple and marshmallows.
Add Cool Whip, then mix everything together and chill.

title: swiss chicken casserole
directions: Arrange chicken in greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Top with cheese.
Combine soup and milk.
Stir well.
Spoon sauce over chicken.
Sprinkle with stuffing.
Drizzle butter over casserole. Cover.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion in skillet.
Add tomatoes, water and taco seasoning.
Stir well and simmer for 10 minutes.
Cook noodles until tender and drain.
In greased 2 1/2-quart casserole dish, layer beef mixture, noodles, cheese, nacho chips and salsa 3 times.
Sprinkle nacho chips on top.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: penuche icing
directions: Melt butter, add brown sugar and cook 2 minutes.
Stir in milk; bring to low boil.
Add powered sugar.
Beat well.

title: corned beef cheese ball
directions: Mix all together and roll into a ball.
Reserve some beef to roll on outside of ball.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour 2 loaf pans.
Add oil and sugar to beaten eggs; then add zucchini and vanilla.
Cream these together.
Mix dry ingredients together.
Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture and mix until thoroughly blended. Add nuts to mixture.
Pour in pans and bake 1 hour or until done. Let cool and enjoy.

title: nutty crescents
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar together.
Mix in water and vanilla, then flour and nuts.
Chill for 3 1/2 hours.
Form dough in long rolls, 1/2-inch across.
Cut in 3-inch lengths and shape in crescents.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet in 325° oven for 15 minutes.
(Do not brown cookies.)
Remove from heat and cool slightly.
Roll in confectioners sugar.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix all together.
Pour into unbaked pie shells. Bake at 400° until the pie doesn't shake.
Makes 2 pies.

title: sausage-egg bars
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
In bottom of greased casserole dish, unroll 1 can of rolls.
Place sausage on rolls.
Pour beaten eggs on sausage.
Take remaining can of rolls and roll out on top of mixture.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top.
Follow directions for baking rolls on can of rolls.
Cut into bars after cooking.

title: grilled chicken
directions: Mix together the sauce and salad dressing.
Pour this mixture over the chicken and marinate for 3 hours in the refrigerator. Put chicken on grill and cook slowly on low heat.

title: chocolate covered cherry cake
directions: Mix cake mix, eggs, oil and almond extract together.
Batter will be stiff.
Fold in cherry pie filling.
Pour batter into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: easy chicken pot pie
directions: Place chicken in bottom of large casserole dish.
Mix broth and soup.
Pour over chicken.
Layer sliced eggs.
Add vegetables.

title: jane's sopapillas
directions: Sift flour, salt, sugar and baking powder together in bowl. Blend in shortening with fork.
Add yeast to warm milk and mix well with dry ingredients.
Let rise, covered, for 30 minutes or more.
Roll 1/4-inch thick on lightly floured board.
Cut into 2-inch squares and fry in oil until golden, turning once.
Drain on paper towels and sprinkle with cinnamon.
To serve, bite out one corner of sopapilla and pour in honey right before eating.

title: wild rice casserole
directions: Cook rice as directed on package. Saute the onion and pepper in margarine.
Add vegetables, mushrooms and cheese to hot cooked rice. Stir until cheese melts. Pour into baking dish.
Cook 30 minutes at 350°.

title: crispy chicken
directions: Mix 1/3 can of soup and 1/4 cup milk; set aside.

title: easy fruit dip
directions: In medium bowl, combine sour cream, brown sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Serve with fruit pieces.

title: bread pudding
directions: Prepare lemon filling early in the day.
Cool.

title: easy pudding milk shakes
directions: Pour milk into blender.
Add pudding mix and ice cream; cover. Blend at high speed 30 seconds or until smooth.
Pour into glasses.
Serve immediately (mixture thickens as it stands).
Thin with additional milk if desired.
Makes about 5 cups.

title: fran's potatoes
directions: Grease a 2-quart casserole.
Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 45 minutes.
Cover and cook 30 minutes more. This may be frozen and stored.

title: chicken divan
directions: Pound chicken breasts until thin.
Cut broccoli into spears and immerse in boiling water to scald.
Wrap chicken breasts around a broccoli spear and place in greased pan.
Mix mushroom soup with just enough milk to make it smooth.
Spoon over chicken bundles.
Top with shredded cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, uncovered.

title: fruit 'n' juice squares
directions: Stir boiling water into gelatin in large bowl at least 2 minutes until dissolved.
Mix cold juice and ice to make 1 1/2 cups.
Stir into gelatin.
Refrigerate 30 minutes or until slightly thickened.
Remove 1 1/2 cups of the gelatin; stir in fruit.

title: sandy's rainbow jello
directions: Mix hot water and Jell-o until Jell-o is completely dissolved. Add ice cream and stir until it has melted.
Pour into mold or bowl.
Let the Jell-o/ice cream mixture set up (approximately 20-30 minutes).
Repeat this process with different flavors.
Just before serving, turn the mold over onto a plate or platter.
The rainbow will release from the mold easily.
Garnish with mint leaves.

title: oreo dessert
directions: In freezer proof dish, crush the box of Oreo cookies.
Spread the melted gallon of vanilla ice cream on top of cookies.
Spread Cool Whip on top of ice cream.
Put in freezer until frozen, cut into squares and cover with chocolate syrup when serving.
tags: gallon of homemade vanilla ice cream

title: apricot fluff
