directions: Soften gelatin in 1/2 cup cold water.
Add hot water and stir until dissolved.
Stir in sugar, salt, lemon rind, apricot and remaining water.
Chill until mixture begins to thicken.
Beat until fluffy and fold in egg whites.
Chill until firm.

title: hot cheese and sausage dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in bowl.
Put into microwave on Medium-high for 2 minutes; stir.
Repeat until cheese is melted. Or use crock-pot and combine all ingredients for approximately 1/2 hour on medium.

title: dump cake
directions: Dump pineapple and cherries into a 13x9-inch cake pan.
Spread the dry cake mix over top of that.
Cut butter into squares and layer over the whole top of cake.
Sprinkle with pecans and bake at temperature of the cake box and time too.

title: artichoke casserole
directions: Use small amount of oil to saute onion.
Cool.
Mix all ingredients together in a baking dish.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes.
If there is an excess of oil drain off.
May be served hot or cold.

title: coca-cola chicken
directions: Place chicken breasts in a large heavy skillet sprayed with Pam.
Pour sauce and Coke over the chicken.
Cook over medium heat for 30 to 40 minutes.
Turn chicken after about 15 minutes.

title: crystal light pie(sugar-free)
directions: Mix pudding, Crystal Light and milk; let it set a few minutes. Fold in Cool Whip and pour into pie shell. Refrigerate for about 2 hours before serving.

title: mexican soup
directions: Mix all together.
Heat thoroughly.
Serve with flour tortillas or cornbread.

title: barbara's dessert
directions: Mix cake mix, margarine and one egg together.
Mix well, then press mixture into a lightly greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix remaining two eggs, powdered sugar and cream cheese.
Pour over first layer.
Sprinkle chopped nuts over top.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Top will be slightly soft to light touch when done.

title: mocha rum balls
directions: Dissolve coffee in rum and water in a bowl.
Add remaining ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Roll in balls, using a rounded teaspoonful of mixture for each.
Store in a tightly covered container for several days.
Roll in additional confectioners sugar.

title: oreo cookies and cream
directions: Dip Oreos into milk until soft. Layer cookies and whip cream until bowl is filled. Each layer of cookies needs to be dipped into milk. Add hard Oreos to top layer. Chill until cold.

title: amazing raisin apple cake
directions: Mix first 10 ingredients. Beat 2 minutes.
Stir in fruit and nuts.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes. Bake in Bundt pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: chocolate bliss - one bowl cookies
directions: Microwave baking chocolate in large bowl on high for 2 minutes. Stir until melted and smooth. Stir in sugar, margarine, eggs and vanilla. Stir in flour and baking powder. Last, add chunks and nuts. Drop by teaspoonful onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes. Cool 1 minute and remove to cooling rack.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream well sugars, butter and Crisco.
Add and blend well eggs and vanilla.
Blend in well the flour, soda, cream of tartar and salt.
Make into small balls about the size of a walnut.
Mash with a glass dipped in sugar (bottom of glass).
Bake at 375° until done, about 8 to 10 minutes.
These sure are good and crisp.

title: scallop stew
directions: Saute sliced scallops in melted butter and crushed garlic until no longer transparent (about 1 minute).
Add scallop mixture, sugar and salt to milk in a pot.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator.

title: shoestring salad
directions: Mix and add shoestring potatoes just before serving.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Bake at 375° in a 9 x 13-inch pan for 1 hour.

title: texas hash
directions: Brown first 3 ingredients.
Add the remaining ingredients. Pour into casserole dish; cover.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Stir occasionally, adding a little water if too dry.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix together and pour in greased and floured square pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Double for larger cake.

title: 7 layer bean dip
directions: Layer ingredients in order in a 12 x 7-inch or 2-quart oblong Corning or Pyrex pan.

title: bread pudding
directions: Place bread in 9-inch baking dish.
Pour in milk and butter mixture.
Blend eggs, sugar, cinnamon and raisins.
Mix with bread in baking dish.
Place dish in a pan with 1-inch of hot water; bake until knife inserted 1 inch from edge comes out clean.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: bavarian cream cake
directions: Mix milk, egg yolks, sugar and flour and cook until thick. Mix 1/2 cup pineapple juice with gelatine and let stand until dissolved, then add to milk mixture after it has cooled.
Add crushed pineapple.
Break cake in pieces.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour milk mixture over cake and spread Cool Whip over top. Sprinkle coconut over top of Cool Whip.

title: chocolate-sour cream pound cake
directions: Beat butter at medium speed with an electric mixer about 2 minutes or until soft and creamy.
Gradually add sugars, beating at medium speed 5 to 7 minutes.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating just until yellow disappears.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Stir all ingredients and
pour in graham cracker crust. Cool in refrigerator for 2 to 3 hours.

title: no guilt brownies
directions: Process all, except powdered sugar for dusting and chocolate chips or walnuts, until smooth.
Mix in chocolate chips or walnuts. Pour into a greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake 22 minutes (20 to 25 minutes) or until just set at 350°.
Cool and dust with powdered sugar.

title: stuffed crabs
directions: Saute celery, onion, pepper and garlic in butter.
Add moistened bread, crab meat, parsley and egg.
Add seasonings. Fill aluminum crab shells.
Sprinkle tops with crumbs.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned, approximately 15 minutes.

title: braised leg of lamb  bordeaux
directions: Brown lamb on all sides in a heavy 5-quart saucepan with the oil (butter) over high heat.
When brown, add remaining ingredients, one at a time.
Cover tightly and cook over very low heat until tender, about 1 hour.
Slice and serve sauce separately. Yields 4 servings.

title: parmesan potatoes
directions: Scrub potatoes, do not peel.
Slice lengthwise about 1/4-inch thick.
Put layers of potatoes in a buttered casserole dish. Sprinkle liberally with onion salt, celery salt, seasoned pepper and Parmesan cheese.
Dot with butter.
Repeat layers. Bake at 350° in a covered dish for 1 hour.

title: mashed potato bake
directions: Mix the cream cheese and onion dip with the potatoes. Add milk accordingly to make nice fluffy mixture.
Put in casserole. Dot with margarine and sprinkle with shredded cheese. Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: mrs. a. r. reddin's chocolate pie
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients, then add 3/4 cup boiling water. Mix the next 2 ingredients and add to first mixture.
Cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Add margarine and vanilla.
Pour into crust and place meringue on top.

title: quick and easy appetizers
directions: Serve on Melba toast, rounds or any type of cracker that is not flavored with cheese, garlic, etc.

title: homemade noodles
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Turn out onto a floured board and roll to 1/8-inch thick.
Then cut into noodles.
Let air dry for 30 minutes and cook in your favorite broth until tender.

title: 5 cup recipe for a happy home
directions: Take 1 cup friendship and 1 cup thoughtfulness; cream together with a pinch of powdered indulgence.
Then in a bowl of loyalty, beat very lightly 1 cup of faith, 1 cup of hope and 1 cup of charity.
Be sure to add a spoonful of gaiety that sings and the ability to laugh at little things.
Moisten with sudden tears of heartfelt sympathy.
Bake in a good natured pan and serve repeatedly.

title: date-nut pudding
directions: Beat eggs and then add other ingredients as listed.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: congealed salad
directions: Adobe from the Philippines is made from whatever you can get. I prefer to believe that the first that I had was made from monkey.
Into a crock-pot, put cup vinegar, 1/2 cup coconut, lime slices, browned chicken and/or pork, sliced sweet potatoes or rutabaga, onions, peppers, celery and etc.
Low heat all day. Serve with rice.
Better than it sounds.

title: cinnamon drop cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; beat in eggs; blend in remaining ingredients.
Chill 2 hours.
Roll in balls size of walnuts and then roll balls in 2 tablespoons of sugar and cinnamon.
Bake on greased cookie sheet 2 inches apart.
Bake at 325° for about 15 minutes.

title: apple cake
directions: Combine and allow to stand while mixing batter.
Combine all ingredients.
Mix batter until quite smooth.
Pour half batter into greased and floured tube or spring-form pan.
Pour 3/4 of apple mixture on top of first layer of batter.
Pour remaining batter over the apples.
Put remaining apple mixture over second layer of batter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: watergate salad
directions: Drain the juice from the pineapple chunks.
Mix the pineapple chunks, pistachio pudding and whip cream.
Now you can mix the mini marshmallows to the cream.
Best results is to chill before serving.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water. Add pie filling and pineapple (juice and all).	Put in an 8x12 inch pan and let set. Mix the cream cheese, sour cream, sugar and pecans together for topping.

title: peanut butter temptations
directions: Use tea cake tins (paper liners optional).
Do not grease tins.
Take wrappers off candy.
Mix ingredients except Hershey's Kisses.
Form into 1-inch balls and drop in tins.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 375°.
Place candies in center.
Let cool.
Can freeze. Yields 4 dozen.

title: tomatoes stuffed with broccoli
directions: Cook broccoli until barely tender; drain well.
Completely hollow out and drain tomatoes.
Make a cream sauce of the butter, flour, milk, salt and pepper.
Combine cream sauce and broccoli; stuff tomatoes with this mixture.
Sprinkle tomatoes with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for approximately 15 minutes.
If made ahead of time and refrigerated, bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: cotton pickin cake
directions: Beat all ingredients and cook in 2 layers at 325° for 30 minutes.
Slice 2 layers into 4 layers while still hot.

title: pinwheels
directions: In small bowl stir together all ingredients except bread. Flatten each slice of bread with rolling pin.
Spread each bread slice with 1 1/2 tablespoons cheese mixture.
Roll up bread jelly roll fashion, beginning with short side.
With serrated knife slice each roll into 4 pinwheels.
Secure each with wooden toothpick.
Place on cookie sheet.
Heat broiler.
Broil 5 inches from heat 1 1/2 to 2 1/2 minutes or until lightly browned and cheese is melted.
Remove from cookie sheet.
Serve immediately.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients, except cheese and peppers.
Pour mixture into hot greased skillet.
Sprinkle with cheese and peppers.
Use rest of batter.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes or until done.

title: sweet potato surprise
directions: Place sweet potatoes, halved lengthwise, in greased 10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish.
In saucepan, combine brown sugar, cornstarch, salt, cinnamon and orange peel.
Drain apricots; reserve syrup.
Stir 1 cup apricot syrup into cornstarch mixture. Cook and stir over medium heat until boiling.
Boil 2 minutes. Add butter.
Add apricots and pecan halves over sweet potatoes. Pour syrup mixture over all and bake in 375° oven, uncovered, for 25 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: jello blocks
directions: Boil water and pour over remaining ingredients.
Put in 13 x 9-inch pan; refrigerate.
When set, cut in cubes for finger food. Children really like it this way.

title: marinated shrimp
directions: Layer shrimp and onion.
Pour dressing over.
Put lemon slices on top.
Refrigerate 12 hours.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions on box.
Mix pudding according to directions on box.
Crumble 1/2 of cake in bottom of a punch bowl.
Pour 1/2 of pudding mixture over cake.
Top with 1/2 of pie filling, 1/2 of pineapple, 1/2 of Cool Whip and 1/2 of walnuts.
Repeat all layers and refrigerate until serving.

title: yankee doodle dandy
directions: Saute celery in oleo until tender.
Stir in flour and salt. Gradually add milk.
Add corn and cooked noodles.
Add cheese and beef.
Bake in a greased casserole at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hot spiced lemonade
directions: In a medium saucepan combine all ingredients. Simmer uncovered 20 minutes. Remove spices and serve hot.

title: sock it to me cake
directions: Mix all this well together.
Then mix 2 tablespoons brown sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Then grease and flour tube pan. Pour half of the batter in the pan and sprinkle your cinnamon and sugar mixture over it.
Then pour in the rest of the batter.
Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 300°.
Glaze while hot.

title: cherry delight
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs and butter.
Press in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan to form crust.
Cool in refrigerator.

title: corn pudding supreme
directions: In a mixing bowl, blend cream cheese, eggs and sugar.
Add all of the remaining ingredients and mix well.
Transfer to a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until set.
Yield:
12 to 16 servings.

title: potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes with skins on until cooked through and tender. Do not overcook.
Dice boiled eggs and combine with the rest of ingredients.
Cube potatoes while they are warm and add to mixture. Skins may be left on if preferred or removed before cutting into cubes.

title: butternut cake
directions: Cream shortening, butter and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time. Add dry ingredients alternately with milk and water.
Stir in butternut flavoring.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan or Bundt pan for 1 hour and 20 minutes (test with toothpick).
Start in cold oven.
Leave in pan 20 to 30 minutes before taking out of pan.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake 4 to 5 hours at 300°.

title: milk chocolate peanut butter bars
directions: Combine softened margarine and peanut butter; beat until smooth.
Add sugar, eggs and vanilla; beat until creamy.
Blend in flour and salt.
Stir in 1 cup of the chips.
Spread into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until edges begin to brown.

title: company breakfast casserole
directions: Butter bread on both sides.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Line bottom and sides with slices of bread.
Use 1/2 slices for the sides.
Sprinkle grated cheese over the bread. Pour eggs and milk over slices of bread.
Top with crumbled meat.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: five layer meal
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in covered casserole dish.
Bake 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Mix in order given.
Pour into lined loaf pan and bake 50 minutes at 350°. Freezes well.

title: lemon icebox pie
directions: Mix well 1 can condensed milk, 2 egg yolks and 1/2 cup lemon juice.
Pour into pie crust.
Let chill about 1 hour.

title: nutty cheese sandwich
directions: In a medium mixing bowl, stir together the softened cream cheese, shredded Cheddar or Colby cheese, shredded carrot or zucchini, honey, apple or pear and peanuts or pecans.
Cover and chill the cream cheese mixture up to 1 week.

title: aunt jenny's potted beef
directions: Cook onions slowly in melted Crisco until brown.
Cut beef into small serving pieces.
Add to pan, increase heat and brown meat on both sides.
Mix flour with seasonings and sprinkle over meat.
Add water, vinegar and ketchup.
Cover and simmer until meat is tender (1 1/2 hours).
Serves 6.

title: potato dumplings or chicken dumplings
directions: Using a pressure cooker, cook potatoes in water.
Sift flour with baking powder and salt.
Beat egg; add milk.
Combine mixtures.
Drop batter from spoon into juice of potatoes or chicken broth. (Take out chicken.)
Cook uncovered 5 minutes. Cover.
Steam for 5 minutes without vent.
Remove dumplings onto hot platter.

title: veal piccata
directions: Brown veal in margarine.
Remove veal to heated platter. Deglaze pan with white wine and chicken broth.
Add lemon slices to sauce and simmer until thickened (may need to add a touch of cornstarch to thicken).
Add garlic.
Put veal back in sauce. Cook for 2 to 3 minutes over medium-low heat.
Garnish with fresh parsley.
Makes 4 servings.

title: paw paw's creamy pralines
directions: Mix sugar, salt, milk and butter in a 2 quart pan.
Cook, stirring constantly, over low heat until sugar is dissolved.
Add pecans and cook over medium heat to a soft ball stage (234°) stirring constantly.
Remove from heat, let cool 5 minutes.
Stir rapidly until mixture thickens and coats pecans.
Working quickly, drop teaspoonfuls on waxed paper, forming patties.
Let stand until cool and set.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: brunch dish
directions: Put bread in bottom of a buttered 9 x 13 dish.
Sprinkle cheese and meat on top.
Beat eggs, salt and milk together and pour over all.
Make sure all bread is covered with the egg mixture.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: pineapple cheese casserole
directions: Drain cans of pineapple and place in a casserole bowl.	Cook flour, pineapple juice, sugar and egg until slightly thickened. Pour over pineapple chunks and mix.
Top with grated cheese.
Mix crushed Ritz crackers and margarine and put on top of cheese. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: chocolate icing
directions: Mix all together and add enough milk to make soft and creamy. Place on low burner until it boils.
Stir constantly.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla.

title: whole grain pancakes
directions: *Use any combination of whole wheat, rye, soy, oat, millet or buckwheat, rolled oats, wheat or rye bran, wheat grain or cornmeal.

title: down home potato salad
directions: Peel potatoes and boil along with eggs until desired firmness (of potatoes).
After potatoes are done, drain water and place potatoes in a bowl and add seasoned salt and cover bowl.
Peel eggs and dice.
Dice (chop) bell peppers, onions and celery.
Add the chopped vegetables to potatoes (stir when adding each), then add eggs, pickle relish, mayonnaise and mustard.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Cream margarine, oil and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add to cream mixture alternately with sour cream.
Stir in zucchini.
Pour into 9 x 12-inch pan, greased and floured.
Sprinkle chocolate chips over top.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: chocolate walnut puffs
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease cookie sheet.
Melt chocolate chips over warm water.
Beat egg whites with salt until foamy. Gradually add sugar.
Beat until stiff peaks form.
Beat in vanilla and vinegar.
Fold in melted chocolate and chopped nuts. Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet.
Bake about 10 minutes.

title: veal "mock turtle" soup
directions: Put pickling spices in a small cheesecloth bag.
Cook veal in a kettle of water with pickling spices.
When veal is cooked, grind it with a meat grinder.
While meat is cooking, peel and dice vegetables.
Add to meat and broth and continue cooking. Brown flour in skillet, stirring constantly.
When vegetables are cooked, add diced lemons and diced hard-boiled eggs.
Add water to browned flour until you have a thin smooth paste consistency. Gradually add browned flour paste, stirring constantly, so flour will mix thoroughly.
Add can of tomatoes, including liquid, to soup.
Serve with Ritz crackers.
Freezes well.
Lots of work, but delicious!

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Put sugar, eggs and margarine in bowl; beat well.
Add flour and flavoring; beat for 10 minutes.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Simmer chicken for 1 to 1 1/4 hours.
Debone chicken; cut into large pieces.
Reserve 2 1/2 cups chicken broth.
To the remaining, add 3 quarts water and 2 tablespoons salt.
Boil and add spaghetti; cook 6 minutes.
Drain and place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: guacamole
directions: Peel, seed and mash avocados.
Add lemon juice and sour cream. Mince onion.
Add to avocado.
Peel tomato.
Remove seeds and juice.
Chop tomato and add to avocado.

title: beef enchilada casserole
directions: Brown ground beef with onion and taco seasoning; drain excess fat and set aside.
In a separate small skillet, precook just to soften each tortilla by using tongs to flip and heat each side in a small amount of oil.
Place tortillas on paper towels to drain excess oil until needed.

title: strawberry pies
directions: Mix all of the ingredients with mixer until very smooth and no lumps.
Add 1 carton Cool Whip and mix for 1 minute.
If mixture is too stiff, add a little milk.
Pour into pie shells and refrigerate.
These pies can be made up ahead of time and frozen. When ready to serve, top with fresh strawberries or your favorite fresh fruit.

title: potatoes donna
directions: Layer first 3 ingredients in casserole.
Blend together milk and flour.
Pour over potatoes, onion and ham.
Dot with butter and bake for 2 hours at 350°.

title: ham and swiss stuffed chicken breasts
directions: Place a ham and cheese slice on each breast half.
Roll up chicken from narrow end.
Secure with toothpicks.
In skillet in hot oil, cook chicken for 10 minutes on all sides.
Spoon off fat. Stir in remaining ingredients; heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover; simmer for 10 minutes.
Garnish with chopped fresh parsley, if desired.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Melt the oleo; add water and cocoa and bring to a boil.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour in greased cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
(This takes a large cookie sheet or it will boil over in the oven.)

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into pie crust.
Top with Cool Whip.
Chill.

title: hot spinach salad
directions: Wash spinach and remove stems; dry leaves.
Tear greens into bite-size pieces (about 10 cups).
Heat salad dressing in chafing dish.
Add bacon bits and toss until greens are well coated. Yields 6 servings.

title: magic lemon meringue pie
directions: In medium size bowl, combine sweetened condensed milk, lemon juice and rind.
Blend in egg yolks.
Turn into cooled crust.
In a small size bowl, beat egg whites with cream of tartar until soft peaks form.
Gradually beat in sugar until stiff peaks form when beater is raised.
Spread over filling.
Seal to edge of crust. Bake in slow oven (275° to 325°) for 12 to 15 minutes or until meringue is golden brown.

title: chicken squares
directions: Blend cream cheese and 2 tablespoons butter until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients, except crescent rolls and croutons; mix well.
Separate crescent dough into 4 rectangles.
Firmly press perforations to seal.
Spoon 1/2 cup meat mixture into each rectangle.
Pull corners of dough to top and twist.
Brush top with butter.
Dip in crouton crumbs.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 20 to 25 minutes, until golden brown.
Bake at 350°. Heat one can of cream of chicken or cream of mushroom soup and pour over top.

title: butterflied leg of lamb
directions: In saucepan, combine vinegar, jelly, sugars, butter and lemon juice.
Bring to a boil.
Add mustard and salt.
Pour over lamb. Cover and marinate 3 to 4 hours or overnight in refrigerator. Before grilling, drain and reserve marinade.

title: sour cream coconut cake
directions: Mix and bake cake according to directions.
Mix coconut, sugar and sour cream together.
Set aside 1 cup mixture.
Frost cooled cake.

title: cornbread
directions: Mix above ingredients.
Use cast-iron (cornbread sticks) pan, heating it as you turn on oven at 400°, and while mixing ingredients.
Bake about 20 minutes.

title: zucchini or broccoli quiche
directions: Crust:
Unroll crescent rolls and shape into quiche pan or 10-inch pie pan.
Prebake according to directions.

title: "drunken cranberry" compote
directions: Place all ingredients into a Pyrex or Corning Ware baking dish.
Cover and bake at 300° for 1 1/4 hours.
Stir twice during baking time.
Cool slightly.
Serve warm or cold.
Great with turkey, ham, pork roast, chicken, etc.

title: lemon pecan pound cake
directions: Place pecans in bottom of a 9-inch microwave-safe pan.
Sift together flour, baking soda and salt.
Set aside.
In a small bowl, stir together milk, lemon juice, lemon zest, vanilla and food coloring.
Set aside.
In a large bowl, cream butter at medium speed 45 seconds.
Gradually add sugar and gelatin in a steady stream.
Beat until mixture is fluffy, 5 minutes.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating about 1 minute after each addition. Scrape bowl while adding eggs.
Reduce to lowest speed of mixer. Alternately stir in 1/4 of the flour mixture and 1/3 of the milk mixture.
Beat well after each addition.
Turn batter into prepared microwave-safe pan.
Level top using a rubber spatula. Microwave at High power for 5 minutes.
Rotate cake one-quarter turn during baking.
Allow the cake to rest 3 minutes.
Microwave at High power for 4 minutes.
Rotate cake during baking.
Cool cake in pan.
Turn out on serving plate.
While cake is still warm, poke holes in top of cake.
Pour glaze on top and dribble down the sides.
Let cool completely before serving.

title: baked fish
directions: Clean and dry fish, cut in pieces.
Dip in milk after adding salt, then bread crumbs.
Place in baking dish adding a little olive oil.
Add little butter to fish.
Brown quickly in very hot oven with no water in pan.

title: butch wright's bread pudding
directions: Melt margarine in casserole dish.
Mix other ingredients. Pour into casserole dish.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: broccoli and cheese quiche
directions: Cook broccoli until tender and drain.
Spray deep glass pie plate with Pam and pour mixture in.
Bake 45 minutes at 375°.
You can add chopped ham or cooked bacon that has been crumbled, if you wish.

title: porcupine meat balls
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix all ingredients (except tomato soup) thoroughly.
Form into balls (12 to 14) and place in a deep baking dish.
Heat the tomato soup with 1 can of water.
Pour over meat balls in a casserole, having the balls well covered.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes in a covered casserole.

title: best cole slaw!
directions: Combine all three vegetables.

title: easy garlic rolls
directions: Cut biscuits in 1/2.
Roll into soft balls.
Bake on a greased cookie sheet as directed on can.
Melt butter.
Mix all remaining ingredients; stir and pour over hot rolls.

title: sausage bread
directions: Brown sausage, onion, bell pepper, garlic and fennel seed (optional).
Drain excess grease.
Roll out pizza dough.
Spread sausage mixture over dough.
Roll up like a jelly roll, from longer side.
Place, seam side down, on pan and bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Brush crust with butter; bake another 5 minutes, until golden brown.

title: chili dip
directions: Brown ground beef and onions together.
Add tomato paste and chili mix to ground beef.
Stir in Cheddar cheese and heat on low. Serve warm with corn chips.

title: ham and cheese dinner
directions: In saucepan, cook onion in butter until tender.
Blend in gravy, water, cheeses and sherry.
Heat until cheese melts; stir often.
Add ham, parsley and pimiento.
Heat; stir occasionally. Serve over noodles.
Makes about 3 cups, 4 servings.

title: layer cake
directions: Blend sugar, Crisco and eggs well, then add flour, milk and vanilla.
Bake at 350° until brown or springs back when touched in middle.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown beef in skillet. Add onion. Drain off fat. Reduce heat and add salt, chili powder, Worcestershire sauce and brown sugar. Stir in tomato sauce and vinegar. Cook mixture about 5 minutes, stirring occasionally to prevent sticking. Serve on hamburger buns.

title: cole slaw
directions: Boil sugar and vinegar and set aside to cool.
Then mix all ingredients with liquid.
No salt!
No pepper!

title: coleslaw
directions: Combine all vegetable ingredients in large bowl. Pour Marzetti dressing over all and mix well.

title: pina colada punch
directions: Mix all except Sprite. Chill. Add Sprite and serve.

title: no-bake bars
directions: Lightly grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine sugar, cocoa, milk and margarine in a large pan.
Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Remove pan from heat.
Add peanut butter and vanilla.
Mix well.
Stir in oats and coconut.
Spread in pan. Refrigerate until set.
Cut into bars.
Store in refrigerator.

title: oriental rice
directions: Brown beef, onion and celery. Add rice, mushroom soup, soy sauce and water.
Bring to a boil. Stir. Reduce heat to low. Cover and cook 15 to 20 minutes until rice is cooked.

title: marinated slaw
directions: In a large bowl, place cabbage, alternating with onions.
Top with 3/4 cup sugar.
Do not stir.
Heat vinegar, oil, 2 tablespoons sugar, salt and celery seed.
Let boil.
Pour over cabbage and onions.
Refrigerate 8 to 12 hours.
Drain before serving.

title: baked chop suey
directions: Brown hamburger, onions and celery. Add soups and water.
Stir well. Add soy sauce and rice. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Sprinkle noodles on top. Bake 15 minutes more.

title: corn bread
directions: Cream together sugar, margarine and butter.
Add eggs, corn meal, flour, milk, baking powder and salt.
Mix well.
Place in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
(Pan can be sprayed with Pam cooking spray.)

title: orange slush
directions: Combine sugar and 3 cups water and boil.
Remove from heat and cool.
Combine remaining ingredients with sugar water.
Freeze and enjoy (stir while freezing).

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion and drain. Add Ro-Tel tomatoes and cream of chicken soup. Put a layer of chips on bottom of casserole dish. Put half of meat mixture on top, then half of grated cheese. Put another layer of chips and rest of meat mixture. Top with rest of cheese and put in 350° oven for 20 minutes.

title: hershey's kiss cookies
directions: Cream
butter
and sugars.
Add milk, vanilla and eggs. Mix in	peanut	butter.
Finally,
add	flour, soda and salt. Form into
balls
and roll in sugar.
Slightly flatten dough. Bake at 350°
for 8 minutes.
Remove from oven gently and put kisses or stars
in
center of each cookie and bake another 2 minutes.

title: jalapeno cabbage
directions: Chop the cabbage in large pieces.
Preboil until tender, about 8 minutes.
Drain the cabbage.
Make 2 cups white sauce, then add the cheese.
Stir until the cheese is melted.
Pour over the drained cabbage, stirring slightly to blend.
Place the cabbage mixture in a sprayed or buttered 2-quart casserole dish.
Pour the melted margarine on top of cabbage mixture.
Sprinkle the crushed crackers on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: focaccia bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water with olive oil, 1 teaspoon salt and sugar.
Stir in the flour a little at a time.
When you can no longer stir, turn the dough onto a floured board and knead until the dough is smooth and elastic.
Place dough in an oiled bowl and let rise until it has doubled in size, about 30 to 40 minutes.

title: meatballs
directions: Saute onion; add tomato sauce, water and sugar and stir.
Let it come to a boil.
Add meatballs and cook 1/2 to 3/4 hour. Remove meatballs and add sauerkraut.
Stir together; put meatballs back in pot and cook together another 1/2 to 3/4 hour.
Tastes like stuffed cabbage!
Freezes well.

title: taco bake
directions: Brown ground beef, add taco seasoning (mix as directed on pkg.).
Set aside.
In a 9 x 13-inch greased deep-dish pan, layer crescent rolls and press into pan (make a second layer if need be). Prick holes in rolls with fork.
Bake at 375° for 6 minutes. Remove from oven.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix all but butter and Ritz crackers.
Spread in casserole dish.
Melt butter and mix with crackers; put on top.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: cherry cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream butter and 1/2 cup sugar until fluffy.
Sift dry ingredients together in another bowl; add this alternately to creamed mixture with milk.
Beat until smooth. Pour into loaf pan or 2-quart casserole.
Spoon drained cherries over batter.
Sprinkle with sugar, 1/4 to 1/2 cup as needed per tartness of cherries.
Pour 1 cup fruit juice and water mixture over top.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes, until top browns.
During baking, juice goes to bottom and cakelike layer comes to the top.

title: chicken fettucini paprikash
directions: Coat chicken cubes with seasoned flour.
Saute chicken and onion over medium heat in pan heavily coated with Pam.
Sprinkle lightly browned chicken and onion with paprika and cayenne.
When chicken is lightly browned, stir in chicken broth, bringing mixture to boil.
Cook fettucini according to directions; drain and then add with yogurt to chicken mixture.
Stir to blend all ingredients and serve hot.
Garnish with chopped parsley.
Great with a salad and French or Cuban bread.

title: brunch egg bake
directions: In a large bowl, combine cheese.
Sprinkle 1/2 cheese in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Saute mushrooms, onions and pepper in oleo.
Brown meat.
Layer vegetables and meat over cheese.
Sprinkle remaining cheese over meat.
Combine flour, milk, eggs and parsley; beat. Pour over other ingredients.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 35 to 45 minutes or until brown and eggs are set.
Garnish with pepper and parsley, if desired.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Stir all ingredients in a glass bowl until well mixed. Microwave on High for about 2 minutes.
Stir and spread evenly into an 8-inch square low pan and refrigerate.
Cut into 16 pieces.
Adding coconut, nuts, marshmallows, Rice Krispies and raisins will add additional calories, etc. to recipe.

title: rice pilaf with peas
directions: Cook bacon until crisp (reserve a small amount for later). Remove from skillet.
Cook onion in small amount of fat until tender.
Stir rice, frozen peas, water, chicken broth, salt and pepper.
Add to bacon and onion.
Heat to boiling point.
Reduce heat to low and cover.
Let simmer about 20 minutes until rice is tender.

title: melon-ball compote
directions: Boil sugar, water, salt and mint 15 minutes.
Let cool. Remove mint.
Pour over melon balls and cover.
Chill 2 to 3 hours.

title: play dough or clay
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add water.
Mix a few drops of food coloring in oil and mix well.
If making clay objects, let dry for a few days and then color, paint or use markers to decorate.
If using as play dough, store in an airtight container between uses.

title: make-ahead chicken macaroni casserole
directions: Combine and mix all ingredients in a large bowl; cover and refrigerate overnight.
Turn into a shallow glass casserole (13 x 9-inches).
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: spicy turkey breast
directions: Mix all the spices together.
Rub melted butter over turkey breast.
Pat spices all over.
Cover completely.
Bake in preheated 275 degree oven until internal temperature of 1750 (approx. 3 1/2 to 4 hours).

title: pineapple hot dish
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat by hand.
Add bread cubes and pineapple.
Put in a greased loaf pan and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: chicken roll
directions: Combine ginger, almonds, shallots, curry powder, salt and pepper, lemon juice, softened butter, cream cheese, and chicken. Toast in heavy skillet over medium heat 3/4 c. sesame seed, 1 tbsp. sugar.
Cool.
Shape chicken mix into 4 rolls.
Cut wax paper, spread 2 tbsp. seed on paper and roll the rolls in it.
Bring to room temperature to serve with sesame crackers.

title: starter-sourdough bread
directions: Mix and put in a large glass bowl, sprayed with Pam.
Cover with dry dish towel overnight (leave out).
In morning, knead 10 times.
Divide into 2 parts; knead each 8 to 10 times.
(Use a little flour, if necessary.)
Put into pans sprayed with Pam. Cover and let rise all day until supper.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in a 12 x 12-inch dish, sprayed with Pam for about 30 to 45 minutes at 375°.
Crushed potato chips on top are good.

title: spinach salad with pears, pecans and feta(middle east)
directions: Toss together the spinach, pears, pecans, Feta and mint.
Mix together the lemon juice, vinegar, honey, mustard and yogurt. Whisk in the olive oil or shake together in a jar.
Add salt and pepper.
Toss with the salad just before serving.
Serves 4.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken.
(Boil about 45 to 60 minutes.)
Make stuffing from broth of chicken and butter.
Place stuffing mix in oblong pan.
Place chicken on top of stuffing.
Beat soup with milk and pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
You'll love it!

title: crab dip
directions: Mix all ingredients, except crab meat, well.
Add crab meat and stir in gently.
Put in greased casserole.
Sprinkle another 1/2 cup grated Cheddar cheese on top.
Bake at 150° for 1/2 hour.

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: Cook beans and corn as directed on package.
Break cauliflower into pieces; slice mushroom.
Add vegetables to marinade.
Chill well and serve chilled.

title: chicken divine casserole
directions: Place chicken in ungreased casserole.
Top with hot broccoli and cheese.
Stir soup and milk together.
Pour over cheese. Bake, uncovered, 25 minutes at 350°.
Top with onion rings.
Bake 5 minutes longer.

title: cowpoke cookies
directions: Beat margarine until light.
Add peanut butter.
Gradually add the white and brown sugar.
Beat well.
Add egg and vanilla and beat until very light.
Sift together flour and soda.
Gradually add to mixture.
Form into small balls.
Roll in granulated sugar and place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes. Remove from oven.
Place a solid milk chocolate candy kiss in center of each cookie, pressing down firmly.
Bake 2 to 3 minutes longer.
Makes about 6 dozen.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add remaining ingredients except peanut butter and chocolate chips.
Press into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until light brown. Remove from oven.
Spoon peanut butter over hot base.
Melt chocolate chips in a saucepan or microwave with 2 tablespoons butter or margarine.
Drizzle over peanut butter and spread evenly.

title: crabmeat dreams
directions: Trim crust from bread and cut into squares.
Mix other ingredients.
Spread on bread.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 350°. Makes 48.

title: black-eyed pea cornbread
directions: Mix cornmeal, flour, salt, soda, eggs, buttermilk and oil. Add onion, jalapenos, corn and browned meat. Then add black-eyed peas and cheese. Pour into well-greased pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Can be served hot or cold.

title: angel food candy
directions: Boil sugar, syrup and vinegar until it reaches 300° in high pan.
Take from flame.
Add tablespoon baking soda.
Stir like crazy.
Pour into buttered 9 x 9-inch pan.
When cool, break into pieces.
Dip in chocolate.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Pour coconut and pecans into a well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Prepare chocolate cake mix as directed on box.
Pour over nuts and coconut.
Mix margarine, cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Drop by spoonfuls on top of cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: homemade soup
directions: Cook meat until free of blood.
Add potatoes, carrots, celery, onions and cabbage. Cook until vegetables start to get tender, then add corn, tomato juice and milk.
Reduce heat and let simmer 25 to 30 minutes.

title: lo-cal quiche
directions: Spray a 9-inch pie plate with Pam. Grate cheese in bottom of plate.
Put onion on top and 1 cup vegetable if you wish.
All else in blender.
Pour in pie pan on top of other ingredients. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes. Serves 4.

title: caramel icing
directions: Mix brown sugar, granulated sugar and Carnation milk.
Boil for 15 minutes.
Remove from stove and add margarine and vanilla. Stir until thick and spread on cake. Can add nuts, if desired.

title: pumpkin spice bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
In a medium bowl, mix flour, pumpkin pie spice, baking soda and salt; set aside.

title: pot roast
directions: Brown roast in iron skillet on both sides (no need to add oil). Remove from skillet and put into 4-quart pressure cooker. Add other ingredients. Put 1 cup water in iron skillet and stir to loosen any drippings, then pour into cooker with meat. Cover and pressure cook for 1 hour or until meat is tender. Remove from broth and put meat in covered serving dish.

title: daina salad
directions: Rinse lettuce, tear into bite-size pieces and spin in salad spinner (a must).
Dice purple onion.
Toss together lettuce, onion, Blue cheese, vinegar, oil, seasoned salt and pepper. Tasty!

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Mix soup, onion, egg and mayonnaise into broccoli.
Place in small casserole.
Top with cheese, then bread crumbs.
Dot with margarine.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cheese soup
directions: Heat broth and milk slowly in large pot.
Stir grated cheese into broth until melted.
(Remove from heat if you can't keep stirring.)
Mix cornstarch with as much water as needed to make it pourable.
Pour cornstarch mixture slowly into pot.
Saute vegetables in margarine; add to soup.
Serves 8.

title: double rich brownie torte
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Melt chocolate and butter in top of double boiler until smooth. Stir in vanilla.
Beat eggs in a large bowl until light and lemon colored.
Slowly beat in chocolate mixture. Sift flour with malted powder, then beat into chocolate mixture one tablespoon at a time.
Butter a 9-inch loose-bottom tart pan. Pour batter into pan.
Bake about 25 minutes, until toothpick inserted in center comes out fairly clean.
Center should be very moist.
Cool completely on a rack.
Remove from pan and serve, cut into thin slices (10 servings).

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli, drain.
Arrange in 9 x 13 inch pan.
Cut cooked chicken into pieces and place over broccoli.
Combine soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice, and curry powder. Spoon over chicken. Sprinkle with cheese.
Combine cornflake crumbs and margarine. Sprinkle over top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: banana pudding cake
directions: Slice bananas into large mixing bowl; beat until well mashed. Add remaining ingredients.
Blend; then beat at medium speed for 2 minutes. Pour into a well greased and floured 10 inch tube pan or Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 or 70 minutes.
Cool.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: homemade bread
directions: Leave a little bread dough in mixing bowl each time bread dough is rolled out.
Sift 2 cups flour over dough; set aside until finished shaping the bread dough into loaves.
Cut down dough and flour until it becomes crumbly.
Leave dough covered in mixing bowl until ready to make bread.
Store at room temperature.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown meat, onion and pepper.
Drain.
Mix all ingredients. Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.

title: refried bean dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and enjoy!

title: squash casserole
directions: Mash squash.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: dilly oyster crackers
directions: Stir oil and dill together.
Add dip and mix well.
Add crackers; stir well from bottom.
Stir periodically until all oil is absorbed.
Store in airtight container.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes, slice thin.
Make white sauce of butter, flour and milk.
Put half the potatoes in greased 2-quart casserole. Cover with half the sauce, seasoning and onion.
Add remaining potatoes, seasonings and onion; then remaining sauce and 1/2 cup shredded Cheddar cheese.

title: sour milk biscuits
directions: Sift together flour, salt, baking powder, and soda. Add cold shortening and mix with hand until it looks like coarse cornmeal. Add milk, stir about 20 seconds. Turn out on lightly floured board. Knead about 20 strokes. (Add flour if needed.) Roll out to 1/2 inch to 3/4 inch thick. Cut. Place in greased pan. Bake in hot oven (400°) 12 to 15 minutes.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: In a large skillet, brown the ground beef, stirring until cooked through; drain fat.
Add taco seasoning, seasoned salt, tomatoes, tomato sauce and chilies.
Blend well.
Bring to a boil, then reduce heat to a simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes.

title: unstuffed cabbage
directions: Cook beef and onions in 4 quart Dutch oven until lightly browned.
Drain. Stir in cabbage.
Cover and cook over medium heat 5 to 7 minutes until cabbage wilts.

title: cheesy chili dip
directions: Brown ground beef, chopped onion, salt and pepper; drain.
In large pot, mix all of chili and add hamburger, garlic salt and cubed cheese.
Heat until cheese is melted.
Serve with chips for dipping.
Great recipe for parties.

title: crab bisque
directions: In 3-quart saucepan, melt butter over low heat.
Add celery and onion.
Cook until tender.
Stir in flour, thyme and pepper. Gradually add milk.
Stir constantly.
Add potatoes.
Bring to boil.
Simmer 15 minutes or until potatoes are tender, stirring occasionally.
Add crab substitute.
Heat 5 minutes more.
Enjoy!

title: cherry cobbler
directions: Thicken cherries in a saucepan with sugar and 1/4 cup flour. Make biscuit dough with remaining ingredients.
Pour bubbling cherries into casserole; cover top with biscuit dough.
Put into a 425° oven; turn down to 325° and bake 10 to 15 minutes.

title: easter bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, combine 1 cup of flour, sugar, salt and yeast.
Heat milk and 2 tablespoons of margarine in saucepan over low heat until liquid is warm.
Add to dry ingredients.
Beat 2 minutes at medium speed, scraping bowl.
Add 2 eggs and 1/2 cup of flour.
Now, beat at high for 2 minutes.
Stir in enough flour to make a soft dough.
Turn onto floured board. Knead 8 to 10 minutes.
Place in greased bowl; turn to grease top. Cover; let rise until doubled (about 1 hour).
Punch dough down. Turn onto floured board; knead.
Divide dough in half.
Roll each piece into 24-inch rope.
Twist together loosely to form a ring on a greased baking sheet.
Brush with melted margarine.
Place colored eggs into spaces in the twist; cover and let rise for another 1 hour, then bake for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: 7-up or sprite pound cake
directions: Beat butter or margarine and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs (one at a time).
Beat well.
Add flour and drink; beat well. Add flavoring.
Bake in 10-inch tube pan (greased and floured) at 300° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Add 1 teaspoon baking powder to flour for a lighter textured cake.
This recipe makes 3 (9-inch) layers, 2 to 3 dozen cupcakes or a thick 9 x 13-inch sheet cake.

title: gingerbread
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time. Sift flour, ginger, cinnamon and soda together.
Add alternately with buttermilk.
Bake in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan for 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken salad
directions: Boil leg quarters until tender.
Take chicken off the bone. Mix ingredients together and make into a ball or put in sandwiches.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together and top with Ritz cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Cook ground beef and chopped onion in Dutch oven until done. Add spaghetti sauce, mushrooms, oregano and parsley.
Cook in covered kettle about 30 minutes on low heat.
Serve over cooked spaghetti.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Melt butter and saute onion.
Remove onion, leaving butter in skillet.
Mix onion with beans.
Line casserole dish with green beans.
Layer cheese, soup and beans.
Make 2 layers of everything. Put Ritz crackers on top and pour butter over them.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.

title: potato salad
directions: Boil, peel and cube potatoes. Mix with celery and onion. Combine mix with 1/2 cup mayonnaise and water. Add to potatoes. Toss to coat. Chill. Serves 4 to 6.

title: raspberry pretzel dessert
directions: Melt margarine.
Crush pretzels (blender works well).
Do not "dump" pretzels into blender.
You do not want all the salt that is in the bag.
Mix together and press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Let cool.
Heat pineapple juice to boiling (hot enough to dissolve jello).
Dissolve jello in pineapple juice and set aside.
Mix cream cheese and sugar.
Spread on pretzel mixture.
Spread large Cool Whip on cream cheese mixture.
Take frozen (partially thawed) raspberries and pour into jello mixture. It will set up quicker, putting frozen raspberries in.
When it begins to set up, spoon on top of Cool Whip layer.
(Pan will be full to the top.)

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Mix all together, except potato chips.
Put in a 13 x 9-inch dish.
Sprinkle the crushed potato chips over top.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown the ground beef.
Add onions, bell pepper and soup; mix well.
Add drained corn.
Cook noodles and add to ground beef mixture.
Mix well.
Place grated cheese (save some for top) in casserole.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Pour catsup over top and cook in 350° oven for 20 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: dump cake
directions: Butter bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour pineapple and its juice in bottom of pan.
Spoon cherry pie filling over pineapple evenly.
Sprinkle cake mix over both evenly.
Drizzle margarine on top.
Sprinkle nuts over all.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: glazed nuts
directions: In small mixing bowl, combine sugar, spices and salt.
Beat egg white lightly and stir into sugar-spice mixture; stir in water.
Blend well.
Add nuts, 1/2 at a time.
Use fork, stir to coat nuts well.
Lift up and drain.
Place on greased baking sheet, separating each nut.
Bake at 275° until golden crusty, about 45 minutes.
Remove from baking sheet with a spatula.
Store in container with tight lid.
Makes 3 cups.

title: tunaburgers
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Divide evenly into buns.
Wrap each in foil and place on cookie sheet.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: cranberry-orange chutney
directions: Combine all ingredients
in
a large saucepan and bring to a boil.
Reduce
heat and simmer 5 minutes or until berries begin to burst.
Chill until serving time.
Yields 5 1/2 cups.

title: rhubarb coffee cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening. Add egg. Combine flour, sugar, baking soda and salt. Add alternately with sour cream to creamed mixture. Fold in rhubarb. Spread in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.

title: spanish hamburger rice
directions: Brown rice in 2 tablespoons cooking oil until golden brown. Add hamburger, onion, green pepper and celery.
Stir and cook until brown, then add tomatoes, bouillon, salt, soy sauce and sugar.
Cover and simmer for 45 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: chess cake
directions: Mix together first three ingredients and press into bottom and up sides of a greased 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Mix together cream cheese, sugar and 3 eggs and pour into crust.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
No frosting required.
This is a moist, pudding-like cake.

title: keep cole slaw
directions: Cover with boiling water.
Let set 1 hour.

title: key lime pie
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Beat 4 egg yolks.
Add condensed milk and lime juice.
Beat until thick; pour into baked pie shell.

title: saucy brussels sprouts
directions: Cook fresh Brussels sprouts as directed; drain well. Meanwhile, in an 8-inch skillet or medium saucepan, cook chopped onion in butter until tender, but not brown.
Blend in flour, brown sugar, dry mustard and 1 teaspoon salt.
Stir in milk. Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened and bubbly.
Blend in sour cream.
Add cooked Brussels sprouts; stir gently to combine. Cook until heated through, but do not boil.

title: 7-up salad
directions: Add hot water to dissolve lemon and lime jello.
Add 7-Up. When jello is set a little, add pineapple, nuts and marshmallows. Let this set to harden.

title: wassail(hot cider drink)
directions: Stick whole cloves in the orange.
Mix all ingredients together and place orange in mixture.
Place cinnamon sticks in mixture.
Cook on high for 1 hour and then simmer 6 to 8 hours. Best done in crock-pot.
When done, take out the orange and the spices.

title: delicious lemon cake
directions: Mix cake, pudding, eggs, water and oil.
Beat well.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes; do not overbake.
Punch top of cake with fork.
Pour mixture of lemonade and powdered sugar over cake.
Return to oven for 5 minutes.

title: les' spaghetti
directions: Put water in medium size saucepan.
Add green pepper and onion.
Cook 10 minutes.
Add tomato juice.
Simmer 1/2 hour. Dice bacon and fry until brown.
Take out of pan and drain on paper towels.
Add to first mixture, along with a little bacon fat, for taste.
Cook spaghetti.
Drain and combine with tomato juice mixture.
Serve.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into casserole.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: honey bread(spice bread; pain d'epice)
directions: Sift into a mixing bowl the first 6 ingredients. Add honey, egg and milk. Beat thoroughly 15 minutes at the very least. If you have an electric beater, beat 1/2 hour. Spoon into a buttered loaf pan, 9 x 5-inches, or into bread stick pans. Bake at 350° about 50 minutes for a loaf, 25 for bread sticks.

title: shamrock key lime pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat 4 egg yolks and add condensed milk and then lime juice.
Beat until thick.
Beat 1 egg white stiff, then fold into mixture.
Pour into baked graham cracker crust.

title: blueberry pound cake
directions: Grease a 10-inch tube pan with 2 tablespoons butter.
Sprinkle pan with 1/4 cup sugar; set aside.
Cream remaining 1 cup butter, gradually add remaining 2 cups sugar, beating well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add vanilla.
Combine 2 3/4 cups flour, baking powder, and salt; add gradually to creamed mixture, beating until well blended.
Dredge blueberries in remaining 1/4 cup flour.
Stir to coat well.
Fold blueberries into mixture.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: uncooked ketchup
directions: Grind
all
ingredients
in food grinder. Add salt; let stand 2 hours. Drain through cloth sack; put in large container.
Add
3 pints vinegar, sugar and allspice.
Fill jars. Do not cook. Refrigerate.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In a large bowl, whisk together the sweet potatoes, the granulated sugar, 1/2 cup of the butter, the eggs, the vanilla, the evaporated milk and the nutmeg until the mixture is smooth.
Transfer the mixture to an 8-inch square (2-quart) baking dish.

title: sara salad
directions: Drain fruit cocktail; take 1 1/2 cups juice and full boil. Dissolve jello.
Refrigerate to medium hard.
Mix cream cheese and mayonnaise until fluffy.
Add jello.
Mix well.
Add Cool Whip with spoon gently.
Stir in fruit, maraschino cherries, marshmallows and nuts.
Freezes well.
Takes 8 hours to thaw. Makes 1 large bowl.

title: cranberry-orange sauce
directions: Chop and mix together.
Let stand 12 to 24 hours.
Keep refrigerated.
This will keep several weeks.
Very good at Thanksgiving and Christmas with or in place of cranberry sauce.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Spread soup in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put asparagus over soup. Spread pimentos over asparagus.
Slice eggs on top of pimentos. Cover with grated Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour. Remove from oven.
Cover with French fried onions.
Return to oven until onions are toasted.

title: indian chicken
directions: Mince onions and garlic and fry in large sauce pan until brown.
Add turmeric, curry, salt, chili powder, oregano, ginger and pepper.
Stir well and simmer for 5 minutes.
Add chicken and fry for 5 - 10 minutes.
Add 1 cup of warm water, cover and cook for 1 1/2 hours.

title: company breakfast
directions: In 9 x 13-inch baking pan, arrange first 3 ingredients in layer. Beat next 5 ingredients and pour over bread layers.
Cover with foil and refrigerate overnight.
Next morning, remove foil and bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Serve hot.
This is good with syrup on top.
You can also add your own variations with ham or Canadian bacon, etc.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well and freeze in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Cut into squares. Serve on lettuce and top with mayonnaise and cherries or strawberries.

title: fantasy fudge
directions: Combine sugar, butter and milk in saucepan.
Bring to a full rolling boil; stir constantly.
Continue to boil 5 minutes over medium heat.
Remove from heat; stir in chocolate bits until melted.
Add marshmallow, nuts and vanilla.
Beat until well blended, then pour in pan 9 x 13-inches.
Cool at room temperature, then cut in squares.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar.
Add egg and beat well.
Add dry ingredients, mixing well.
Stir in bananas, lemon juice and nuts.
Fill 3 well-greased No. 2 tin cans one-half full or 1 (9 x 5 x 3-inch) loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes.
Remove from pan or cans.
Cool on rack.
Yields 3 small loaves or 1 large loaf.

title: me ma buchanon's egg nog
directions: In large bowl beat together pudding mix, sugar, vanilla, milk and egg yolks.
Carefully fold in stiffly beaten egg whites. Chill thoroughly.
Serve in punch cups topped with nutmeg.

title: mexican wedding cakes
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Work in vanilla, flour and nuts. Shape into small balls and place on ungreased sheets.
(If dough is too sticky, place in refrigerator until chilled.) Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
When cool, roll in confectioners sugar.
Add a little more flour to dough, if needed.

title: great spiced tea mix
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Add 2 heaping teaspoonfuls to mug of hot water.
Enjoy on a cold winter day.

title: spinach dip
directions: Combine and chill several hours before serving.
Serve with raw vegetables or 1 round loaf black rye bread.
Cut out center of bread and put dip in bread. Break off bread and dip.

title: warm chicken salad with rosemary dressing
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine the celery root and onion. Toss with the olive oil, lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Marinate for at least 10 minutes or cover and refrigerate until needed.

title: thailand pork and shrimp dip
directions: Combine coriander, garlic and white pepper.
Pound or process to a smooth paste.
To aid in processing, you may add a little coconut milk.
Heat thin coconut milk in a saucepan over medium heat until it is just simmering.
Stir in coriander paste, pork, shrimp and shallots.
Bring to a boil and reduce to a simmer. Cook, stirring, uncovered, for about 5 minutes or until pork is cooked.
Stir in tamarind water, fish sauce, brown sugar and peanuts.
Cook until sugar dissolves.
Remove from heat.

title: squash souffle
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine the squash, butter or margarine, brown sugar, cinnamon, orange peel, nutmeg and pepper. Beat until fluffy.
Add egg yolks; beat well.
Carefully fold squash mixture into stiffly beaten egg whites.
Turn into 1 1/2-quart souffle dish.
Bake souffle at 350° until set, 55 to 60 minutes.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: quick taco skillet casserole
directions: Brown beef in deep skillet, drain fat.
Stir in remaining ingredients and simmer for 20-25 minutes.
Serve over Taco corn chips.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Saute onion and celery in a little oil.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer a couple hours, then add browned ground beef.

title: butter pecan cake
directions: Cream butter, Crisco and margarine.
Add sugar and egg yolks and beat well.
Add sifted flour and soda.
Add buttermilk and flavoring.
Beat well and stir in pecans.
Fold in egg whites. Pour into three greased and floured 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool and put Cream Cheese Icing on cake.

title: turtle cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed and put half the batter in a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Melt caramels with condensed milk and margarine.
Spread over the baked cake.
Sprinkle chocolate chips and nuts on top.
Cover with remaining batter.
Return to oven for 20 minutes or until done. Frost with Fudge Frosting.

title: orange slice cake
directions: In large bowl, flour the cut candy slices, dates, nuts and coconut in the 1/2 cup flour.
Cream sugar and shortening.
Add soda to buttermilk and add milk and dry ingredients alternately to the sugar mixture.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla. Stir in fruit and nuts.

title: chicken crisp
directions: Dip chicken in butter, then roll in corn flakes or Rice Krispies.
Put in a pan with foil lining.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: bacon-cheese balls
directions: Fry bacon crispy.
Combine the first four ingredients; form into balls the size of a teaspoon and roll in crushed bacon. Chill.
Serve with crackers.

title: old fashioned pound cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Add alternately with milk and flour; mix well.
Add flavoring.
Beat 3 minutes really well.
Put in pan.
Bake for 1 hour and 20 minutes at 300°.

title: texas hash
directions: Saute meat, onion and bell peppers.
Add seasonings.
Add cooked rice (I use Minute rice).
Add tomatoes.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Bake in a 350° oven for 25 minutes.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Heat potatoes in own juice.
When they come to a boil, drain and mash.
Bake in oven at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Cut carrots in half crosswise, then lengthwise into 2 or 3 sticks.
Simmer, covered, in a small amount of boiling, salted water, about 10 minutes or until crisp-tender.
Drain.

title: crabmeat casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients (except crumbs).
Mix well.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: beef and vegetable casserole
directions: Mix ingredients except beef.
Place into a casserole dish; cover with beef and add 4 slices of bacon that have been cut. Cover the dish and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Uncover and bake another 30 minutes longer.

title: bean pot
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Fry bacon until crisp. Saut onions and garlic in bacon fat until soft.
Combine all ingredients and mix well. Put in 2-quart casserole. Bake, uncovered, approximately 1 hour, stirring twice. Makes 8 servings.

title: rice pilaf
directions: In medium saucepan, combine water, rice, chicken bouillon cubes and salt.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer on low heat until liquid is absorbed, about 15 minutes.
Melt butter in large skillet.
Add celery and onion.
Cook until almost tender, about 5 minutes.
Add mushrooms.
Heat.
Fold in hot, cooked rice.
Yields about 6 cups.

title: oatmeal chocolate chip cookies
directions: Blend oatmeal.
Measure and blend in a blender to a fine powder.
Cream butter and both sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix together with flour, oatmeal, salt, baking powder and soda.
Add chips, candy and nuts.
Roll into balls and place 2-inches apart on cookie sheet.
Bake for 6 minutes at 375°.
Makes 112 cookies. Recipe can be halved.
Let set on cookie sheet several minutes to cool before removing.

title: tartar sauce
directions: Stir well.
Cover and chill for 2 hours before serving.
Will stay good in refrigerator for several weeks.

title: lemon chicken
directions: Wash and dry chicken thoroughly and rub with pepper.
Puncture 2 lemons 20 times each and place inside chicken.
Skewer and tie legs loosely.
Place breast side down in preheated 350° oven for 20 minutes.
Turn breast side up and cook for another 20 minutes. Raise temperature to 400° and cook for another 20 minutes.

title: navajo fry bread
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, salt and dry milk powder. Add enough warm water to form dough.
Knead until dough is soft but not sticky.
Let stand covered for 2 hours. Shape into 2 inch balls. Flatten into 8 inch circles.
Heat 1/2 inch oil in large frying pan.
Fry dough until brown. Turn over and brown the other side.
The thinner the circles, the crisper the fry bread.

title: baked eggs
directions: Melt margarine.
Blend in flour, salt and prepared mustard. Add milk and cook, stirring constantly until mixture thickens and comes to a boil.
Remove from heat; add grated cheese, stirring occasionally until cheese is melted.
Stir in Tabasco.
Divide sauce into 6 individual baking dishes.
Break 1 or 2 eggs into each dish.
Bake in a moderate oven (350°) until eggs are set, about 12 minutes.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Mix all together in big bowl.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake for 55 minutes at 350°.

title: pineapple angel food cake
directions: Combine ingredients and place in 9 x 13 pan, ungreased, and bake according to package directions.
Top with fat-free whipped topping.

title: pudding dessert
directions: Mix ingredient for crust.
Put into 9x13 inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Cool.

title: krazy kake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan (do not grease pan).
Level off with fork.
Make 3 wells in dry mixture. Put cider vinegar into one, oil into one and vanilla into one.
Add water over top and mix with fork, but do not beat.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes or until done.
Put 1 1/2 cups mini-marshmallows on top of cake and put back in oven until melted; spread evenly over top.
Frost with 2 squares unsweetened chocolate, 1/4 cup powdered sugar and 1/4 cup butter, melted together.

title: soda bread
directions: Blend together first 6 ingredients with fingers.
Add raisins and buttermilk (more if necessary).
Turn out on floured surface and knead.
Put in square 9 x 9-inch tin.
Score on top with knife.
Bake at 350°.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together.
Add oil, eggs and vanilla and blend well.
Bake in three nine-inch pans (grease and flour each pan) at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: stuffed chicken rolls
directions: Stir margarine into hot water until melted.
Add stuffing and egg.
Stir until moistened.
Spoon stuffing on chicken and roll tightly and secure with toothpicks.
Place in baking dish.
Brush with margarine and sprinkle with pepper.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cover with chicken gravy.

title: yankee jambalaya
directions: In an 8-quart pot, boil the chicken until it falls off the bone.
Strain the broth and debone the chicken.
Slice the sausage in about 1/4 to 3/8-inch round slices and in the same empty pot, fry in small amount of oil.

title: lemon mousse pie
directions: In a small saucepan, combine gelatin, lemon juice and water. Let stand 1 minute.
Stir over medium heat until dissolved.
Stir in lemon peel and food coloring.
In a small bowl combine cream cheese and sugar.
Beat until smooth and fluffy.
Gradually add the gelatin mixture.
Blend well.
Refrigerate about 15 minutes. Fold in the whipping cream.
Spoon into cooked pie shell. Refrigerate about 1 hour.
Garnish with strawberries.
Store in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: pineapple dessert
directions: Heat milk and dissolve marshmallows and let cool.
Add pineapple and whipped cream.
Cover bottom of dish with 1/2 of the graham cracker crumbs.
Pour cream mixture, then cover with remaining crumbs.
Top with maraschino cherries.
Let stand overnight.

title: prime rib
directions: Preheat oven to 235°.
Season ribeye with seasoning salt, pepper and kosher salt.
Place ribeye on roasting rack.
Leave airspace between rack and drip pan.
Load the oven with the ribeye and then turn oven down to 225°.
Cook for 3 hours, until internal temperature reaches 140° for medium-rare.
Turn oven down to 150° and hold until serving.
Serve with au jus.

title: beefaroni meat sandwich
directions: Saute onions and luncheon meat cubes in margarine.
Add mustard and beefaroni; mix well.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Spoon mixture onto buns; top with cheese slices.
Serves six.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Cream together sugars and shortening.
Add eggs and milk; mix well.
Sift together flour, salt, soda and baking powder.
Add creamed mixture.
Mix well.
Add apples.
Pour in a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle a mixture of white and brown sugar and cinnamon over top.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: fish in foil
directions: Tear foil in 18 x 20-inch pieces.
Make 4 boats.
Place a slice of onion on bottom. Put fish on top.
Place veggies on side of fish.
Sprinkle with seasonings.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or put on barbecue grill.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, except crackers and nuts.
Pour mix into 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Top with cracker crumbs, then nuts.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: heavenly seven layered salad
directions: In 2-quart serving bowl, layer lettuce, tomatoes, mushrooms, peas, cheese and onions.
Spread mayonnaise over onions, sealing to edge of bowl.
Sprinkle bacon over top, if desired.
Cover and chill several hours or overnight.
Makes 8 servings.

title: spaghetti sauce with meat
directions: Brown ground beef.
Saute onions and garlic in oil.
Mix together.
Set aside.
Mix tomato paste, crushed tomatoes, tomato soup, dry spaghetti sauce mix and Italian seasoning together.
Add water to achieve desired consistency.
Blend ground meat into sauce.

title: parmesan potato rounds
directions: Slice potatoes into rounds.
Pour oleo into 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan.
In plastic bag, combine flour, cheese, salt and pepper. Shake a few slices to coat with flour mixture.
Single layer over butter.
Turn slices over and sprinkle with Italian seasoning, approximately 30 minutes until tender.

title: indian tacos
directions: Deep fry round, flat bread in hot oil.
Set aside.
Saute hamburger, potatoes, cumin and taco seasoning.
Fold bread like a taco and fill with sauteed filling.
Add shredded lettuce, tomatoes, onions and grated cheese.

title: crabbies
directions: Blend first 5 ingredients and add fish; mix and spread on split muffins.
Place on cookie sheet and freeze.
When frozen, cut in 4 to 6 wedges.
(These can be frozen in freezer bags until needed.)
Broil until browning and bubbly.
These can be cooked without freezing.

title: spinach in cream
directions: Prepare spinach by washing carefully and discarding all tough stems.
Throw spinach into a kettle of boiling water; boil 3 minutes (no longer).
Remove from fire and drain.
In a heavy pan, put butter.
Shake on it the flour; blend well.
Add spinach, onion, cream, salt and pepper.
Heat thoroughly and serve immediately.
This is equally good if thick sour cream is used in place of the whipping cream.
Serves 8.

title: hamantaschen(tart)
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Add vanilla.
Refrigerate overnight.
Let soften 1 hour.
Roll out with as little flour as possible.
Use cookie sheet, greased.
Top with Baker's cake or pastry filling of desired flavor.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Saute onions in margarine or butter.
Add rice and brown with onions about 5 minutes.
Add salt and water and cover until water is absorbed.
Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Do not overcook.
Mix rice, broccoli, soup and cheese spread together.
Put mixture in large greased baking dish and top with crumbs.
Bake in 350° oven about 20 minutes.

title: baked chicken and pineapple
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Wash and skin chicken.
Drain well on paper towels.
Combine rosemary, salt and pepper.
Rub into chicken pieces.
Arrange chicken, meaty side up, in a baking dish. Sprinkle with onion pieces.
Combine pineapple juice and ginger; pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake uncovered 55 to 60 minutes or until tender.

title: toffee treasure cake
directions: Generously grease and lightly flour 9 or 10-inch Bundt pan, Teflon too.
Combine 1/4 cup sugar with cinnamon; set aside. Measure flour by lightly spooning into cup and level off.
In large mixer bowl, combine remaining ingredients, except nuts, candy bars and butter.
Blend at low speed until moistened.
Beat 3 minutes at medium speed, scraping bowl occasionally.
Spoon 1/2 of batter into prepared pan; sprinkle with 2 tablespoons of cinnamon-sugar mixture, then with nuts and crushed candy.
Pour remaining batter and top with 1/4 cup melted oleo over batter. Bake at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes, until top springs back when touched.
Cool in pan for 15 minutes.
Remove from pan.
If desired, sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: strawberry jello cake
directions: Bake cake according to package instructions in flat pan.
After cake is baked, poke holes in it with a toothpick.
Before cake cools, dissolve Jell-O in 1/2 cup hot water.
Add 3/4 cup cold water.
Pour evenly over top of cake.
Allow to cool at least 1 hour.
Mix Whip 'n Chill according to box instructions.
Pour immediately over Jell-O treated cake.
Allow to cool until set.
If desired, a layer of fresh strawberries can be added.
Finally, top cake with Dream Whip.
Refrigerate until served.

title: clown cupcakes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place 2 1/2-inch paper liners in 24 muffin cups.
Prepare, bake and cool cupcakes following package directions.

title: shrimp with garlic sauce
directions: Peel and devein shrimp.
Melt butter.
Add garlic and shallots.
Stir in lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce, cayenne pepper, parsley and wine.
Place shrimp on a broiler pan.
Pour 1/2 garlic butter mixture over shrimp.
Broil 5 inches from heat for 3 minutes.
Turn shrimp over, pour remaining butter mixture and broil 3 minutes.
Allow shrimp to marinate 2 minutes before serving.
Makes 4 servings.

title: luscious lemon squares
directions: In medium bowl, stir together 2 cups flour and 1/2 cup plus 2 tablespoons confectioners sugar.
Cut the margarine into the mixture until it is crumbly.
Pat dough into a 15 x 10-inch nonstick pan.
Bake the crust until set (10 to 15 minutes).

title: overnight salad
directions: Place ingredients in bowl according to order shown.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: clam dip
directions: Put clams in last.
Mix in
blender.
For best results let stand for hours before serving.

title: whip cream cake
directions: Cream butter; add sugar 1 cup at a time.
Cream well.
Add egg one at a time.
Add flour and vanilla.
Whip cream and fold in cake mixture.
Bake 2 hours at 300°.

title: sweet potato pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients and place in buttered baking dish. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: naomi chambliss' turtle cake
directions: Mix cake mix as directed.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch sheet cake pan.
Pour half the batter in pan.
Spread evenly.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Melt Kraft caramels with milk and margarine. Pour caramel mixture over cake.
Sprinkle chocolate chips and chopped pecans over caramel mixture.
Add small amount of coconut, if desired.
Pour remaining batter into pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool before serving.

title: southern veggies over rice
directions: Cook bacon until transparent; add onions and cook slowly.
Add tomatoes; turn up heat and add spices and peas.
Cook 30 to 40 minutes.
Add okra and cook 30 minutes or more.
Better flavor after it ages some (eat next day).
Serve over rice or pasta.

title: pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 9-inch tube pan. Cream butter and sugar.
Beat well, add flour and eggs.
Beat well.
Pour mixture into pan and bake for 1 hour.
Enjoy!

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Mix cake mix as directed on box and bake. When cooled, cut in half and crumble one in bottom of punch bowl. Mix pudding as directed on box, then add layers of each of the following using about 1/4 of each per layer.

title: crock-pot special
directions: Put steak, onion and garlic in pot.
Stir in flour and mix to coat steak.
Add remaining ingredients except sour cream.
Stir well.
Cover and cook on low for 7 to 10 hours.
Add sour cream 30 minutes before serving and stir thoroughly.
Serve over hot noodles or rice.

title: cheesy potato casserole
directions: Melt mayonnaise and cheese together in a large bowl in microwave.
Add frozen hash browns and mix well.
Top with bacon and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until bubbly.

title: yum yum
directions: Combine mix, egg and margarine until crumbly.
Press into 9 x 13-inch dish.
Blend cream cheese, powdered sugar, nuts, eggs and coconut.
Pour over crust and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes. Cool and cut like brownies.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Cook spaghetti; drain.
Mix all ingredients with spaghetti in a greased baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, in a preheated 350° oven, about 30 to 40 minutes.
Makes 12 servings.

title: banana-lemon cake
directions: Cream together butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Sift together cake flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix in alternately with milk and vanilla.
Pour in 2 (9-inch) layer pans.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.
While cake is baking, prepare the following Lemon Filling or use 1 box prepared lemon pie filling or pudding.

title: red, white and blue delite
directions: Prepare pudding according to box.
Slice pound cake and put 1 layer in bottom of clear glass bowl.
Sprinkle rum over cake, if desired.
Spread 1/3 of pudding over cake.
Place sliced strawberries on pudding.
Add another layer of sliced cake, rum and pudding.
Place crushed pineapple or blueberries on this layer. Add final layer of sliced cake, rum and pudding.
Place remaining layer of fruit and refrigerate 1 hour.
(Dessert will settle.) Cover top with Cool Whip before serving.
Can use fat-free cake. Make pudding with skim milk and use lite Cool Whip.
Use any fruit you like.

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook spinach by package directions.
Drain well and squeeze to remove excess moisture.
Combine with all remaining ingredients. Shape into small balls and place on lightly greased baking sheet. Bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chili rellenos casserole
directions: Split chilies; rinse and remove seeds.
Dry on paper towels. Arrange chilies on bottom of 11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish (or 9 x 9-inch pan).
Top with cheeses.
In bowl, beat eggs; add milk and biscuit mix.
Blend well; pour over cheese.
Sprinkle with salt.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 55 minutes or until golden brown. Serve with salsa.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: great chocolate cake
directions: Mix all together.
It's a big cake.
Bake in a tube pan at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Ice with chocolate icing and sprinkle with chopped walnuts.

title: ham and cheese ball
directions: Mix (all but nuts), roll in ball, chill then roll in crushed nuts.
May be frozen.
Keep refrigerated as it softens and runs in extreme heat or upon long standing.
Serve with crackers.

title: coconut-cashew brittle
directions: Combine sugar, Karo syrup, water and butter in 2-quart glass container; microwave on full power for 17 to 18 minutes, until mixture reaches 270° (hard-ball stage).
Remove from oven and add the raw cashew bits.
Return to oven and cook 5 to 6 minutes longer, until mixture reaches 300° (brittle stage).
Stir in coconut, vanilla and soda.
This temperature is very important as the brittle will remain sticky if this temperature is not reached. Pour onto buttered platter, working quickly.
Cool partially by lifting edges with spatula so mixture won't stick.
When firm, but still warm, turn over.
Pull as thin as desired at this point. When cool, break into pieces and store in airtight container. Makes 2 pounds.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Tear chicken meat from bones in small pieces.
Spread in buttered glass casserole dish.
