Mix soup and milk and spread over chicken.
Mix margarine and water; heat and mix with dressing mix.
Sprinkle over soup mix.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
May add onion and celery, if desired.

title: cranberry chicken
directions: Place chicken in baking dish.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 5.

title: delicious chicken
directions: Lay chicken in dish.
Put cheese on top of chicken.
Pour soup mixture all over chicken and cheese, then put 2 cups of bread stuffing on top, then 1/2 cup oleo on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
(Do not cover.)

title: cornbread
directions: Grease cornbread pan with the meat grease.
Pour mixture into pan. Cook at 450° until brown on bottom, then turn up to broil.

title: hawaiian beans
directions: Brown bacon, onion and pepper.
Drain grease.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake slowly for 2 to 3 hours at 300°.
Bake uncovered.

title: baked corn casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Place in a greased 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: red, white and blue salad
directions: Dissolve strawberry Jell-O in 2 cups boiling water.
Pour in 3-quart glass bowl. Refrigerate until firm.
Dissolve unflavored gelatin in 1/2 cup cold water; set aside.
Over low heat, carefully dissolve sugar in whipping cream, stirring constantly, until mixture nearly boils. Remove from heat and add unflavored gelatin.
Cool.
Blend in sour cream and vanilla.
Pour over first layer.
Refrigerate until firm. Dissolve the raspberry Jell-O in 1 cup boiling water.
Add the blueberries and juice.
Pour over second layer. Refrigerate until firm.

title: confetti chocolate chip cookies
directions: Combine Crisco, brown sugar, milk and vanilla in large bowl. Mix with mixer; beat in egg.
Combine flour, salt and baking soda. Beat into creamed mixture at low speed.
Stir in walnuts and chocolate chips.
Drop by tablespoon.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 9 minutes.

title: fiesta nibbles
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a large bowl; stir well. Combine taco sauce and next 4 ingredients in a small bowl.
Add cereal mixture; toss gently to coat.
Add cheese; toss well. Spread mixture evenly into a 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan. Bake at 250° for 50 minutes, or until crisp, stirring occasionally.
Let cool completely.
Store in an airtight container.
Yields 6 cups (serving size:
1 cup).

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Chill for at least 1 hour.
Form balls.

title: swiss vegetable medley
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, combine vegetables, soup, 1/2 cup cheese, sour cream, pepper, pimiento and 1/2 can onions.
Pour into 1-quart casserole.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle remaining cheese and onions on top.
Bake, uncovered, for 5 minutes.
This makes 6 servings.

title: olivia's drop sugar cookies
directions: Have all ingredients at room temperature.
Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Cream together butter or margarine, sugar, shortening and vanilla; mix thoroughly.
Add the egg; cream until mixture is fluffy.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Blend in milk.
Drop by teaspoons onto cookie sheets.
Flatten with bottom of glass which has been dipped in sugar.
Bake at 400° for 12 minutes.

title: cherry dump cake
directions: Place crushed pineapple on bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Next, layer pie filling, then cake mix.
Slice butter all over top of dry cake mix.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes until brown.

title: green tomato relish
directions: In large bowl combine tomatoes, peppers and onions.
Sprinkle with pickling salt and mix well.
Cover and chill overnight.
Drain well.
Tie mustard seed, celery seed and pickling spice in a spice bag or cheesecloth.
In 6 to 8-quart saucepan, combine all ingredients and bring to boil over medium heat, stirring occasionally.
Reduce heat and simmer for 30 minutes.
Remove spice bag.
Fill hot pint jars with mixture, leaving 1/2 inch from top. Seal with hot lids and process in boiling water for 15 minutes.

title: crab alfredo
directions: Chop crab meat in small pieces and set aside. Combine all other ingredients and microwave on Medium 6 to 8 minutes or until sauce is smooth. Stir every 2 minutes. Add crab meat and serve over hot cooked pasta. Serve with bread and salad.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix and bring to a boil for 3 minutes until thick.
Pour over cake.

title: black bean salad
directions: Soak and cook beans according to package directions or substitute 2 cans black beans, drained.
Add all ingredients and stir.
This keeps well and is good warm or cold.

title: tunamato
directions: Cook macaroni as directed.
Drain.
Add tuna, Velveeta, milk, salt and tomato soup.
Stir.
Cook on low heat until cheese is melted.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Blend everything together in large mixing bowl.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Makes about 40 cookies.

title: nibbling stix
directions: Combine all ingredients uniformly.
On a floured surface, pat dough out into and 8 inch square.
With a pizza cutter, cut the square in half.
Then, cut each half into 1 inch strips.
Bake at 450 degrees for 15 minutes.
Serve with fancy mustard or cheese dip.

title: vegetable soup with chicken
directions: Simmer on low heat for 1 hour.

title: rhubarb bars
directions: Combine rhubarb, cornstarch, white sugar and water.
Cook until thick.
Add vanilla.
In separate bowl, combine remaining ingredients and mix until crumbly.
Place 3/4 of this mixture in greased 9 x 13 pan.
Spread rhubarb over top, then sprinkle rest of crumbs over rhubarb.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown beef.
Stir in taco seasoning and tomato sauce.
Simmer on medium heat about 30 minutes.
Crush chips and mix with beef mixture.
Pour in casserole dish and top with cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted.
Serve hot.

title: meat filled pizza
directions: Roll out 1 loaf of bread dough to fit a lightly oiled jelly roll pan.
Brown beef, onions and mushrooms.
Drain.
Spread on dough.
Sprinkle with olives, cheese, salt and pepper; pour sauce over all.
Roll out other loaf of bread dough and top, pinching edges.
Put holes in top and bake at 375° until brown, about 30 minutes.

title: mabel's banana bread
directions: Mix ingredients in order given, mashed bananas in last.
Fold in batter.
Bake in a greased loaf pan.
Bake in 325° oven for 50 to 60 minutes.
Serve with butter or cream cheese.

title: butterfinger torte
directions: Mix together butter and powdered sugar.
Add egg yolks and vanilla.
Mix together.
Beat until creamy.
Add Cool Whip.
Fold together.
Pour over broken pieces of angel food cake.
Crush 6 Butterfinger candy bars on top.

title: chiles rellenos with cheese
directions: You will need 6 toothpicks.

title: fettucini alfredo
directions: Cook fettucini in 4 quarts boiling water until tender.
Drain and place back in pot.
Add butter and toss fettucini.
Add the cream; heat until thick.
Add cheese, salt and pepper.
Allow cheese to melt and become a smooth sauce.
Serve hot with Caesar salad and garlic bread.

title: chicken kiev
directions: In a small bowl mix butter, chives and garlic. Shape into a 3 x 2-inch rectangle.
Cover and freeze until firm.
Flatten each chicken breast to 1/4-inch thickness. Cut frozen butter mixture crosswise into 6 pieces.
Place one piece in the center of each chicken breast.
Fold along sides over butter.
Fold ends up and secure with a toothpick.
Combine cornflakes, parsley and paprika. Dip chicken with buttermilk and coat evenly with cornflake mixture.
Place chicken seam side down on a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake, uncovered, 425° for 35 minutes.
Remove toothpicks before serving.
Serve with rice.
Makes 6 servings.

title: mayonnaise
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Blend in egg yolks.
Add vinegar; mix well.
Add salad oil, 1 teaspoon at a time, beating with rotary or electric beater until 1/4 cup has been added.
Add remaining oil in increasing amounts, alternating last 1/2 cup with lemon juice. Makes 2 cups.

title: stuffed potatoes
directions: Saute onions until soft but not brown.
Combine beef, onions, oil or butter, pine nuts, seasoning and lemon juice.
This is your stuffing.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Remove seeds from all peppers
Place ingredients in food processor or blender and puree.
Store in an airtight container in refrigerator until ready to use.
Makes about 2 cups.

title: cheese-garlic biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix Bisquick, cheese and milk.
Drop dough by spoonfuls onto lightly greased pan.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.

title: meat balls with grape jelly
directions: Mix egg, milk, seasonings and crumbs.
Let stand a few minutes before adding beef.
Shape into small balls and brown. Remove balls from pan and add the jelly and chili sauce to drippings in pan. Replace balls and heat.

title: pancit sotanghon
directions: Drain sotanghon and cut to short strands.
Set aside.
Saute onion in hot oil. Add chicken breasts and saute until the meat becomes firm and white.
Season with salt, patis and white pepper. Add chicken broth.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Add vegetables and cook until snow peas are done, but still crisp, about 4 to 5 minutes.
Add sotanghon and cook for a few minutes more.

title: cold oven pound cake
directions: Cream sugar,
butter and shortening.
Add eggs one at a time; beat
after
each.
Add
flour and milk alternately with flour being added last.
Add vanilla, lemon and brandy flavorings.
Add baking
powder
last.
Place
in greased tube pan. Place in cold oven.
Turn
heat to 325° or 350°.
Bake 1 hour and 15
minutes or
longer.
Cool
and remove from pan.
Cool about 10 minutes.

title: gorilla casserole(serves 8)
directions: Brown the ground beef in the 2 tablespoons oil (about 5 minutes). Add chopped onion, celery and grated carrots.
Cook for another 5 minutes. Stir in the tomatoes, salt, oregano, pepper and garlic powder. Bring to a boil. Lower the heat and cover.
Simmer for 1 hour.

title: plains, georgia cake
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients until well blended.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Fold in nuts and peanut butter chips.
Pour into a greased and floured Bundt pan. Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: dark chocolate cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients. Add remaining ingredients, except boiling water. Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes. Stir in boiling water. Pour into 2 (9-inch) pans or 3 (8-inch) or 1 oblong. Bake at 350 degrees for 30 to 35 minutes. Ovens may vary, so check in center. Cool completely and frost.

title: apple bread pudding with vanilla sauce
directions: Mix cream, milk, eggs, egg yolks, sugar, vanilla and 1/4 teaspoon of cinnamon until blended.
Add bread, apples and raisins and toss until saturated.
Let set for 1 hour.
Pour pudding into greased 8-inch square pan.
Sprinkle 1 tablespoon of sugar and cinnamon over top.
Place pan in shallow pan and fill with water until 2/3 of the way up sides of pudding pan.
Bake 50 minutes in preheated 350° oven.

title: fresh summer pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 475°.
Prepare pan with olive oil and sprinkle with corn meal. Stretch out pizza dough until very thin.
Top with a little olive oil.
Rub around top of dough.

title: creamed corn
directions: Cook corn
with butter over low heat.
Slowly add milk, water, salt and pepper.
Stir.
Cook ten minutes.

title: crescent roll sandwiches
directions: Divide crescent roll triangles.
Place four on a cookie sheet and flatten the triangles a bit.
Place sliced meat on triangle, then cheese.
Cover tops of sandwiches with remaining triangles. Flatten and pinch top and bottom rolls together.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: rollups
directions: Place slice of hamm out flat and spread with cream cheese, enough to cover the whole piece. Place pickle or crab leg on top of cream cheese. Roll up and slice. Place toothpicks into sections to help hold together.

title: pork chops and cabbage casserole
directions: Brown 4 to 6 chops on both sides and place in a baking dish. Arrange a layer of thinly sliced potatoes over chops.
Season with salt and pepper.
Cut cabbage into 1/4 inch slices (remove the core) and place in a layer over potatoes.
Dilute 1 can of cream of celery soup or cream of mushroom (or both) with equal parts of water or milk.
Pour over all, bake covered at 375° for 1 hour. You can add an additional layer of potatoes and cabbage using 2 cans of soup.

title: eggnog
directions: Beat egg whites separately; set aside.
Beat egg yolks until thick, then fold in egg whites.
Add 1 cup of sugar, milk and rum. Beat heavy cream until thick and add to mixture.
Add the store-bought eggnog.

title: delicious banana bread
directions: Melt butter; stir in sugar.
Add beaten eggs and mashed bananas.
Add 1 cup flour with soda and salt.
Add other flour mixed with nuts.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake 350 degrees for one hour.

title: candy coated nuts
directions: In a heavy 2-quart saucepan, bring sugar, sour cream or yogurt and oleo to a boil.
Cook to a soft ball stage, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat and add vanilla and cinnamon. Stir until mixture begins to thicken.
Add nuts and stir until well coated.
Turn out onto buttered cookie sheet.
Separate into clusters, individual nuts or small pieces.
Makes 1 1/2 pounds.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine flour, sugar, salt, baking powder and cinnamon.
Mix and add wet ingredients.
Bakeat 350° in a greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3 pan for 1 hour until done.

title: sugared pecans
directions: Preheat oven to 325 degrees.
Melt butter in 13 X 9 X 2 glass baking pan.
Beat egg whites, at room temperature, until soft peaks form.
Gradually add sugar and salt beating until very stiff.
Fold in pecans.
Spread mixture into melted butter.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes, stirring at 10 minute intervals, until butter is absorbed and coating is browned on nuts.
Remove and spread on wax paper to cool.
Store on air tight container.
Yield 3 1/2 cups.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream well butter and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time.
Beat well after each egg.
Add vanilla and almond flavoring.
Sift together cake flour, plain flour, salt and baking soda. Alternating with sour cream, add flour and sour cream to butter and sugar mixture.
Beat well.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: lefse
directions: Boil water and butter.
Add potato flakes and milk, then add sugar, salt and flour.
Cool and work on a floured surface.
Roll thin and bake on lefse griddle.
Remove to damp towel, covered with waxed paper.
Place sheet or paper over each lefse.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs, bananas and nuts, then add flour and soda.
Pour into greased and sugared (instead of flour) bread pan.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: kidoni(quince jelly)
directions: Place sliced
quince
in water quickly after slicing to prevent darkening.	Drain
and
place
in
kettle
with 2 cups water.
Cook,
covered,
until tender, about 15 to 20 minutes. Add sugar and boil on high heat to thicken syrup.
Add vanilla and lemon juice
quickly.
Stir 2 or 3 times and boil for 3 or 4 more minutes.
Stir in almonds until evenly distributed and quickly remove
from heat.	Cool, then place in glass containers for refrigerator or canning jars for storing.

title: moist onion chicken
directions: Thoroughly mix soup mix and bread crumbs.
Brush chicken pieces on all sides with mayonnaise.
Pour crumb mixture on wax paper.
Roll chicken in crumbs until well coated.
Place in a shallow pan.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes or until golden brown.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit well.
Prepare pudding according to package directions.
Fold in whipped cream.
Fold fruit into pudding mixture along with marshmallows and bananas.

title: beef stew
directions: Brown beef in pan with a little Crisco.
Add tomatoes (chop them up a little), broth, marjoram, salt and pepper.
Cover and cook until meat is almost tender.
Add onion, potatoes, carrots, celery and parsley.
Let simmer.
(I usually let it simmer for 3 to 4 hours.)
Stir occasionally.

title: barbecued beef brisket
directions: Cover brisket with liquid smoke.
Add all other ingredients, except barbecue sauce, in generous amount to brisket.
Leave in refrigerator overnight.
Cover; bake at least 5 hours at 275°. Uncover.
Pour barbecue sauce over meat and bake an additional hour.
May be fixed a day ahead to insure brisket is well done when served.

title: brownies
directions: Melt butter and chocolate.
Beat together eggs and sugar.
Add chocolate mixture to egg mixture.
Add flour, salt and baking powder. Add nuts and vanilla. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine potatoes, sugar, eggs, vanilla, milk and coconut. Pour into an 8 x 12 x 2-inch casserole dish.
Sprinkle with topping.
Bake in a 350° preheated oven for 30 minutes.

title: rice pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake about 1 hour or until set, at 350°.

title: ribbon jello mold
directions: Helpful Hint:
Cream filling can be done in a blender, re-blend before each addition.
Milk can be heated in a microwave.

title: deer jerky
directions: Mix meat and spices together.
Roll a piece, about the size of a grapefruit, between two pieces of wax paper.
Roll to 1/4-inch thickness.
Remove top piece of wax paper; place meat on a cookie sheet, leaving bottom piece of wax paper on.
Brush on equal amount of liquid smoke and water, about 4 tablespoons of each in a small dish.
Bake at 100° for 5 hours, then turn meat over, remove wax paper and baste.
Bake again for 1 hour, remove from cookie sheet and cut into strips.

title: jo ann's olive dip
directions: Chop pepper, olives and onion.
Mix and add taco sauce. Tastes best when refrigerated overnight.
Tomatoes (chopped) can be added.
Serve with Doritos corn chips.
Yummy.

title: hot curried fruit salad
directions: Drain all fruit well.
Cut into small bite sized pieces. Place into 9 x 12-inch buttered baking dish.
Sprinkle with mixture of remaining ingredients.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°. Serve hot.

title: fiesta rice
directions: Saute the celery, green pepper and onion in butter until wilted.
Mix with the remaining ingredients and pour into a large casserole dish.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sausage balls
directions: Shape into balls. Place onto slightly greased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: seafood chowder
directions: In large saucepan, combine first 4 ingredients.
cook over low heat 10 minutes; stir now and then.
Add whitefish; cook 5 minutes more.
Remove bay leaf.

title: marinated mushrooms
directions: Mix all ingredients together and marinate in a bowl in refrigerator for 3 to 5 days.

title: beef bacon and cheese steak
directions: Rinse steak (rub down with mixture of softened margarine, salt, pepper and garlic salt); broil in oven until cooked the way you like it.
While steak is in oven, fry bacon until crisp.
Cool and crumble into small pieces.
Set aside in small bowl.
Melt Velveeta in microwave or in double boiler.
When steak is done, ladle cheese over steak; crumble bacon on top of cheese and garnish with onion slices or cooked onion.

title: parmesan puffies
directions: Preheat oven to 475°.
Dip biscuit tops in melted butter, then cheese.
Place, cheese side up, on a baking sheet.
Bake until golden brown, 8 to 10 minutes. Serve hot.

title: meatless lasagna
directions: Combine Ricotta, half the Mozzarella, the egg and the spinach plus the spices.
In 13 x 9 x 2-inch greased pan, layer 1/2 cup spaghetti sauce, 1/3 of the noodles, 1/2 cheese mixture.
Repeat. Finish with final noodles, 1/2 c. spaghetti sauce and 1/2 remaining Mozzarella.
Add water to edges of pan by pulling noodles away from sides of	pan.
Fill water up to top layer. Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove foil immediately but let lasagna sit 15 minutes.

title: puffy meat patties
directions: Beat egg yolks until lemon colored.
Add ground meat, salt, baking powder, pepper, parsley and onion.
Mix thoroughly.
Fold in the beaten egg whites.
Blend gently.
Dip with large spoon into about 1/8-inch very hot oil.

title: sweet 'n sour shrimp
directions: Cut large shrimp in half. Cook onion and green pepper in margarine until tender, but not brown.
Drain pineapple and reserve syrup. Combine pineapple syrup, vinegar, sugar, cornstarch, soy sauce, dry mustard and salt. Shake together until well blended.
Add to cooked vegetables. Cook, stirring constantly, until thick and clear. Gently stir in pineapple chunks, cherry tomatoes and shrimp.
Heat thoroughly.
Combine cooked rice and almonds. Serve sweet and sour mixture over almond rice.
Makes 6 servings.

title: spanish beans
directions: Brown together the beef, onion and garlic and drain.
Mix in remaining ingredients and simmer on low for 20 or 30 minutes.

title: beef pot pie
directions: Cut beef into small pieces.
Saute pepper and onion in oil until brown.
Add meat, soup, mushrooms, garlic powder and salt. Simmer for 20 minutes.
Mix 2 tablespoons cold water with 2 tablespoons cornstarch.
Add to hot filling and stir.
Pour mixture into pie shell and top with 2 cups sliced potatoes.
Top with pie shell and bake at 350° until brown.

title: potato soup
directions: Saute onion and celery in oil until soft (do not brown).
Peel and cook potatoes (cut in small cubes).
Add chicken broth and potatoes to onion and celery; simmer.
Just before serving, add half and half and milk to taste.

title: rice chantilly
directions: In saucepan combine pudding, rice, salt and amount of milk pudding mix calls for.
Cook as directed, then refrigerate placing wax paper directly on surface to prevent formation of skin.
Into cooked rice mixture, fold whipped cream, sugar and vanilla.
Spoon into 6 sherbet glasses.
Sprinkle with nutmeg; refrigerate.
Also nice spooned over almost any fresh, frozen or canned fruit.

title: farmer's market(6 servings)
directions: Cook the presoaked beans for about 1 1/2 to 2 hours in plenty of water with the salt, bay leaf and oregano.
Remove them from the heat when they are soft, but not mushy, as they will continue to cook in the stew.
Drain the beans and save the broth.

title: mixed fruit salad
directions: Mix strawberries, papayas and kiwi.
Toss with Poppy Seed Dressing.
Serve on salad greens and sprinkle with toasted almonds if desired.

title: homemade macaroni & cheese
directions: Preheat oven to 375. Boil macaroni until tender not soggy (about 8 minutes), drain well and transfer to a large bowl. Mix macaroni with remaining ingredients reserving 1/4 cup of milk and 1/4 cup cheese. Pour ingredients into baking dish, pour reserved milk over top and sprinkle with reserved cheese. Bake until top is golden brown about 25 minutes.

title: red jello salad
directions: Dissolve raspberry gelatin in 1 cup hot water.
Stir in pie filling.
Let harden in 11 x 7-inch dish.
Dissolve lemon gelatin in 1 cup hot water.
Beat cream cheese and mayonnaise together. Add lemon jello gradually.
Stir in undrained pineapple.
Whip the 1/2 cup whipping cream or Cool Whip.
Fold miniature marshmallows into cream.
Combine with lemon gelatin mixture.
Pour the lemon on the raspberry mixture.
Let harden.
Cut in squares.
Serves 9 to 12.

title: our own fish sticks
directions: In a small bowl, combine the eggs and sour cream. Mix well. Place the bread crumbs in a shallow dish. Season the fish with the salt and pepper. Dip each fish strip into the egg mixture, then the bread crumbs, coating completely.

title: freezer slaw
directions: Mix and let stand 1 hour.

title: chinese pot roast chicken
directions: Rub chicken pieces thoroughly with 1/4 cup soy sauce and let stand for 15 minutes.
Brown chicken
slowly in hot oil.
Add sherry and garlic; cover and simmer 30 minutes or until tender. Meanwhile, cut celery and green onions in slices.
Remove chicken from pan and keep warm.
Add celery and green onions to pan and stir-fry.
Combine remaining ingredients and 3/4 cup water.
Stir into pan and cook until thickened.
Serve sauce and vegetables with chicken.

title: german beef supper
directions: Brown meat in hot Crisco, add apple, carrot, onion, 1/2 cup water, wine, salt, garlic, bouillon cubes, bay leaf and thyme. Cover and simmer for 2 hours.
Remove bay leaf.
Cook as per package directions the noodles.
Drain.
Add margarine and poppy seed to noodles and mix.
Combine cornstarch and cold water.
Add to beef mixture.
Cook and stir until thickened.
Add 1/4 teaspoon Kitchen Bouquet for color and mix.
Serve over poppy seed noodles. Serve with pumpernickel bread.

title: feather rolls
directions: In a bowl, add oil, sugar and salt to milk.
When lukewarm, add yeast.
Stir well and add eggs and enough flour to make a stiff dough.
Cover and let rise until double.
Punch down and put in muffin pans.
Let rise.
Bake 30 minutes at 375°.
Makes approximately 24 to 30 rolls.

title: savory meat loaf
directions: Whisk egg and meat loaf seasoning mix.
Add onion and green pepper.
Add meat and 1/2 can of tomatoes with the juice.
Form into a loaf.
Put it in a loaf pan.
Add the rest of the tomatoes and juice on top of the loaf.
Bake at 350° until done, approximately 1 hour.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Add more brown sugar; the sweeter the thicker while it is baking with chicken or ribs.
Can be used as a pour over meat if it is almost cooked.
Finish up the last ten minutes; it will get thick the longer it bakes with the meat.

title: cherry cream cheese pie
directions: Soften cream cheese to room temperature;
whip until fluffy. Gradually add condensed milk while continuing to beat until well blended.
Add lemon juice and vanilla; blend well.
Pour into crust.
Chill 2 to 3 hours before garnishing top of pie with cherry pie filling.

title: chicken creole
directions: Split chicken breasts in half lengthwise; cut into 1/2-inch cubes and set aside.
Heat oil in a large skillet, saute onion until translucent.
Add mushrooms and cook over medium heat until liquid evaporates; then add garlic, celery and spices and cook for 1 minute.
Add peppers and cook for 2 minutes.
Stir in tomatoes and cook for about 5 minutes.
Add wine, lemon juice, hot peppers and mix.
Set aside.
In another skillet, heat 1/2 the margarine. Add 1/2 the chicken and sprinkle with black pepper.
Cook over high heat, stirring frequently, until pieces are evenly and lightly browned.
Do not overcook.
Transfer chicken to separate dish. Repeat procedure for remaining chicken and then return the first batch to the skillet.
Pour Creole sauce over all and stir gently to blend.
Simmer together for about 1 minute.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Serves 8.

title: apple (or pear) crunch
directions: Peel and slice apples or pears.
Place in glass baking dish. Cover with white sugar.
Mix brown sugar and flour with butter or oleo to make a paste.
Drop over apples or pears.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Take out and sprinkle chopped pecans over top. Bake another 30 minutes.

title: venison supreme
directions: Combine flour, salt and pepper in plastic bag, add venison, seal and shake to coat evenly.
Heat oil in heavy bottomed stockpot on medium-high heat.
Add venison and brown, turning to cook evenly.
Add mushrooms and onion.
Saute until onions are tender.
Stir in tomato juice, oregano and bay leaf.
Simmer for 25 minutes or until venison is tender.
Add celery and sour cream, simmer, covered for 15 minutes.
Meanwhile cook noodles according to package directions.
Serve venison over noodles.

title: artichoke nibbles
directions: Drain marinade from 1 jar of the artichokes into a frying pan. Drain the other jar.
Chop all the artichokes; set aside.
Add onion and garlic to frying pan and saute until onion is limp, about five minutes.
In a bowl, beat the eggs with a fork.
Add the crumbs, salt, pepper, oregano and hot pepper seasoning.
Stir in the cheese, parsley, artichokes and onion mixture.
Turn into a greased 7 x 11-inch baking pan.
Bake in a 325° oven for about 30 minutes or until set, when lightly touched.
Let cool in pan, then cut into 1 inch squares.
Serve cold or reheat in the pan in a 325° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes about 6 dozen appetizers.

title: refrigerated pickles
directions: First Night:
Soak cucumbers in 2 cups salt and enough water to cover cucumbers.

title: chocolate fudge pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and cook over low heat.
Bake frozen pie crust before pouring the chocolate mixture into it. Bake at 325° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Let cool and serve.

title: irish fadge(potato pancakes)
directions: Mix together the potatoes, salt and a few tablespoons of melted butter.
Add flour to mixture until thickened.
Roll out, using a floured rolling pin.
Use a glass or cookie cutter to cut "dough" into circles or triangles.
Cook on a hot, buttered frying pan until browned on both sides.

title: green enchiladas
directions: Brown the ground beef and onion in skillet. Mix separately the cheese, milk, chip mix, chili peppers, pimento and chicken soup. Layer the tortillas on the bottom of 9 x 13 Pyrex baking dish. Add mixture, then meat. Top with grated cheese. Bake 20 minutes at 350° until bubbly hot.

title: hot salsa
directions: Place whole tomatoes, onion, salt, sugar and at least 3 hot peppers in a blender and chop well.
Pour mixture into a large saucepan.
Add tomato puree.
Simmer on stove for several hours or until desired thickness, stirring occasionally.
Pour into hot pint jars.
A whole hot pepper can be added for extra flavoring to pint jar before sealing.
Place in hot water bath for 10 minutes. Will keep on shelf for years.

title: pumpkin pie pudding
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients in a large bowl.
Fold in topping (enough to make marbleized effect).
Spoon in dessert glasses. Refrigerate an hour.
(Can use more topping when served if desired).
Enjoy.

title: italian potato salad
directions: Toss lightly the first 5 ingredients.
Blend in carefully the dressing and oregano.
Cover and chill 1 hour.

title: squash pickles
directions: *Four tablespoons pickling spice may be used instead of the celery salt and the mustard seed.

title: bill's heavenly waffles
directions: Beat egg; add oil and Bisquick.
Add club soda last.
Stir until mixed.
Pour appropriately onto waffle iron.

title: cheese stuffed bread
directions: Cut bread in half lengthwise.
Hollow out both pieces of bread and set removed portions aside.
Melt butter over low heat.
Add pieces of bread that were set aside and cook until golden.
At the same time, also add garlic and sesame seed.
When it turns golden, remove from heat.
Now add sour cream, Monterey Jack cheese, Parmesan cheese, parsley and 1/2 cup Cheddar cheese.

title: delicious jams(mix and match fruit and jello)
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients and boil for 20 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in the jello until dissolved.
Put into jars.

title: punch
directions: Mix ginger ale, pineapple juice and Hawaiian Punch together and add sherbet.
Good, quick and easy.

title: spinach balls
directions: Mix all ingredients and roll into small balls. Bake in 350 degree oven until warm or microwave for 18 minutes.

title: chicken fried steak
directions: Cut steak into slices, season with garlic and salt.
Dip steak slices in eggs, coat with flour and then bread crumbs.
Fry in frying pan to desired tenderness.

title: chicken curry
directions: Fry on medium-high heat the oil, all spices and celery leaves until absorbed by oil and not powder.
Add tomato sauce and cook until thick.
Skin and cup up chicken and put in large pot. Add sauce to chicken and simmer 20 to 25 minutes.
Add water to not quite halfway to the top of chicken.
Cover and simmer until done.

title: susie dail's quick punch
directions: Dissolve sugar and Kool-Aid or Jell-O in boiling water. Let cool.
Add the other ingredients.
Pour over ice to serve.

title: shrimp congealed salad
directions: Boil soup.
Add cream cheese; beat until smooth.
Add gelatin and cool.
Add remaining ingredients; put into mold.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: chocolate hash snack
directions: Measure nuts, coconut, sunflower seeds and Rice Krispies; place together in a bowl.
Melt white chocolate in a large microwave bowl on Medium-high (70%) power for 2 to 3 minutes.
Add all the other ingredients; stir well and spread on a buttered cookie sheet. Chill until firm; break in 1-inch pieces.
Store in cool place. This makes a nice Christmas gift.

title: no sugar molasses cookies
directions: Combine.
Let stand 1 hour before rolling out.

title: quick coconut muffins
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat the cake mix and butter. Add water, lightly beaten eggs, drained pineapple, almond and coconut extracts; mix well, then fold in coconut and pecans. Spoon into greased or paper-lined muffin tins, filling 2/3 full. Bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes. Cool a bit before removing from pan.

title: orange cupcakes
directions: Squeeze 2 oranges.
Grind 1 orange and lemons.
Make batter for pound cake.
Use 1 teaspoon batter per cupcake.
Bake at 350°. Dip cupcakes in the orange icing.

title: stuffed burgers
directions: In the mixing bowl, stir together sour cream, bread crumbs and pepper.
Add meat, then mix well.
Shape meat mixture into 8 (1/4-inch) thick patties.
Place stuffing-onion (or whatever you prefer) on the 4 patties.
Top with the other 4 patties and pinch the sides to close.
Place in microwave, uncovered, on High for 3 minutes.
Turn patties over.
Rotate dish 1/2 turn and cook for 3 to 5 minutes longer.
Top with cheese.

title: kun koyi pot roast
directions: Toast sesame seeds in a small skillet over low heat, shaking pan often, just until golden brown. Combine seeds with water, soy sauce, molasses, vinegar, green onions, garlic powder, and cayenne in a 2-cup measure. Trim excess fat from beef; place in a large glass bowl; pour marinade over; cover. Refrigerate overnight, turning meat several times in marinade to season evenly. When ready to cook, remove meat from the marinade, then pat dry with paper towels. Brown pot roast in a large skillet. Place meat in a slow cooker; pour marinade over; cover. Cook on low (190-200°) 10 hours, or on high (290-300°) for 6 hours, or until beef is tender when pierced with a fork. Remove beef to a heated platter to keep warm. Turn heat control to high. Combine cornstarch with 1/4 c. cold water in a cup; stir into liquid in slow cooker until well blended. Cover; simmer 15 minutes. Carve meat into 1/4 inch slices; serve with gravy.

title: beef enchiladas
directions: Dip tortillas, one at a time, into hot oil to soften and drain on paper towel.
Sprinkle beef, onion, cheese and pepper on tortilla and roll up.
Place, overlapped side down, in shallow baking dish and cover with enchilada sauce.
Top with grated cheese and bake at 350° until cheese is melted.
A can of nacho cheese soup poured along with the enchilada sauce on top of these enchiladas is good.
Just mix soup and sauce thoroughly and pour over top and heat thoroughly.

title: 4 layer dessert
directions: Mix margarine, flour and 1 1/2 cups pecans together.
Press in bottom of a 2-quart baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 7 to 10 minutes. Mix cream cheese, confectioners sugar and 3/4 of Cool Whip.
Spread over cooled crust.
Mix the milk and pudding mix together.
Spread over the cream cheese layer.
Top with Cool Whip and sprinkle with nuts.

title: fruit and nut cookies
directions: Combine apricots and water, let set 10 minutes; drain well. Sift together dry ingredients.
Beat butter, sugar, fruit rinds, eggs and lemon juice together until fluffy.
Combine flour and butter mixtures with sour cream.
Fold in apricots, candied fruits and nuts.
Drop onto greased cookie sheet 1 1/2 inches apart. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: healthy chicken and noodles soup
directions: *Tastes best with salt and lots of pepper.

title: jewish coffee cake
directions: Cream butter and granulated sugar together.
Add eggs one at a time, mixing well after each. Add vanilla. Sift baking soda, flour, baking powder; add to creamed mixture.
One at a time, fold in gently the sour cream, lemon rind, and juice. Divide half of the batter between pans.

Mix together the light brown sugar, nuts, and cinnamon. Swirl half of this mixture into batter in pans; add remaining batter, then swirl in remaining sugar/nut mixture. Bake in 350 degree oven for 35 to 45 minutes until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: orange yoghurt cake(use yoghurt pot to measure ingredients)
directions: Mix everything but the powdered sugar and orange juice together, pour into an 11 x 7-inch baking pan.
Bake at 325°f. 160°c. gas mark 3 for 1 hour.
Allow to cool, turn out of the pan. Add the orange juice to the powdered sugar until desired consistancy to make a frosting for the cake.

title: chocolate angel delight
directions: Melt first 3 ingredients over hot water.
Add 2 beaten egg yolks and remove from heat. Cool 10 minutes. Add 2 stiffly beaten egg whites.
Mix.
Fold in whipping cream, stiffly beaten (or use Dream Whip).
Put half the angel food cake, broken into pieces, in bottom of buttered 8 x 12-inch pan.
Add half the chocolate mixture, then rest of cake pieces and top with remaining chocolate mixture.
Serve with Cool Whip on top.

title: waffles
directions: Preheat waffle iron.
Place egg yolks in large mixing bowl and whites in small bowl.
To yolks, add buttermilk; beat well.
Add flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Beat until smooth.
Stir in melted butter.
Beat egg whites until soft peaks form.
Fold into batter.
Bake in preheated waffle iron set at medium heat 5 or 8 minutes or until steaming stops and waffle is golden brown.

title: tostitos scoops party dip
directions: Mix well and refrigerate overnight to blend the flavors.
To serve, spoon into Tostitos Scoops (13 scoops = approximately 3 WW points).

title: chipati(makes 14)
directions: Pour warm water into a mixing bowl.
Add salt.
Begin to add flour.
Continue until dough sticks together and is hard.
Add butter and knead dough until it is soft.
Pinch off some dough and roll it out to 6 or 7-inch circle.
Heat until very hot a frying pan.
Cook each chipati until it is a bit brown.
Stack on a plate.
Then add some oil or butter to pan and cook each chipati again, frying both sides of chipati.

title: lemon squares
directions: Mix margarine, 2 cups flour and 1/2 cup sugar together.
Pat into bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.

title: peach delight
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add cold water.
Stir in other ingredients.
Allow to congeal.
Spread topping.

title: cabin buttermilk biscuits
directions: Stir dry ingredients together and blend with lard or shortening.
Add buttermilk, about 1 cup, to make soft dough. Roll out to 1/4 to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut with biscuit cutter. Place on baking sheet and bake in 350° oven for about 10 minutes or until brown.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Grind zucchini, onions and peppers in food grinder or processor until medium coarse.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup salt and let stand overnight.
Drain and rinse well in cold water.
Mix vinegar, sugar, cornstarch and spices.
Bring to a boil in a large kettle.
Add ground vegetables, then simmer 30 minutes.
Ladle into hot jars, leaving 1/2-inch at top.
Process in boiling water for 15 minutes.
Makes 7 pints.

title: u.s. senate bean soup
directions: Place beans
in
enough
water
to cover in a saucepan; bring to a
boil and boil for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and soak for 1
hour.
Drain
and rinse beans.
In a large kettle, place beans, ham
bone
or hocks and 3 quarts water.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat;
cover and simmer for 2 hours.
Skim fat, if
necessary. Add onions, garlic, celery, parsley, potatoes, salt and pepper. Simmer 1 hour longer.
Remove meat and bones from the soup. Remove meat from the bones; dice and return to kettle.
Heat through.
Garnish
with
parsley
or
chives. Yield:
2 1/2 quarts or 8 to 10 servings.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Mix sugar, milk, flour and butter.
Pour into a greased pan and spread fruit evenly on top.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: flying saucers
directions: Prepare Dream Whip with 1/2 cup milk and vanilla in a small bowl.
In another bowl, add rest of milk to pudding and mix.
Beat for 2 minutes and stir into Dream Whip mixture.
Spread filling on crackers and top with another cracker.
Press and smooth edges. Freeze about 3 hours.

title: bacon fry(grzybek ze stoninka)
directions: Fry bacon just until golden in a 10-inch skillet.
Remove 2/3 cup bacon and drippings.
Beat eggs with milk.
Add 1 cup flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Beat until smooth.
Beat in remaining flour.
Pour 1/2 of batter just in center of skillet of bacon and drippings.
Tilt skillet slightly to spread batter. Cook until browned on bottom and set on top.
Turn.
Sprinkle half the reserved bacon and 1 tablespoon drippings over top.
Pour on 1/2 of the remaining batter.
Turn when bottom is browned. Sprinkle remaining bacon and 2 tablespoons drippings on top.
Pour on remaining batter.
Turn when bottom is browned.
Cook until browned.
Cut into wedges for serving.

title: jalapeno corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 450°; grease an 8-inch ovenproof skillet.
In mixing bowl mix dry ingredients.
Stir in next 4 ingredients. Combine remaining ingredients.
Add to dry ingredients and stir only until dry is moistened.
Bake in skillet 25 to 30 minutes or until browned lightly.
Remove from oven and let stand 5 minutes before cutting in pie shaped pieces in 10-inch skillet.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.

title: barb's oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream margarine, sugar, eggs and vanilla together.
Slowly add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes on ungreased cookie sheet.

title: angel food
directions: Take a cup of kindness, mix it well with love.
Add a lot of patience and faith in God above.
Sprinkle very generously with joy, thanks and cheer and you'll have lots of Angel Food to feast on all the year.

title: quick 'n' easy brownies
directions: Mix together cake mix, eggs and oil.
Batter will be extremely stiff.
(May have to wet hands and mix by hand.) Stir in morsels and nuts.
Pat into 9 x 13 x 2-inch greased pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
(Do not overcook.) Cool and cut into bars. Delicious!

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Cook and stir the ingredients, except for the jello, until thick and clear.
Remove from heat and add 1/2 small jello.
Cool and pour over 1 quart of strawberries in pie shell.
Cover with Cool Whip.

title: cherry fluff
directions: Mix wafers, sugar and butter.
Press half of mixture into 9 x 11-inch pan; chill.
Melt marshmallows with milk; cool.
Whip Dream Whip and mix with marshmallow and milk mixture.
Pour half on crumbs; chill.
Add cherry pie mix over this; cover with other half of marshmallow mixture.
Use remaining crumbs on top; chill.

title: triple layer cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
in 13 x 9-inch pan, melt oleo in oven. Sprinkle crumbs over oleo.
Top evenly with coconut, then milk. Bake 25 minutes until lightly browned.
In small saucepan, melt chips with peanut butter.
Spread over hot coconut layer.
Cool 30 minutes.
Chill thoroughly.
Cut into bars.
Makes 36 bars.

title: crostini alle olive(fried bread with olives)
directions: Cut a loaf of French bread into 1/2-inch slices.
Do not cut all the way through.
Butter slices generously.
Sprinkle with garlic powder and grated Romano cheese.
Wrap in foil paper.
Put in 325° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: rice casserole
directions: Bake at 350° about 1 hour in greased casserole pan.

title: pork loin with sour cream gravy
directions: Place roast, fat side up, on a rack in a shallow roasting pan.
Brush with lemon juice, salt, and pepper.
Bake uncovered for 1 hour and 20 minutes at 325°.
Let stand 10-15 minutes before slicing.
Garlic can be inserted in roast in 1/2 inch slits at 1 inch intervals on top of roast (5 cloves of garlic).

title: breakfast dish
directions: Place bread cubes on bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with cheese.
Beat eggs with 2 1/4 cups milk and dry mustard. Spread sausage over cheese and pour on egg mixture.
Dilute soup with 1/2 cup milk and pour over rest of ingredients.
Make night before and refrigerate.
Can also bake 1 1/2 hours at 300°, uncovered.
Very good use for old bread.

title: pickled pig's feet
directions: Wash and scrape pig's feet.
Boil until meat will slip from bone; drain.
Place meat in bowl.
Combine vinegar, cloves, salt, pepper, bay leaf and onion.
Boil 30 minutes.
Add 2 cups broth in which the pig's feet were cooked.
Strain.
Pour over pig's feet.
Let stand 3 days before using.

title: impossible pie
directions: Grease pie pan with butter (this will make 2 pies).
Mix all ingredients.
Pour into greased pie pans.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes (until firm).

title: banana cake
directions: Set the oven at 350°.
Butter a 9-inch square pan.
Cream butter until light and fluffy.
Beat sugar in gradually.
Add eggs, slightly beaten.
Beat thoroughly and add mashed banana and vanilla or lemon extract.
Sift together the pastry or cake flour, baking soda (1 teaspoon if sour cream or milk is used) and 1/4 teaspoon salt.
Add the flour mixture to the butter mixture alternately with milk or cream (sweet or sour).
Spoon into pan.
Bake about 40 minutes.
Frost with cream cheese frosting or serve in squares with whipped cream on top.

title: fiesta guacamole dip
directions: In a small bowl, combine refried beans and chilies.
Spread on large serving plate.
Combine sour cream and taco seasoning. Spoon over bean mixture evenly.
In a small bowl mash avocados; stir in lime or lemon juice and salts.
Spoon evenly over sour cream.
Cover and chill several hours.
Just before serving, garnish with last 4 ingredients.
Serve with tortilla chips. Serves 15.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients. Top with crackers and melted butter. Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: hot dog chili
directions: Saute beef and onions.
Drain off fat.
Add all other ingredients. Stir well.
Simmer about 1 hour. Taste.
Add more chili powder if needed.

title: scripture cake
directions: Blend butter, sugar, spices, and salt.
Beat egg yolks and add.
Sift in baking powder and flour, then add water and honey. Put fruits and nuts in food processor.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg white.
Put in 13 x 9 inch pan.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar when slightly cooled.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix first 10 ingredients together.
Pour into 9 x 13 casserole dish.
Top with dressing mix that has been mixed with margarine. Bake about 30 minutes or until bubbly at 350°.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Cook onion and garlic in shortening; add beef, stirring to keep meat separated.
Mix in the soup, water and chili powder. Cook a few minutes longer. Break spaghetti into 1-inch pieces. Heap into a greased 2-quart casserole.
Pour in the meat mixture and stir until blended.
Cover and bake 1 hour (without stirring) in a 350° oven. Remove cover and stir.
Top with cheese and cook 15 minutes longer or until cheese melts.
Serves 6.

title: date cake
directions: Mix dates with boiling water and cool to lukewarm.
Cream shortening and brown sugar.
Add egg and vanilla.
Beat well. Combine with dates.
Add flour, salt and soda.
Beat well.
Bake in greased 13 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Top with broiled icing.

title: halibut in foil
directions: Place halibut in foil with all ingredients on top.
Wrap foil loosely and close each end.
Put on baking sheet in oven at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: sweet and sour beans
directions: Fry bacon until crisp; dice.
Mince the onion and cook in bacon fat.
Stir in flour.
Add vegetable liquid, vinegar, sugar, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Stir in green beans.

title: monkey bread
directions: Break each biscuit into quarters.
Pour sugar and cinnamon into plastic bag.
Drop in biscuits and shake thoroughly, using all of the sugar-cinnamon mixture.

title: dawn's iced tea
directions: Boil 4 to 6 cups of water and remove from heat. Add 3 tea bags and set aside to brew. Best if steeped until cool. Remove tea bags.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Combine beef, onion, green pepper, salt and pepper in a skillet; cook until beef is brown.
Drain.
Spoon into a 3-quart casserole dish.
Top with Tater Tots.
Combine remaining ingredients, blending well.
Spread over Tater Tots.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until well browned.

title: betty's spaghetti and meatballs sauce
directions: Add to above.
Simmer on low for 1 hour.

title: knaidlach(matzoh balls)
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Beat egg yolks until light.
Add salt, pepper and melted fat to beaten yolks; fold gently into egg whites.
Fold in matzoh meal one spoonful at a time.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour.
Moisten hands and form batter into walnut-size balls.
Drop into rapidly boiling soup or water.
Reduce heat and cook slowly, covered, for 30 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: pot roast meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients and form into a loaf and place in pan large enough to surround with 3 med. potatoes and 3 med. onions, both sliced 1/4 inch thick, and 3 carrots sliced 1/4 in. Sprinkle with 2 tsp. parsley, 1 tsp. salt, and a dash of pepper. Cover tightly with foil. Bake in 375 degree oven for 1 hr. uncover and bake 10 minutes more.

title: fudge pie(no crust)
directions: Melt in pie pan the chocolate and margarine.
Beat eggs slightly and add sugar.
Let chocolate mixture cool a little, then add to eggs and sugar. Stir in flour and add nuts.
Pour back into pie pan and bake 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: layered tostada dip
directions: Combine beans and chili powder; mix well.
Spread on the bottom of a glass pie pan.
Combine avocados, salad dressing, bacon, onion and seasonings; mix well.
Spread on top of the bean mixture.
Layer olives, tomato, chilies and cheese.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Mix all ingredients except butter and beat well.
Add melted butter last.
Bake in 9-inch pie pan at 300° for 50 minutes.

title: 3 in 1 pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together, stirring well.
Pour into single crust pie crust.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Can double recipe for 2 pies.

title: healthy carrot bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 5/8-inch loaf pan.
Stir together flour, sugar, baking powder, soda, cinnamon, salt, nutmeg and cloves in small bowl to mix well.
Beat eggs in large bowl until well blended.
Add oil, vanilla and carrots; beat until well blended.
Fold in walnuts and raisins.
Turn into prepared pan.
Place a row of pecan halves down top center.
Bake in preheated oven for 45 minutes.
Cool bread in pan 10 minutes. Turn out onto wire rack to cool to room temperature.
This loaf slices better if stored overnight.

title: guess-again cookies
directions: Beat butter, sugar and vanilla until fluffy.
Add flour, potato chips and pecans.
Mix well.
Drop by scant teaspoon 2 inches apart onto an ungreased baking sheet.
Flatten by pressing with bottom of glass, greased and dipped in sugar.
Place pecan half on top of each cookie.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: shrimply great mold(serves 8)
directions: Dissolve gelatin in cold water; set aside.
In a saucepan, heat soup; add gelatin mixture; stir until dissolved.
Add cream cheese; remove from heat.
Beat until well blended.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into a well-oiled 1-quart mold; chill until firm.
Serve portion on a crisp lettuce leaf; garnish with a lemon twist.

title: fruity delight
directions: Whip cream until stiff and combine with sour cream, lime juice, sugar and ginger.
Mix well and refrigerate.
Drain peach slices.
Rinse and hull strawberries.
Combine all fruits and mix with dressing.
Chill.

title: jo's gazpacho
directions: Mix all of the above ingredients; test seasoning and chill. Serve in small mugs or glasses with ice cubes.

title: gail's cheese ball
directions: Mix well.
Roll into a ball and coat with 1 cup chopped nuts.

title: french beef stew
directions: Mix together in roaster or covered dish and bake at 325° for 3 1/2 hours, or until meat is tender.
Will be browned and all thickened.

title: peach a la orange
directions: In medium bowl, dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Drain oranges, reserving juice.
Set oranges aside.
Measure juice and add enough cold water to make 1 cup.
Stir juice into gelatin. Chill until it starts to thicken.

title: no bake cookies
directions: In saucepan on low heat, mix together peanut butter, salt and chips.
Crush corn flakes and add to mixture.
Drop on cookie sheet covered with wax paper.
Chill for 10 minutes.

title: honey-mustard swordfish
directions: Arrange steaks in a baking dish.
Combine wine and next 3 ingredients.
Pour over steaks.
Cover and marinate in refrigerator for 1 hour.
Remove steak from marinade, reserving 1/4 cup.
Place marinade in a saucepan and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes.
Coat grill rack with cooking spray.
Place on grill over medium hot coals.
Place steak on rack; cook 15 minutes or until fish flakes easily when tested with fork, turning once and basting frequently with marinade.
Yield:
4 servings (189 calories and 30% fat per serving).

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Mix hamburger, salad dressing and onion together.
In a 9 x 9-inch baking dish, place 1/3 of hamburger, 1/3 of spaghetti, 1/3 of spaghetti sauce and Velveeta slices to cover.
Make two more layers, same as first.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes until cheese is melted and browned.
Let stand a few minutes before serving.

title: russian teacakes
directions: Mix butter, powdered sugar and vanilla. Stir flour and salt together and add to butter mixture. Mix in nuts. Chill dough.

title: instant rice pudding
directions: Make any flavor instant pudding.
Mix in cooked rice. Refrigerate until firm.

title: nachos and cheese
directions: Brown hamburger and onions in skillet.
Drain fat, then add taco seasoning.
Spread nachos on cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with hamburger mixture.
Top with grated Cheddar cheese.
Brown in oven until cheese melts.

title: infallible rice
directions: Saute onion in butter until transparent.
Add broth or make broth from bouillon cubes and water in same utensil, keeping onions in same utensil.
Add rice to hot broth and onions and bring to boil.
Put mixture in casserole, cover and bake at 325° to 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Feeds 4 hungry or 6 polite people!

title: orzo salad(orzo is a small oval pasta.)
directions: Prepare orzo according to directions; drain and cool.
Mix ingredients and refrigerate for at least 2 hours.

title: no fat mild chili
directions: Combine
1/4 cup water and bouillon cube in a 2-quart saucepan.
Bring to a slow boil while adding chopped onions.
Boil for about 1 to 2 minutes; add all of the other ingredients.
Bring to a slow boil.
Cover and reduce heat to simmer for about 1/2 to 3/4 hour.
Serve over white rice.

title: strawberry angel dessert
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Chill until slightly congealed.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Drain and reserve 1 cup juice from berries.
Fold in strawberries and whipped cream.
Rub off brown crumbs from angel cake; tear into pieces.
Put in large bowl and fold in strawberry cream mixture.
Spread in jelly roll pan.
Let set until firm.
Lightly frost with whipped cream. Drizzle with glaze.

title: casserole roasted chicken
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Wash and dry chickens.
Sprinkle cavities lightly with salt and pepper.
Melt butter or margarine in Dutch oven or large, heatproof casserole.
Brown chicken on all sides. Sprinkle with tarragon.
Cover.
Roast 30 minutes.
Add mushrooms and celery.
Roast 30 minutes longer or until chicken is tender.

title: fried squirrel
directions: Clean; cut up squirrel.
Add salt and pepper to meat.
Roll in flour.
Fry until done.
Use for young rabbit too.

title: pickled herring
directions: Soak fillets in cold water for 6 hours, changing water often. Rub fillets under cold water until not slick.
Combine above ingredients; heat until sugar dissolves.
Cool.
Layer slices of herring, sliced red onion, bay leaves and whole allspice.
Add brine; let stand for 3 days.

title: tomato soup cake
directions: Cream together sugar, eggs and shortening; add soup, mixed with soda, alternately with other dry ingredients.
Add raisins. Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: white gooey frosting
directions: Combine in double boiler.
Beat until peaks form.
Remove from heat and add 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Beat and spread.

title: 7-minute frosting
directions: Mix together egg whites, corn syrup, sugar and salt in double boiler top.
Beat slightly with mixer; place over rapidly boiling water and beat constantly until frosting holds stiff peaks, about 7 minutes.
Remove from heat; add vanilla and beat 1 minute.
Add a couple drops of food coloring (red).
Delicious on angel food cake.

title: broccoli cauliflower salad
directions: Break broccoli and cauliflower into small pieces. Fry bacon, drain and break into small pieces. Mix together, adding onions and raisins. Mix together mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar in separate container for dressing. Refrigerate both until needed. Pour dressing over salad mixture and toss well.

title: cheese ball
directions: Blend thoroughly all ingredients.
Refrigerate.
Makes one large ball or two small balls.

title: carrot pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Grease 2-quart casserole.
Beat egg yolks and sugar until light; hold.
Mix cornstarch with small amount of milk.
Heat remaining milk.
Add cornstarch and stir until smooth and slightly thickened.

title: strawberry punch
directions: Put Kool-Aid and sugar in bottom of punch bowl.
Dilute with 1 cup of water.
Put in frozen strawberries, lemonade and orange juice.
Fill bowl half full with ice.
Pour in Sprite as served.

title: top of the stove cabbage casserole
directions: Season meat well; brown with onions, bell peppers and celery. Add tomatoes, sauce, rice and shredded cabbage.
Put extra seasoning because rice and cabbage will absorb seasoning.
Add the 5 cups water; cook, covered, on low heat until cabbage and rice are done.
Serves about 10.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add all other ingredients and mix well.
Pour into mold and let set.
When turning out of mold (if using ring mold), fill the center with cranberry sauce or relish.

title: frenchy's cheese ball
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Form into ball or log.
Refrigerate until firm.
Roll in chopped nuts before serving.
Serve with crackers.

title: todd's baked caramel corn
directions: Melt butter and stir in brown sugar, corn syrup and salt. Bring to a boil, stirring constantly; boil without stirring for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat; stir in baking soda and vanilla.
(It swells; be sure to use a big enough pan.) Gradually pour over popped corn, mixing well.
Turn into a large shallow baking pan or two smaller pans.
Bake in a 250° oven for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Put out onto wax paper on the countertop to cool.
Break large pieces and store in an airtight container or plastic bags.

title: party punch
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water. Add sugar. Add remaining ingredients, except ginger ale.
Mix well. Freeze. Before serving, thaw enough to mash with a potato masher. Place in a punch bowl and add the ginger ale. Serves 80.

title: hot mustard sauce
directions: In a small mixing bowl mix together all ingredients until smooth.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well with hands.
Shape into bite size meatballs.
Bake in oven at 350° until brown.
When done, pour barbecue sauce over it.
Heat slowly until ready to serve.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs thoroughly.
Add sugar and corn syrup.
Add butter, salt, vanilla and pecans.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 300° to 325° and bake almost an hour, or until filling no longer shakes.

title: heavenly orange jello
directions: Empty Jell-O in a mixing bowl.
Pour in 1 cup boiling water. With a fork, break up package of cream cheese in the Jell-O into tiny pieces.
Pour in cup of cold orange juice and mix well. Chill in refrigerator until set.
Empty mandarin oranges (drained) in the Jell-O.
Stir in the Cool Whip and carefully blend. Finish in the refrigerator until ready to serve.
More Cool Whip can be added if desired.

title: chicken rotel casserole
directions: Boil chicken.
Save 1 1/2-quarts broth.
Saute onions and bell pepper in oleo. Cook vermicelli in saved chicken broth and do not drain.
Add tomatoes, cubed cheese and Worcestershire sauce to vermicelli.
Cook 5 minutes longer.
Add drained peas, mushrooms and sauteed onions and pepper.
Add cut up chicken.
Stir thoroughly.
Pour in baking dish and cook at 350° for 45 minutes. Make ahead and freeze.
Let thaw before baking.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix milk and pudding thoroughly.
Add sour cream and orange juice; mix thoroughly.
Chill.
Use with strawberries, grapes and cherries.

title: zucchini jelly
directions: Chop
zucchini in blender.
Drain well.
Mix altogether and cook well for 10 minutes.
Recipe can be doubled.

title: macaroons
directions: Beat egg whites stiff.
Slowly beat in 1 cup sugar.
Fold in cracker crumbs.
Fold in coconut.
Fold in dates and nuts.
Drop by teaspoon.
Can top them with 1/2 red cherry.
Bake in 350° oven.
As soon as edges are tan, shift to upper shelf.
They bake fast.

title: minestrone soup
directions: Soak beans overnight and drain.
Place beans, garlic and onion in water and bring to boil; lower heat and simmer for an hour. Add celery, carrot, potato, green beans, tomato sauce and seasonings.
Simmer another 30 minutes, then add zucchini.
Cook another 30 minutes and add cabbage and macaroni.
Cook until tender, about 20 minutes or so.

title: cabbage salad dressing
directions: Mix well.
Can be poured over cabbage, lettuce or fresh fruit.

title: chicken-pecan fettuccine
directions: Melt 1/4 cup margarine in large skillet; add chicken and saute until lightly browned.
Remove chicken from skillet; set aside. Leave drippings in skillet; add mushrooms, 1/2 teaspoon salt, 1/4 teaspoon pepper and 1/4 teaspoon garlic powder.
Saute until tender.
Add chicken; simmer 20 minutes or until done.

title: chicken poppy seed
directions: Cook 3 to 4 chicken breasts in water until tender.
Mix cut up chicken, soup, sour cream and poppy seed together.

title: pecan drops
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Chop pecans rather coarsely.
Cream butter and shortening until smooth, then beat in confectioners sugar gradually.
Stir in flour thoroughly; add vanilla and pecans.
Mix well.
Roll in balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until delicately brown.
Roll again in confectioners sugar.

title: ham on bun
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients together.
Spread on both sides of 8 buns.
Add ham and cheese.
Wrap buns in foil.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all.
Pour into well-greased and floured pan.
Cook at 350° until golden brown.

title: crepes for 10
directions: Mix all together with 1/4 cup milk and a little more to make batter easy to pour. Cook on a hot skillet greased with vegetable oil over medium heat.

title: potato salad
directions: Put the potatoes in a pot with enough water to cover them and cook until tender, about 35 minutes or less, according to size. Drain off the hot water and pour in cold water to cool the potatoes.
When they are cool enough to handle, peel and dice the potatoes and place them in a large bowl.
Add all the other ingredients and mix well.
Refrigerate until ready to serve. Serves about 10.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook the vegetables as directed on package and drain.
Combine soups and cheese.
Heat until cheese melts.
Pour over vegetables and place in baking dish (9 x 13-inch).
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Put onion rings on top and bake 5 more minutes.

title: frozen marshmallow treats
directions: Mix all the ingredients together.
Line 8 muffin cups with paper baking cups.
Spoon mixture into the 8 cups.
Freeze about 2 hours.
When ready to serve, take them out of the freezer and let them stand for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: sausage snack wraps
directions: Separate dough into 8 triangles and cut lengthwise into thirds.
Place sausage on shortest side and roll.
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: peanut cream chocolate bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, combine cake mix, oil and 1 egg until crumbly.
Measure 1 cup crumbs to reserve for topping. Press remaining crumbs in bottom of ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake for 10 minutes.

title: cinnamon ornaments
directions: No baking and simple for kids.
Mix 3/4 cup applesauce with 4 (12 ounce) ground cinnamon for stiff dough.
Roll out to 1/4 inch thickness.
Cut with cookie cutters.
Make hole for ribbon.
Put on rack to dry.
Let air dry several days, turning occasionally. Makes 12.

title: broccoli-corn casserole
directions: Alternate all the ingredients (mix egg with corn and melted butter).
Put in casserole.

title: banana bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan or two 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pans.
Measure all ingredients into a large mixing bowl.
Beat on medium speed 1/2 minute, scraping sides and bottom of bowl constantly.
Pour into pan(s).
Bake 55 to 65 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Remove from pan. Cool thoroughly before slicing.

title: "easy" cheese ball
directions: Ahead of time, let cream cheese and garlic cheese soften to room temperature.

title: geneva cason's watergate salad
directions: Mix pudding.
Fold in pineapple, then Cool Whip, coconut and nuts.
Chill until firm and serve.

title: hot beef macaroni casserole
directions: Dice roast beef; add to macaroni.
Mix in peas, cheese, celery, onion, green pepper, ketchup, mustard and mayonnaise. Pour into well-greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs and top with butter.
Bake in 400° oven for approximately 25 to 30 minutes.

title: tuna-macaroni casserole
directions: Cook macaroni as package directs, drain.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Combine all.
Bake in ovenproof dish at 350° for 30 minutes (or until bubbly).
Serve with crackers.

title: fish or chicken stew
directions: Fry fatback and take up.
Fry onions in fatback grease until they turn clear.
This does better on medium heat.
Add tomato soup and water.
Then add sugar, onion soup mix, hot sauce, salt, pepper and catsup.
Let come to a boiling point.
Add fish and simmer very slow until fish is tender.

title: quick biscuits
directions: Stir flour, baking powder and salt.
Add shortening and cut into flour mixture like pie dough.
Add milk.
Stir until moist. Knead on lightly floured board 10 to 12 strokes.
Pat out to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut with small round glass dipped in flour, or use biscuit cutter.
Bake at 425° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: chow-chow
directions: Next morning, mix celery seed and mustard seed.
Mix in turmeric until light yellow.
Mix 1 cup sugar to vinegar and 1/2 quart water to 1 quart vinegar.
Add a little more water, if needed, to cover stuff while cooking.
Cook at medium heat until cabbage is done.
Can while hot.

title: cottage meat loaf
directions: In a large bowl combine all ingredients.
Put mixture in a 9x5 loaf pan.

title: classic waldorf salad
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover; chill.
Makes 5 1/2 cups.

title: lemon fluff
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water. Add lemon juice and pineapple juice. Cool.

title: breakfast special
directions: Layer in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan the bread, sausage, cheese and eggs.
Refrigerate overnight.
In the morning before baking, combine cream of mushroom soup and 1/2 cup milk.
Pour over the top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes until brown on top.

title: tuna shoestring salad
directions: Toss all ingredients except potatoes.
Cover and refrigerate for 1 hour; add potatoes just before serving.

title: divinity
directions: Heat the sugar, water, corn syrup and salt, stirring constantly until the sugar has dissolved.
Continue to cook without stirring until the syrup forms a hard ball when dropped in cold water.
Beat egg whites until they peak.
Pour the syrup slowly into the egg whites.
Continue to beat until the candy is stiff enough to hold its shape.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Drop by teaspoon on wax paper or pour into greased pans, cutting into squares.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour bread loaf pan. Combine flour, cinnamon, baking soda, salt and baking powder in mixing bowl.
In another bowl, beat eggs, sugar and vegetable oil with electric beater.
Beat in vanilla and flour mixture.
Stir grated zucchini into batter.
Spoon batter into pan and bake 55 to 60 minutes or until tester (toothpick) comes out clean.
Remove from oven and cool on rack.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: hash brown potatoes
directions: Mix butter or oleo through the other ingredients, except cheese and chips.
Put 1/2 of cheese over dish of potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Take out of oven; sprinkle crushed potato chips and rest of shredded cheese.
Put back in oven for 15 minutes.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: cranberry coffee cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9-inch tube pan.
Sift flour with baking powder, baking soda and salt.
In a large bowl, beat butter.
When creamy, add sugar, 1/4 cup at a time.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Mix in almond extract.
Stir in dry ingredients, about a fourth at a time, alternating with sour cream.
Spoon half the batter into the pan.
Add half the cranberry sauce.
Add remaining batter and cranberry sauce. Sprinkle with almonds.
Bake for 55 minutes.
Cool 15 minutes, then turn cake out of pan.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: layered bean dip
directions: Mix together mayo, sour cream, and taco seasoning mix.
Layer as follows, on a large platter, bean dip, guacamole, sour cream mix, vegetables (tomato, olives, onions together) grated cheese. Makers enough for large platter to feed about 10-15 guests.

title: pecan delights
directions: Combine cake mix, butter and 1 egg.
Mix at high speed with electric mixer until mix is crumbly.
Press mixture into 9 x 13 pan.
Blend milk, Heath bits, 1 egg, pecans and vanilla in mixing bowl.
Pour over cake mixture.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes. Cool completely.
Cut and serve with scoop of ice cream, if desired.

title: strawberry pie
directions: One cup of sour cream:
Combine 7/8 cup of sour milk and 3 tablespoons butter or 8 ounces plain yogurt.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: In casserole dish, layer ground beef, potatoes and onions in this order twice, finishing with a layer of ground beef on top (there will be 3 layers of ground beef).
Pour tomato soup on top. Salt and pepper to taste.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until done.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in baking pan.
Let cool.
Mix together the sugar and flour.
Add milk and stir, blending well.
Pour sliced peaches into buttered pan, then pour mixture over this.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix and store in airtight container. Use 2 heaping teaspoonfuls per cup of hot water.

title: corned beef and cabbage
directions: In crock-pot:
Put ingredients in pot in order given.
Cover and cook on low for 12 to 24 hours or high for 7 to 10 hours. Push cabbage wedges down into liquid after 5 to 6 hours (on low) or 2 to 3 hours (on high).

title: apricot muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes. Makes 9 to 12 muffins.
Low-fat and cholesterol.

title: peanut butter cream pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and salt together.
Mix well.
Stir in warm milk and egg yolks.
Cook over low heat until mixture thickens. Add margarine and vanilla.
Beat with a mixer until smooth.

title: barbecue smoked sausage
directions: Combine all ingredients, except sausage, in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil over medium heat.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Cut each sausage link every 2-inches with diagonal slits halfway through sausage. Place in 400° oven for 20 minutes or on grill until done.
Baste with barbecue sauce often.
Add remaining sauce before serving.

title: society pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers.
Cover with boiling water.
Use same water for 4 days.
Pour off and boil again, putting back over cucumbers.

title: sweet potato pie(carolyn henderson's recipe)
directions: Mix all ingredients; bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Use 2 unbaked pie shells.

title: super sloppy joes
directions: In a Dutch oven over medium heat, cook beef, onion, celery and green pepper until the meat is no longer pink and the vegetables are tender; drain.
Add the next nine ingredients; mix well.
Simmer, uncovered, for 35-40 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: dill pickles
directions: Wash the cucumbers and put in jars.
For each 1 quart jar, use 1 head garlic (whole, separated), 2 hot peppers (sliced 2/3 open) and 1/2 bunch fresh dill.
Put these ingredients on top of cucumbers.

title: "nestle quik" cake
directions: Combine and sift all dry ingredients, then add liquids and mix well.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: chicken veronique
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Place
chicken breasts between 2 sheets of waxed paper, skinned side up and gently pound to 1/4 inch thickness.	 Combine
breadcrumbs,	tarragon,
salt
and pepper and chives in
shallow
dish
and
coat chicken evenly. Melt about half of butter in large heavy-bottomed skillet over medium-high heat.
Add chicken	in
batches
and brown on both sides, using more butter as needed.
Remove with slotted spoon and transfer to shallow baking dish.
Add onions and mushrooms to skillet and saute
until onion is translucent.	Add chicken stock and wine and bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Pour over
chicken, tent dish
with	foil
and
bake
until	heated through, about 10 minutes.
Remove
foil,
add grapes and bake for 5 more minutes.

title: shrimp kabobs
directions: Marinate shrimp in olive oil, lemon juice, parsley, pepper and garlic for 2 hours.
Place shrimp on skewers.
Place on hot grill a couple of minutes on each side.
Serve on bed of rice pilaf with vinaigrette salad on the side.
Excellent!

title: date pinwheel cookies
directions: Cream butter, brown sugar, 1/2 cup sugar, vanilla and egg. Beat until light.
Add sifted dry ingredients.
Chill until firm. Chop dates.
Bring to boil with 1/3 cup water, 1/4 cup sugar and a dash of salt.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Add nuts.
Stir often.
Cool.

title: mississippi mud pie
directions: Layer One:
Mix well the chopped nuts, flour and butter.
Bake 30 minutes at 350° in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Saute onion in oil, then add rest of ingredients.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cook in saucepan over medium heat for about 45 minutes.

title: chicken a la king
directions: In a saucepan, melt butter; blend in flour and salt.
Add broth and milk all at once.
Cook, stirring constantly, until sauce is thick and bubbly.
Add chicken, mushrooms, pimento and wine.
Heat through.
Makes 5 servings.

title: cheesy scalloped potatoes
directions: To make sauce, cook onion in oleo until tender, but not brown. Stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Add milk; cook and stir until thick and bubbly.
Add cheese.
Cook 2 more minutes.
Remove from heat.
Place half of potatoes in greased baking dish.
Cover with half of the sauce.
Repeat layers.
Bake, covered, in a 350° oven for 45 minutes, stirring once.
Uncover; bake another 30 minutes or until potatoes are done.

title: diabetes-oatmeal-raisin cookies
directions: Measure oatmeal into bowl.
Stir in melted margarine, egg and sweetener.
Add flour, baking powder, salt, milk and vanilla. Stir in raisins.
Drop on cookie sheet greased with nonstick spray.
Bake at 350° until done.
Yields 24 cookies.

title: nut marshmallow goodies
directions: Combine chocolate morsels, butterscotch morsels, peanut butter in
top
of double boiler.
Place over hot water until morsels melt.
Stir
until
blended.
Add
marshmallows
and salted peanuts; mix well.
Spread in a foil pan.
Chill until firm.
Cut into 1 inch squares.
Makes 64 squares.

title: quick cherry crumble
directions: Pour pie filling into greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch cake pan. Sprinkle with cake mix and melted butter.
Bake.
Serve warm with whipped cream, ice cream or plain.

title: mexican dip
directions: In a clear casserole dish, layer the following ingredients: bottom cream cheese (spread on bottom of dish), 1/2 jar salsa, 1/2 package shredded cheese, 1/2 can of chilies, 1/2 can of black olives, 1/2 jar salsa, 1/2 package shredded cheese and 1/2 can chilies and black olives.
Bake at 350° covered for 1/2 hour and uncovered for 15 minutes until cheese is bubbly and melted.
Dip nacho chips and enjoy.

title: spicy broccoli spread
directions: In a small saucepan, cook broccoli, covered, in a small amount of boiling, salted water about 12 minutes or until tender.
(Can also be steamed in microwave.)
Drain well.

title: party potatoes
directions: Mix ingredients; put in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°, uncovered.

title: chocolate icing for brownies
directions: Mix butter, milk and cocoa together.
Bring to a boil and boil for exactly 1 minute. Gradually stir in the sugar and vanilla. Fold in the nuts. Spread on top of the brownies.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Serve warm with crackers.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Brown meat, onions and celery in oil in large pot.
Add water, salt and pepper; cook for about 1 hour.
Add all other vegetables except canned corn and green beans.
Cook for about 1 1/2 hours or until vegetables are tender.
Add canned corn and green beans. Cook until hot.
Add egg noodles in during the last 15 minutes. If the soup is too thick, add more water while your are cooking.

title: roast beef roll ups
directions: Determine how many sandwiches you will need, and buy beef and tortillas accordingly.
These are made with the 10-inch fajita tortilla and can be cut in half if you want.
Spread each of the tortillas liberally with the horseradish sauce.
If you have folks that don't care for horseradish, I have used plain mayonnaise.
It just doesn't have the same zip!
Place one slice of roast beef in the center of the tortilla and top with a large leaf of lettuce. Roll up and place face down in a 9 x 13 pan to keep from unrolling.
Repeat with the remainder of tortillas and beef. Cover with Saran Wrap and refrigerate.
These are actually better if you can make them a day ahead.
Slice in half if you want before serving.

title: mama mcquaid's lasagna
directions: Prepare meat sauce:
Finely dice 1 onion and 1 clove garlic. Saute onion, garlic and parsley in olive oil.
Add whole tomatoes, tomato paste, bay leaves, salt and uncooked ground beef.
Bring to a boil; then simmer 45 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Put on water for noodles.

title: sour cream salad
directions: Mix all together and chill.
Best done 3 or 4 hours before time to serve.

title: cornbread
directions: Mix ingredients and bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: tasty cabbage pickle
directions: Mix all ingredients together and boil 45 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Seal while hot in sterilized jars.
Makes about 13 to 15 pints.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Combine the crumbs with the seasoning; add milk and liquid/oil from salmon and the slightly beaten eggs.
Mix well.
Flake the salmon and add to egg mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until firm and brown.

title: easy lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef.
While cooking the ground beef, boil water for lasagna noodles.
Drain fat from ground beef, then pour in spaghetti sauce and let simmer on low.
