Put noodles in boiling water and let cook until done.
When noodles are ready, alternate noodles, spaghetti sauce with beef, cottage cheese and Mozzarella cheese in a Pyrex dish (casserole).
Put in a 300° preheated oven for 1 hour.

title: chocolate syrup topping for ice cream
directions: Bring above ingredients to boil.
Remove after bringing to a boil.
Pour
in
container
and
store
in
refrigerator. Place at room temperature before topping ice cream.
Absolutely delicious! Makes 1 cup.
Double recipe if you want more.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Combine the first 2 ingredients; dredge meat in the mixture. Heat skillet.
Add 2 tablespoons of butter.
When melted, add the sirloin strips and brown quickly, flipping meat to brown on all sides.
Add mushroom slices, onion and garlic; cook 3 or 4 minutes, or until onion is barely tender.
Remove meat and mushrooms from the skillet; make the rich sauce.
Add 2 tablespoons of butter to the pan drippings.
When melted, blend in 3 tablespoons of flour. Add the tomato paste.
Now, slowly pour in the cold meat stock. Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens.
No lumps! Return browned meat and mushrooms to skillet.
Stir in sour cream and sherry; heat briefly.
Serve over noodles or rice.

title: tortellini soup
directions: In large saucepan, over medium-high heat, cook garlic in margarine for 2 to 3 minutes.
Add broth and tortellini.
Heat to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Add spinach and tomatoes.
Simmer 5 more minutes.
Serve with cheese.
Makes 6 servings.

title: marshmallow treats
directions: Measure margarine into 3-quart saucepan.
Melt over low heat. Add marshmallows and cook, stirring constantly, until marshmallows are melted and mixture is very syrupy.
Remove from heat.
Add cereal; stir until well coated.
Spread warm mixture in buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Using waxed paper or buttered spatula, press firmly into an even layer.
Cut into squares when cool.
Yields 24 (2-inch) squares.

title: tortilla dip
directions: Brown ground beef.
Spread softened cream cheese in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Drain ground beef and spread over cream cheese. Pour salsa over ground beef.
Sprinkle cheese over salsa.
Bake in 350° oven for 10 to 15 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: date squares
directions: Mix flour with baking powder and salt.
Combine other ingredients.
Gradually add flour mixture, beating well.
Spread batter evenly in baking dish.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Saute onions in butter until tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Simmer, uncovered, for about 15 minutes.
Pour over meat and bake.

title: myrtles turtles
directions: Grease 8 x 8-inch pan with butter.
Layer ingredients, starting with crumbs.
Pour milk over all.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: freezer slaw
directions: Mix grated cabbage and salt.
Let stand 1 hour.
Squeeze off liquid into saucepan.
Add carrots and bell pepper to liquid.
Mix in vinegar, water, celery seed and sugar.
Boil 1 minute while stirring.
Remove from heat.
Add mustard seed and turmeric.
Cool to room temperature.
Pour over cabbage.
Stir until well mixed. Freeze into meal size containers.
After 24 hours of freezing, thaw in refrigerator.
Serve.

title: good custard cooler
directions: Mix eggs, sugar
and
salt.
Gradually
pour
milk into eggs, stirring constantly.
Cook
over
simmering
not boiling water stirring constantly
until mixture coats spoon.
Stir in vanilla. Cool immediately.
Cover and refrigerate.
Pour over fresh fruit in bowl (1/2 cup to 1/2 cup fruit).

title: homemade granola bars
directions: Heat oven to 300°.
Spread oats, coconut, sunflower seeds, sesame seed, wheat germ and almonds on a 9 x 12-inch baking sheet. Bake for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix ingredients.
Roll into small balls (about the size of a walnut).
Bake 20 minutes at 350°. Makes 3 to 4 dozen.

title: mulligan stew
directions: Brown beef in pot with oil over medium heat; salt to taste. Add soup and water.
Cover tightly; let cook slowly for 1 hour. Add carrots, potatoes and onions; cook until tender.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt the first 3 ingredients together in saucepan.
Pour over the cereal.
Put the powdered sugar in a large plastic bag and add the coated Crispix.
Toss until evenly coated with sugar.
Dry on foil and store in an airtight container.

title: thousand island dressing
directions: Blend all ingredients smoothly.

title: chocolate coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into 9-inch pie shells and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 3 pies.

title: fresh peach pie
directions: Peel and slice peaches.
Mix dry ingredients and combine with peaches.
Pour into a 9-inch pie shell and dot with margarine. Cook at 400° for about 40 minutes.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: pink salad
directions: Heat pineapple (not drained).
Mix Jell-O in while pineapple is hot.
Let cool.
Add pecans and cottage cheese, then whipped Dream Whip.

title: dump cake
directions: Grease and flour 13 x 9-inch pan.
Spread pineapple (juice and all) on bottom of pan.
Spread pie filling on top of pineapple. Sprinkle dry cake mix over fruit.
Drizzle with melted butter and sprinkle with pecans.
Bake 1 hour in a 350° oven.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine eggs, corn syrup, salt, vanilla, sugar and melted butter in a bowl; mix well, then stir in pecan halves.
Pour mixture into unbaked pastry shell.
Bake in preheated hot oven (400°) for 15 minutes, then reduce heat to 350°.
Continue to bake for about 35 minutes more, or until knife inserted in center of pie comes out clean.

title: angel wings
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Chill dough for 1 hour.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown ground beef and add onion and celery.
Cook until tender.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Simmer at least 1 hour, covered.
Also delicious served as "chili" over hot dogs.

title: cream of asparagus soup
directions: Heat water and salt to a boil.
Add asparagus pieces (cover and cook for 5 minutes).
Put in a blender.
Blend until smooth.
Add in cream, pepper and dill.
Return to saucepan and add in butter. Heat, but do not boil.
Dress and serve.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Layer in order given in a pretty clear bowl.
Refrigerate overnight or for several hours.
If you want to make it even better, use 2 cans shrimp.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Combine sugar, water, cornstarch and gelatin in a pan.
Bring to a boil and cook until thick and clear.
Cool.
Line cooled pie shells with fresh strawberries.
Pour mixture over strawberries in shells.
Refrigerate until set.
Top with whipped topping.
Makes two pies.

title: turkey swiss pie
directions: Layer in pie shell the turkey, onions and Swiss cheese.
Mix together eggs, mayonnaise and milk.
Pour slowly over turkey mixture in pie shell; bake until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Cooking time is approximately 50 minutes in a 350° oven.
Serves 8.

title: bertha's spinach pie
directions: Combine in mixing bowl the cooked, drained spinach, onion, Feta and cottage cheeses, farina, dill and egg.
Mix well and add olive oil.
Working quickly, brush strudel leaves with melted butter.
Fold in half.
Place a small portion of filling at one end.
Fold like a flag, triangle or individual portion for side dish.
Brush with butter.
Place on greased cookie sheet or pan. Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: fudgy bonbons
directions: Heat oven to 350°. In medium saucepan, combine chips and butter; cook and stir over very low heat until chips are melted and smooth. Add sweetened condensed milk; mix well. Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup; level off. In medium bowl, combine flour, nuts, chocolate mixture and vanilla; mix well. Shape 1 tablespoon of dough around each candy kiss, covering completely. Place 1-inch apart on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 6 to 8 minutes. Cookies will be soft and appear shiny but be firm as they cool. DO NOT OVERBAKE. Remove from cookie sheets; cool.

title: pork chops and noodles
directions: Rub mustard on chops; brown in skillet.
Place in a baking dish.
Add the chicken noodle soup.
Bake for 1 hour at 375°.

title: homemade hot chocolate
directions: Store in
freezer.
Use 1/3 mix to 2/3 boiling water or to taste.

title: sinful potatoes
directions: Mix melted cheese and mayonnaise. Stir into thawed potatoes. Bake at 300° for 30 to 45 minutes, uncovered.

title: mustard sauce
directions: Beat egg yolks slightly.
Mix in double boiler with other ingredients and cook until thick.
Two whole eggs may be substituted for the 3 yolks but the sauce will have to be strained to clear it of the cooked whites.
Serve with baked ham.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine mayonnaise and lemon juice and mix well.
Combine all the vegetables in a large bowl.
Add mayonnaise and lemon juice. Toss until all ingredients are coated.

title: okra and tomatoes
directions: Saute okra and onions together; add tomatoes.
If dry, add tomato juice.
Cook 15 minutes.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: chicken dorito casserole
directions: Saute onion in margarine until tender, then mix with soups and Ro-Tel.
Boil 2 to 3 pound fryer and take off the bone.

title: taco baby burgers
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add ingredients except cheese and crescent rolls and simmer for 10 minutes.
Stir often and cool. Separate rolls into 8 rectangles and push into square shape.
Put meat mixture into center and grated cheese on top of meat mixture. Fold the corners of rolls and pinch together.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 450° until golden brown.
Serves 16.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Salt and pepper chops.
Brown chops in fat.
Brown rice in 1/2 cup of oil and drain.
Place back in frying pan.
Add chili powder, salt, ketchup and tomatoes.
Add chops.
Cook, covered, for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Boil and drain macaroni.
Chop tomato, green pepper and eggs. Add to macaroni.
Mix mayonnaise and dressing with macaroni mixture.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Chill before serving.

title: lemon whippersnaps
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease cookie sheets. Combine cake mix, whipped topping and egg in a large bowl. Stir until well blended. Drop by teaspoon into powdered sugar. Roll to coat.
Place 1 1/2-inches apart on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes until light golden brown.
Remove from cookie sheet and cool.
Yields 4 dozen.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Melt oleo in bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish.
Add rice and stir.
Spread out evenly on bottom of dish.
Arrange chicken breasts on rice.
Add milk to cream of chicken soup and pour over breasts, then pour French onion soup on top.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: dump cake
directions: Spread pineapple over bottom of dish.
Spread pie filling over pineapple.
Sprinkle water and sugar over entire dish.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over pie filling.
Pat with butter and bake 45 minutes at 400°.

title: killer potatoes
directions: Combine all ingredients listed above.
Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream together margarine and Crisco.
Add sugar and beat until smooth.
Add egg yolks and beat well.
Combine flour and baking soda and beat well.
Add creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Stir in vanilla, coconut, and nuts.
Fold in egg whites.
Bake in 3 greased 8 to 9 inch pans at 350 degrees for 25 minutes.

title: death by chocolate cake
directions: Pour oil into a 9 x 13-inch baking pan to cover bottom.
Add cake mix, eggs and water; stir in pan.
Sprinkle chocolate chips on top of cake and bake in 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.
Remove from oven and cool for 10 minutes.
Punch holes in cake with the end of a wooden spoon.
Pour fudge topping in the holes and over the cake.
Cool completely and frost with Cool Whip.
Garnish with nuts, if desired, and refrigerate.

title: chocolate cream(crema di cioccolate)
directions: From my friend, Carrie.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops in
small
amount
of	water.	Combine soup, vinegar, sugar and	water
in
casserole dish.
Top with pork chops.
Cover with lid or foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Yield: 4 servings.

title: beef barbecue
directions: Cook roast.
Let cool.
Tear roast into small pieces.
Take off the fat.
Place in a saucepan.
Add barbecue sauce, sugar and broth.
Let simmer for about 45 minutes.
Serve on hamburger buns.

title: mandarin orange cookie salad
directions: Beat buttermilk and pudding until thick.
Fold in Cool Whip, then add pineapple and oranges.
Crush 15 cookies and fold in mixture (break in small pieces); smooth out and decorate with cookie halves and orange slices.
Cut 5 cookies in half, 10 orange slices.
Alternate cookies and orange.
Stand cookies up.

title: never fail buns
directions: Prep time:
4 hours.
Makes about 4 dozen and makes your house smell great!

title: caramel dumplings
directions: Drop off teaspoon into boiling syrup.
Bake in 350° oven about 30 minutes.
Best made in iron skillet.

title: grilled honey-mustard chicken
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Coat chicken breasts with mixture and grill 8 to 10 minutes or until done.
(Continue to brush on mixture while chicken grills.)

title: artichoke nibbles
directions: Drain liquid from 1 jar artichokes into a frying pan.
Drain other jar.
Chop artichokes and set aside.
Add the onion and garlic to the frying pan and saute until onion is limp.

title: estelle's baste for grilled chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients in boiler.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Brush on chicken frequently while grilling.

title: grape-nut pudding
directions: In bowl, mix eggs, sugar and cornstarch.
Stir into hot milk; stir constantly.
Add vanilla and Grape-Nuts.
Mix.

title: simple salad dressing
directions: Mix all together.
Bring to a boil over low heat for about 1 minute.
Cool.
Beat in oil (Wesson or Mazola).
Delicious on lettuce or any vegetable salad.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Combine sweet potatoes, eggs, 6 tablespoons margarine, milk, nutmeg, cinnamon and sugar in bowl; mix well.
Spoon into casserole.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Mix cornflakes, pecans, brown sugar and remaining melted margarine in bowl.
Spread over sweet potatoes.
Bake for 10 minutes longer.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: watermelon rind pickle
directions: Cut watermelon into squares.
Remove all red.
Soak 2 1/2 to 3 hours in lime water.
Rinse very well and put in cold (ice) water. Bring to a boil.
Rinse and repeat two more times.
Mix syrup mixture (vinegar and 5 pounds sugar).
Add watermelon rinds. Bring all ingredients to a boil and cook 1 hour.
Place into hot sterile jars and seal. Makes 7 to 8 quarts.

title: finger paint
directions: Mix together dry tempra with either liquid detergent or liquid starch and use as finger paint.

title: pepper butter
directions: Grind peppers and mix sugar, white vinegar, mustard and salt together.
Bring to a boil and let boil for 10 minutes.
(Add 1 cup of flour to 1 pint of water.)
Add to the first mixture and bring back to a boil.
Let boil for 10 minutes, then pour into clean jars and seal.
Makes about 9 pints.
Great for hot dogs and hamburgs.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Mix together and pour into ice cream freezer.
Finish filling with milk.

title: summer sausage
directions: Combine ingredients.
Shape into 2 rolls (2-inch diameter). Wrap in foil, shiny side out.
Refrigerate for 24 hours.
Next day, prick holes in bottom of foil.
Bake on broiler rack at 350° for 90 minutes.
Chill well before serving.

title: artichoke nibbles
directions: Drain marinade from 1 jar artichokes into a frying pan and saute onion until limp.
Drain marinade from other jar and throw out, keeping only artichokes.
Chop into pieces.
In a bowl, beat eggs with a fork, add crumbs, salt, pepper, oregano and Tabasco sauce.
Stir in cheese, parsley, artichokes and onions.
Turn mixture into greased 7 x 11-inch baking pan.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes or until set when lightly touched.
Let cool in pan.
Cut into squares and serve cold or hot.

title: chocolate cream squares
directions: Mix flour, margarine, chopped nuts, sugar and salt.
Press into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool.

title: sweet and smoky barbecued chicken
directions: Place chicken in glass 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Place onion on and around chicken.
Sprinkle chicken with smoked salt and pepper.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Mix catsup, mustard, oil, vinegar and syrup and pour over chicken.
Bake for 30 minutes longer, basting with sauce every 10 minutes.

title: stromboli sandwiches
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Drain.
Add other ingredients.
Cook 10 minutes.
Spoon onto onion buns and put slice of Mozzarella cheese.
Wrap each sandwich in foil and heat 15 minutes at 350°.

title: eisenhower sweet chocolate cake
directions: Melt chocolate in 1/2 cup boiling water.
Cool.
Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating well after each one.
Add vanilla and chocolate to butter and sugar; mix until blended.
Sift flour with soda and salt.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with buttermilk to chocolate mixture, beating until smooth.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites. Pour into three 8 or 9-inch greased and lightly floured cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: macaroni and bacon salad
directions: Combine the olive oil, vinegar, salt, pepper and ketchup. Shake together very well.
Add capers and set aside.
Combine macaroni, bacon, onion and mayonnaise in a salad bowl.
Toss together lightly.
Arrange the tomatoes and eggs around the edge. Pour the dressing over the salad and serve.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating well after each.
Sift flour and soda together 3 times. Add flour and sour cream alternately, beating well after each addition.
Add flavorings.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold into batter.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan.
Cook in preheated oven at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serve.

title: crabmeat au gratin
directions: Saute onions and celery in oleo until onions are wilted. Blend flour in well with this mixture. Pour the milk in gradually, stirring constantly. Add egg yolks, salt and red and black pepper. Cook for 5 minutes.

title: dad's casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter; add ground beef and cook until done. Add the cottage cheese.
In buttered casserole, alternate layers of noodles and meat mixture.
Mix mushroom soup and milk and pour over all.
Top with Cheddar cheese and bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: mardi gras fruit cake
directions: Combine until smooth, butter and cream cheese.
Add sugar and beat until fluffy.
Stir in vanilla; add eggs, beating well after each.
Stir together and add 2 1/2 cups flour and baking powder. Combine chopped cherries, chopped pineapple, nuts and 1/4 cup flour.
Add creamed mixture.
Spoon into greased bundt pan or 2 (9 x 5 x 3-inch) loaf pans and bake at 325° for 60 to 80 minutes. (Test for doneness after 60 minutes.)

title: bean salad
directions: Anything else you want to add to it.
Pour bottle of Italian salad dressing over all.

title: choco-chip oatmeal cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat together margarine and sugars until light and fluffy.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Gradually add combined flour, baking soda and salt, mixing until thoroughly blended.
Stir in oats, chocolate pieces and nuts.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 9 to 11 minutes.
Cool 1 minute on cookie sheet; remove to wire cooling rack.
Store in tightly covered container.
Makes 6 dozen cookies.

title: cinnamon coffee cake
directions: Cut dough into 1-inch pieces; form into ball.
Roll in butter, then in mixture of sugar, cinnamon and nuts.
Place a layer of balls so they barely touch in well-greased 10-inch tube pan.
Add another layer; let rise.
Bake at 375° for 60 minutes.
Loosen from pan.
Invert so water-sugar mixture runs down over cake.

title: potato casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix first 8 things in a casserole pan. Mix corn flakes and melted butter; sprinkle over the top.
Bake for 50 minutes.

title: mexican platter dip
directions: Mash avocados and add lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Combine sour cream, mayonnaise and taco mix in a separate bowl.

title: chicken fricassee
directions: Heat lard or vegetable oil in heavy skillet over medium heat. Season chicken pieces with salt, black pepper and cayenne.
When fat is hot, add seasoned chicken.
Quickly brown chicken on both sides.
Drain on paper towels.
Add flour to fat in skillet; whisk until combined.
Cook, whisking constantly, until peanut butter-colored, about 25 minutes.
Stir in onions, celery, garlic, bay leaves, 1/2 teaspoon cayenne, 1 teaspoon black pepper and thyme.
Cook, stirring, until onions are wilted and transparent, about 10 minutes.
Slowly stir in stock or broth.

title: hot milk sponge cake
directions: In a saucepan, melt the butter in the milk.
Set aside.
Beat eggs until light.
Add sugar and continue beating.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt together on waxed paper or in a bowl. Gradually fold into egg mixture.
Add hot milk all at once.
Stir just until smooth.
Pour into 2 greased 9-inch pans.
Bake in a preheated oven for 30 to 35 minutes.
Coconut icing is great on this cake.

title: ma's potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes until tender, peel and cut into small pieces. While potatoes are cooking, hard-boil eggs and dice all other ingredients into bowl.
Add potatoes and eggs.
Put in salad dressing and mix real well.

title: escalloped oysters
directions: Heat oysters in their own juice until edges curl and brown. Melt butter in saucepan and add flour; brown.
Pour over oysters and add all seasonings and 1 cup cracker crumbs.
Pour into casserole; sprinkle with remaining crumbs.
Dot with butter and bake until brown at 450°, approximately 20 minutes.
Serves 8. Double ingredients for 16.

title: eggplant parmesan
directions: Slice eggplant 1/2-inch each. Dip eggplant slices in egg and bread crumbs.
Put in hot oil.

title: meat loaf with onion gravy
directions: Mix all ingredients together except gravy mix.
Form two loaves and roll in flour; brown in hot oil.
Put in greased casserole dish and make the onion gravy mix as directed.
Pour over the meat and bake until done.

title: marinated bean-and-rice salad
directions: Wash green beans; trim ends, and remove strings.
Cut beans into 1-inch pieces.
Place beans in a vegetable steamer.
Place steamer over boiling water; cover and steam 8 minutes, or until beans are crisp-tender.

Combine green beans, rice, celery, green onions, garbanzo beans and garlic in a large bowl; set aside. Combine oregano, white pepper, mustard, lemon rind, lemon juice, vinegar and olive oil; stir well.
Pour over vegetable mixture; stir well.
Cover and chill 8 hours, stirring occasionally.
To serve, line a serving platter with radicchio leaves.
Spoon vegetable mixture onto platter.
Combine olives and parsley; sprinkle over salad.
Yields 12 servings.

title: turkey dressing
directions: Cook onions and celery until tender.
Mix with other ingredients.
Bake 30 minutes at 300°.

title: overnight french toast
directions: Cut French bread into 8 thick slices.
Combine eggs, milk, baking powder and vanilla extract.
Pour over bread.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
The next morning, combine strawberries and sliced bananas with sugar and allspice.
Put in greased baking dish and top with prepared bread.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake in 450° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Combine dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture alternately with beaten egg yolks and buttermilk mixture.
Add vanilla, mashed bananas and pecans.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Bake in large greased tube pan at 325° for about 1 1/2 hours.
Cool before taking from baking pan.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine ingredients except cheese and potato chips.
Pile lightly in a baking dish.
Sprinkle with grated cheese and chips. Bake at 350° for 20-30 minutes in a glass baking dish.

title: asian flank steak
directions: Whisk first 5 ingredients to blend in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch glass baking dish.
Add steak and turn to coat.
Let stand 1 hour at room temperature or cover and refrigerate overnight, turning occasionally.
Prepare barbecue (medium-high heat) or preheat broiler.
Drain marinade into small saucepan and bring to boil. Grill or broil steak about 5 minutes per side for rare.
Transfer steak to platter; let stand 10 minutes.
Thinly slice steak across grain.
Pass marinade as sauce.
Yield: 4 servings.

title: cold spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti, rinse and drain well.
Chop vegetables and add to spaghetti.
Add dressing, Tabasco, mustard and seasoning.
Then add ham/Spam, if you want.
Make the day before so it marinates.

title: great grandma's raisin-filled cookies
directions: Beat sugar and shortening; add egg and milk.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder; add to mixture.
Stir until smooth.

title: no name cake
directions: Mix and press into oblong 9 x 13-inch greased pan first 4 ingredients.
Set aside.
Mix next 3 ingredients.
Pour over cake mixture.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Good!

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine potatoes, sugar, eggs, salt, 1/2 stick margarine, milk and vanilla.
Spoon into a 1 to 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Combine brown sugar, flour, nuts and 1/3 stick margarine.
Spread over sweet potato mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: zucchini appetizer
directions: In large bowl, mix thoroughly.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch lightly oiled pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes, or until set and lightly browned.
Cool; cut into squares.
May be frozen.

title: apricot salad
directions: Mix Jell-O and crushed pineapple in saucepan.
Simmer until Jell-O dissolves. Add sugar, apricots and cream cheese.
Let cool. Fold in Cool Whip. Cover top with grated nuts (1 cup chopped). When chilled, cut into squares.

title: special stuffing
directions: Mix bread crumbs, celery, salt, pepper and sage together. Beat the egg and add to mixture.
Mix with hot water to the desired consistency.
Break sausage meat into small pieces and add to bread mixture.
Stuff bird or put in pan and bake at 300° for 45 minutes.

title: crazy cake
directions: Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix 1 egg, butter and cake mix until crumbly.
Crumble mixture over bottom of pan.
Cover with nuts.
Mix 2 eggs, cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Pour over nuts.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: round steak with sherry and rice
directions: Cut steak into bite-sized chunks.
Saute steak and chopped onion in oil until onion is clear.
Drain grease.
Add sherry. Simmer for one hour in covered skillet.
Add golden mushroom soup. Cook 15 more minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix by hand real good.
Form into balls size of small walnuts. Place on cookie sheet with space between each.
Heat oven to 350°.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve hot.
Makes about 100 small balls.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Combine sugar, flour, cocoa and salt in top of double boiler. Mix in eggs until smooth.
Stir in milk.
Cook uncovered, over boiling water, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Serve over hot buttered biscuits.

title: strawberry topping
directions: Rinse, hull and cut strawberries in half.

In medium saucepan, over medium heat, cook 2 cups strawberry halves, sugar, 2 tablespoons orange juice and lemon juice, stirring constantly, 3 to 5 minutes, until sugar dissolves and strawberries begin to soften.
In blender, mix until smooth.

title: nana's popovers
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Beat ingredients with wire whisk or blend well in blender (can be blended night before).
Preheat Pyrex custard cups placed on cookie sheet or iron muffin tin. Pour approximately 1 tablespoon butter into each cup; pour batter into cups until almost full.
Bake at 425° for approximately 40 minutes until big, brown and done.
Serve immediately with preserves, marmalade, honey and/or bacon (optional).
Increase or decrease cooking for wetter or drier popover (wetter popovers fall faster).
Double the ingredients for 10 to 12 large popovers.

title: easy peas and beans salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large salad bowl.
Mix well.
May add more garlic and herbs to taste.
Serves 4.
Double recipe to serve large groups.

title: potato soup with dumplings
directions: Soup:
Cook celery in 1/2 cup of water until tender; do not drain.
Peel and cube potatoes.
Place potatoes in a 4 quart saucepan with the remaining 2 cups of water.
Add cooked celery and water, onion, salt and pepper.
Cook until potatoes are tender; mash slightly.
Add milk, and simmer until dumplings are prepared.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Boil macaroni according to package directions.
While boiling macaroni, brown ground beef in a large skillet and drain. To the ground beef, add the Cheddar soup and pizza sauce and mix well. Add drained macaroni to beef mixture and mix well.
Put this mixture into a glass 13 x 9-inch dish that has been treated with nonstick spray.
Over the top, add cheeses and bake in a 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes or until cheeses are lightly browned.

title: cheddary scalloped potatoes
directions: Cook onion in butter until tender. Stir in soup and 1/2 cup milk; heat to boiling.
Put potatoes in an 8-inch square baking dish and pour soup mixture over the potatoes.
Cover with slices of American cheese and buttered bread crumbs. Bake at 350° until cheese is melted and crumbs are lightly browned.

title: brownies
directions: Cream butter and sugar thoroughly.
Add vanilla and eggs.
Add combined cocoa and flour; beat well.
Add nut meats.
Bake in buttered 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool; cut into squares before removing from pan.
May be frosted.

title: caramel corn
directions: Boil 5 minutes stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat and add vanilla and baking soda.
Mix well.
Pour over popcorn.
Bake on 2 cookie sheets 1 hour at 250°.
Stir about 3 times while baking.

title: sugar snaps and peppers
directions: Cook garlic in olive oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat, stirring constantly, 1 to 2 minutes.
Add peas and sweet peppers.
Cook, stirring constantly, for 5 minutes or until vegetables are crisp-tender.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Cook carrots (not too hard) and save 1/4 cup carrot liquid. Place carrots in a casserole dish.
Mix together carrot liquid, onion, margarine and horseradish.
Pour mixture over carrots. Stir fresh parsley through carrots and mix all together.
Saute cracker crumbs lightly.
Top carrots with cracker crumbs. Sprinkle with paprika.
Cook at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Do not cover.

title: shrimp pilaf
directions: Mix ingredients and pur over chicken pieces.
Bake 1 to 2 hours (again according to the amount of chicken used).

title: kolby's smothered pork chops
directions: Flour and brown pork chops.
Place in a baking dish.
In saucepan, heat soup and milk.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Pour over pork chops.
Bake in a preheated oven at 350° for about 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: chicken mix
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large kettle or Dutch oven. Cover and cook over high heat until water boils.
Simmer until meat is tender, about 1 1/2 hours.
Remove from heat; strain broth and refrigerate until fat can be skimmed.
Cool chicken, then remove and discard bones and skin.

title: helen allen's wild rice supreme
directions: Soak wild rice for 2 hours.
Brown meat, onion and celery. Saute mushrooms.
Add sherry; mix all ingredients in bowl.
Bake 2 hours at 350° (1 1/2 hours in 2 small dishes).
Half recipe makes two (1-quart) dishes.

title: chocolate-nut devil's food cake
directions: Cream shortening.
Add sugar; cream until smooth.
Add beaten egg yolks; beat 30 seconds.
Add melted chocolate; beat.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Add to sugar mixture alternately with milk, nuts and vanilla.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold in.

title: corned beef and cheese sandwich
directions: Combine the first 7 ingredients; mix well.
Spoon corned beef mixture into buns.
Wrap each bun separately in aluminum foil, sealing well.
Place foil-wrapped buns on cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Yields 12 servings.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Combine margarine.
Add sugar, a small amount at a time. Cream well.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat well.
Sift flour with salt.
Add sugar mixture alternately with milk, beginning and ending with flour.
Stir in coconut and vanilla.

title: chili
directions: Note:
Powdered onion and garlic may be substituted if necessary.

title: two cheese pesto dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Serve with assorted fresh vegetable dippers.

title: hot pepper soup
directions: Heat oil in a large pot. Slice 1 pepper into thin strips. Saute and set aside. Chop rest of peppers and saute with onion, celery and carrots. Add stock, thyme and garlic.
Bring to a boil. Add rice. Simmer for 20 minutes, then blend in a food processor. Add salt and pepper to taste.
Pour soup into bowls.
Top with sour cream, mint and red pepper strips. Serves 6 to 8.

title: frozen salad
directions: Add boiling water to Jell-O.
Add frozen lemonade.
Chill until thick.
Add Cool Whip and chopped fruit.
Freeze.
Remove from freezer and place in refrigerator 3 hours before serving. Slice into squares to suit number of people.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: oatmeal raisin chews
directions: Beat butter and sugars.
Add eggs, honey and vanilla.
Mix flour, soda, salt and spices.
Add to butter mixture and mix with a mixer.
Stir in oats, raisins and walnuts with a fork. Refrigerate over night.
Drop from a spoon onto cookie sheet or may roll up in small balls and place on cookie sheet.
Put a piece of walnut on each cookie.
Bake at 300° about 24 minutes.

title: marshmallow treats
directions: Melt margarine over low heat, add marshmallows. when marshmallows are melted remove from heat. Pour over Rice Krispies, stir until well coated. Place in buttered 13 x 9 x 2 pan. Let cool and cut into squares.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Bottom layer combine pretzels, butter and 3 tbsp sugar.
Pat in 9 x 13 casserole dish and bake at 400° for 8 minutes. Cool.

title: the willows' shrimp curry
directions: Saute garlic, ginger and onion in margarine for about 2 to 3 minutes.
Mix salt, sugar, curry powder and flour thoroughly and add to garlic mixture, stirring to blend.
Add coconut milk, a little at a time, stirring to a smooth thickness.
Cook for 20 minutes on medium heat until mixture boils.
Remove from heat and let stand for several hours.
Strain.
Add cooked shrimp to strained sauce and heat until just before boiling.

Serve with rice and an assortment of condiments such as chutney, raisins, grated fresh coconut, crumbled crispy fried bacon, chopped hard-cooked eggs, chopped peanuts, chopped tomatoes, chopped pineapple, sliced green onions or chives.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: brown sugar shortbread puffs
directions: Beat brown sugar and butter until light and fluffy.
Add vanilla and egg yolk; mix well.
Add flour, stir until mixture forms a smooth dough.
Drop dough by rounded teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes or until lightly browned and set.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine first three ingredients in a bowl.
Refrigerate 30 minutes.
Shape mixture into a ball and roll in chopped pecans coating thoroughly. Serve with crackers.
Yields 2 1/2 cups.

title: lemon icebox pie
directions: Combine sweetened condensed milk with frozen lemonaide.
Stir until mixed well.
Add half tub of cool whip.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Top with remaining cool whip.
Chill for 1 hour.

title: russian dressing
directions: Blend all ingredients together.
Makes 1 cup.

title: pickled eggs
directions: Pour cool syrup over cooked and peeled eggs.
Make sure there is enough syrup to cover the eggs.
Place in refrigerator overnight.

title: six-cup salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, except cherries, in a 2-quart bowl. Refrigerate 24 hours.
Garnish with cherries.

title: salmon ball
directions: Combine all ingredients except parsley in a bowl and mix well. Refrigerate 4 hours or until firm enough to shape into a ball. Shape mixture into a ball and roll in parsley or garnish with parsley in a dish.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour before serving. Serve with crackers or on rye bread.

title: sour cream potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients, except cornflakes and 1/4 cup butter. Mix cornflakes and melted 1/4 cup butter.
Sprinkle on top of potato mixture in a 13 x 9-inch dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate chip raisin cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Add pudding. Mix in flour, soda and salt.
Stir in chips and raisins.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Add milk to eggs to make 3/4 cup.
Mix together hamburg and pork.
Add other ingredients to meat and mix together until soft. Add 1/4 teaspoon allspice and blend.
Form meatballs and place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° for about 1 hour.
Remove meatballs from cookie sheet and put into serving dish.
Make brown gravy (from a package mix) and add to meatballs.
Serve hot over rice.

title: hotstuff(wonderful for a large party.)
directions: This recipe was given to me by the hostess of an annual "Shrimp Feast" to which I was invited.
Guests were treated to a minimal menu but unlimited shrimp with a contest as to who could eat the most.
The winner was presented with a ceramic pig.
A wonderful party!

title: juicy meat loaf
directions: Mix together all ingredients. Shape into a loaf and place in a 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: cheddar potatoes
directions: Peel and slice potatoes thin.
Peel onion and slice thin.
In a buttered casserole dish, layer potatoes and onions.
Mix soup and milk until creamy.
Pour soup mixture over potatoes and onions.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Delicious!

title: cranberry festival cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add egg, beating until thoroughly blended.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir vanilla into milk.
Add dry ingredients alternately with liquid to creamed mixture, mixing well after each addition.
Fold in cranberries. Put batter into greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Sprinkle in the sugar.
Bake 45 minutes in 350° oven or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: hamburger delight
directions: Spray a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan with Pam.
Spread 1 pound hamburger over bottom.
Cover with 1/2 cup onions, then 1 can of undiluted mushroom soup, then green beans.
Cover with cheese slices.
Layer top with frozen Tater Tots.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Butter bottom of pan.
Sprinkle potatoes evenly in bottom of pan; sprinkle cheese over potatoes.
Mix soup with sour cream and spread over cheese.
Sprinkle on onion.
Crush crackers and sprinkle over casserole.
Melt butter and drizzle over crackers. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: apple crisp
directions: Peel, core and slice apples.
Place into a 13 x 9-inch baking dish in a single layer and sprinkle with lemon juice and granulated sugar.
In a separate bowl, combine flour and brown sugar.
Cut in margarine until it resembles coarse crumbs.
Stir in oats.
Sprinkle oat topping over apples, patting down slightly. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until bubbly and browned. Makes 8 servings.
Best if served warm.

title: cheesy rotini
directions: Prepare rotini according to package directions; drain.
In a large skillet, cook beef, pepper and onion for 5 to 7 minutes, stirring until browned.
Drain fat.
Add tomatoes, bouillon, Worcestershire sauce and pepper.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Remove from heat; stir in milk, Ricotta cheese, 1 cup Cheddar cheese and rotini.
Pour into a 2 1/2-quart baking dish.
Top with remaining Cheddar cheese.
Bake, covered, in a 350° oven for 30 minutes. Refrigerate leftovers.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Bring water, pineapple and sugar to a boil.
Add Jell-O.
Let set until it begins to congeal, then fold in whipped cream, pecans and cream cheese.
Chill.

title: chicken luau
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Arrange chicken breasts in baking dish. Sprinkle lightly with salt.
In a small bowl, drain pineapple juice into cornstarch; blend until smooth.
Add pineapple chunks, brown sugar and ginger; pour over chicken breasts, coating them well.
Bake for 45 minutes, basting occasionally with sauce in the pan.

title: apple crisp
directions: Put in bottom of pan 6 sliced apples.
Mix together and pour the rest of the ingredients on apple slices.
On top of this, pour 1/3 cream and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake.
Serve with milk.

title: green pea salad
directions: Mix with enough salad dressing to moisten.
Chill before serving.
Yield:
6 - 8 servings.

title: vacuum cleaner cookies(guaranteed to clean the plate.)
directions: Combine margarine, dry cake mix and one egg.
Stir together until well mixed.
Pat over bottom of 10 x 15-inch (jelly roll) pan, well-greased.
Beat remaining eggs lightly.
Beat in cream cheese and sugar.
Stir in coconut and nuts; spread evenly on base.
Bake in preheated oven at 325° for 50 minutes or until golden brown.

title: feathery light dumplings
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Cut in shortening until mixture is crumbly.
Pour in milk and egg.
Mix only until flour is dampened (dough should be lumpy).
Drop by spoonfuls on top of meat or fruit mixture as desired.
Cover tightly and steam 12 minutes without lifting cover.
Makes 6 dumplings.

title: finnish pancakes
directions: Blend eggs and milk.
Add dry ingredients and combine quickly. The mixture will be lumpy.
Pour into buttered oblong glass dish, 9 x 13-inch.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 30 minutes.
This is done when you can insert a knife and it comes out clean.
Let sit for a few minutes.
Cut into squares, topping with fresh fruit and syrup.
Serves 8.

title: no bake banana split cake
directions: Melt 1 stick margarine and mix with 2 cups crushed vanilla wafers.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Beat other stick of margarine and 1 cup sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time and beat for 5 minutes.
Add 1 tablespoon vanilla and beat. Smooth over crumbs in pan.
Drain pineapple and spread over topping.
Slice bananas and add to top of pineapple.
Cover with Cool Whip, add 1/4 crushed wafers and then add chopped nuts. Refrigerate overnight.

title: french onion soup
directions: Simmer onions in beef stock until very tender.
Salt and pepper to taste.
To serve, pour hot soup in bowl.
Lay crouton on top.
Add Mozzarella cheese.
Serve immediately.

title: rice krispies treats
directions: Melt together caramels, margarine and milk until smooth.
Dip marshmallows in caramel sauce and roll in Rice Krispies.

title: gringo chili
directions: Brown meat and onion; drain. Add back to skillet. Heat all ingredients together until cheese is melted. Serve with tortilla chips or taco shells.

title: stuffed grapevine leaves(dolmathes)
directions: Mix all ingredients except leaves in water.
Salt and pepper to taste. In the center of each leaf, place a heaping teaspoonful of mixture.
Starting from stem, roll, turning in ends and roll tightly to avoid filling coming out.
Form into oblong rolls. Arrange in compact layers in large saucepan and place a dish over rolls to prevent breaking up when boiling.
Add water.
Bring to a boil over high flame.
Reduce heat and cook 25 minutes over medium heat.
Remove from stove and drain off broth into a separate bowl, to be used in avgolemono sauce.
Pour avgolemono sauce over rolls and let stand.
Serve hot.
Serves 5 to 6.
Avgolemono Sauce is also in this cookbook.

title: tacos in pasta shells
directions: Cook pasta shells according to package directions.
Drain and toss with melted butter or margarine.
Brown ground beef, stirring to crumble; drain.
Stir in cream cheese, chili powder and salt; simmer 5 minutes.

title: spaghetti omelette
directions: Mix spaghetti with egg.
Heat frying pan with oil and press 1/2 the spaghetti into it.
Add the grated cheese and top with remaining spaghetti.
Cook until golden on the bottom and flip. Continue to cook until golden.
Cut with pizza cutter.
Serve with warm spaghetti sauce, if desired.
It's good without the sauce.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Mix Jell-O.
Let cool. Cook sugar and pineapple 3 minutes. Put into Jell-O and let cool; start to gel.
Grate cheese, then mix in Jell-O and add nuts.
Fold in whipped cream.
Chill until firm.

title: stuffed french toast
directions: Put 1/2 bread in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Cover with cubed cream cheese.
Add rest of bread.
In a bowl, mix eggs, syrup and milk.
Pour over bread and cheese.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Serve with maple syrup.

title: blueberry jello salad
directions: Drain fruit and reserve 1 cup liquid. Dissolve Jell-O in water and liquid from fruit. Add fruit. Let congeal.

title: dirt or sand casserole
directions: Crumble cookies (dirt or sand) in food processor.
Cream together cream cheese and sugar.
Add pudding mix and milk.
Mix until firm.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Layer cookie crumbs and mixture in clean sand buckets, starting with cookies, ending with cookies.

title: plantation casserole
directions: Brown and drain beef.
Cook and drain noodles.
Mix everything together, adding green peas last.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: ginger sauced carrots(microwave)
directions: In microwave dish, stir together all ingredients, except almonds.
Cover and cook on High for 12 to 14 minutes or until carrots are tender.
Sprinkle with almonds before serving.

title: hot jam
directions: The peppers and vinegar equals 6 cups.
Boil the peppers, vinegar and sugar to about jelly temperature.
Add the Certo liquid.
Return to boil for 3 minutes.
Fill jars and seal.

title: flaky pie crust
directions: In a medium bowl, sift together flour and salt.
Dribble oil over flour.
Mix with flour until oil and flour are mixed.
Dribble water over this mixture.
Stir to form smooth ball.
Dampen work surface.
Put large wax paper down.
Put dough on this.
Cover with another piece of wax paper.
Roll out.
Remove wax paper.
Shape in pie plate.
Prick holes in shell for cream pies.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes in a 425° oven.

title: coconut cake
